agnClkSrcPortAdminStatus.description: This object indicates the Recovered Clock Administrative Status.

agnClkSrcPortType.name: agnClkSrcPortType
agnClkSrcPortType.description: This object is relevant only in case of Recovery Clock. It indicates the Clock Type.

agnClkSrcPortQuality.name: agnClkSrcPortQuality
agnClkSrcPortQuality.description: This object indicates the Clock Source Quality.

agnClkSrcPortNetType.name: agnClkSrcPortNetType
agnClkSrcPortNetType.description: This object is relevant only in case of Recovery Clock. It indicates the Clock Network Type, i.e. the PSN network characteristics and behavior.

agnClkSrcPortState.name: agnClkSrcPortState
agnClkSrcPortState.description: This object indicates the Clock State. freeRun(1) - Clock recovery is not locked to any clock. frequencyAcquisition(2) - Adaptive clock recovery is learning the frequency. rapidPhaseLock(3) - Clock recovery is in training process till it reaches fine phase lock. finePhaseLock(4) - Clock is locked and clock recovery is qualified and stable. holdover(5) - Clock recovery is in holdover mode. notApplicable(6) - Clock recovery is not applicable. .

agnCurrClkObjIdx.name: agnCurrClkObjIdx
agnCurrClkObjIdx.description: This MIB object identifies the object for which the Clock Source is used (System, Other System, Card).

agnCurrClkMode.name: agnCurrClkMode
agnCurrClkMode.description: Current Clock Source Mode. master - refers Master clock fallback - refers Fallback clock internal - only when both Master and Fallback Sources failed

agnCurrClkSrc.name: agnCurrClkSrc
agnCurrClkSrc.description: This object indicates the Current Clock Source.

agnCurrClkPort.name: agnCurrClkPort
agnCurrClkPort.description: This object indicates the Port/Interface Index of the port that is Currently used as Clock Source.

agnCurrClkHoldover.name: agnCurrClkHoldover
agnCurrClkHoldover.description: Current Clock Holdover State. As a last resort, in the absence of higher quality timing: - a SONET/SDH object can enter 'holdover' state, until higher quality external timing becomes available again. In this state (value=yes) the SONET/SDH object uses its own timing circuits for clock of the SONET/SDH signal. - for other objects, the 'holdover'=yes state means that the object uses last available clock (stored by the object) for a pre-defined time, until another clock source is used.

agnCurrClkSsmBased.name: agnCurrClkSsmBased
agnCurrClkSsmBased.description: This parameter indicates whether clock source is selected based on receive clock quality. Clock quality is indicated in S1 byte inside SONET/SDH overhead, (encoded as SSM - Synchronization Status Messaging).

agnCurrClkState.name: agnCurrClkState
agnCurrClkState.description: This object indicates the Current Clock State. freeRun(1) - Current clock state machine is not locked and run from the internal oscillator. rapidPhaseLock(2) - Current clock state machine is locked. finePhaseLock(3) - Current clock state machine is in pre-locking. holdover(4) - Current clock state machine is in holdover mode (due to loss of event). .

agnCurrClkQualification.name: agnCurrClkQualification
agnCurrClkQualification.description: This object indicates the Current Clock Qualification and defines whether the PLL can locked according to the stratum definitions.

agnClkCurrentEntry.name: agnClkCurrentEntry
agnClkCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the Clock Current table.

agnClkCurrentIndex.name: agnClkCurrentIndex
agnClkCurrentIndex.description: An Index that is uniquely represents the Clock.

agnClkCurrentRxPackets.name: agnClkCurrentRxPackets
agnClkCurrentRxPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Packets, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

agnClkCurrentLostPackets.name: agnClkCurrentLostPackets
agnClkCurrentLostPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of Lost Packets, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

agnClkCurrentOutOfOrderPackets.name: agnClkCurrentOutOfOrderPackets
agnClkCurrentOutOfOrderPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of times Out-of-Order Packets encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

agnClkCurrentBufferUnderflow.name: agnClkCurrentBufferUnderflow
agnClkCurrentBufferUnderflow.description: The counter associated with the number of times Underflow event encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

agnClkIntervalEntry.name: agnClkIntervalEntry
agnClkIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the Clock Interval table.

agnClkIntervalIndex.name: agnClkIntervalIndex
agnClkIntervalIndex.description: An Index that is uniquely represents the Clock.

agnClkIntervalNumber.name: agnClkIntervalNumber
agnClkIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals exist).

agnClkIntervalRxPackets.name: agnClkIntervalRxPackets
agnClkIntervalRxPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Packets, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

agnClkIntervalLostPackets.name: agnClkIntervalLostPackets
agnClkIntervalLostPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of Lost Packets, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

agnClkIntervalOutOfOrderPackets.name: agnClkIntervalOutOfOrderPackets
agnClkIntervalOutOfOrderPackets.description: The counter associated with the number of times Out-of-Order Packets are detected, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

agnClkIntervalBufferUnderflow.name: agnClkIntervalBufferUnderflow
agnClkIntervalBufferUnderflow.description: The counter associated with the number of times Underflow event is detected, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

agnMaxNoOfConns.name: agnMaxNoOfConns
agnMaxNoOfConns.description: This variable indicates the maximum number of connections that can be configured for the agent.

lagTable.name: lagTable
lagTable.description: A table defining Link Aggregation Groups port association, and other parameters.

lagEntry.name: lagEntry
lagEntry.description: An entry in the LAG table.

lagCnfgIdx.name: lagCnfgIdx
lagCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

lagIdx.name: lagIdx
lagIdx.description: This object indicates LAG unique index.

lagPortMembers.name: lagPortMembers
lagPortMembers.description: The set of ports which are permanently assigned to the Link Aggregation Group. The default value of this object is a string of zeros.

lagDistributionMethod.name: lagDistributionMethod
lagDistributionMethod.description: This object defines the criteria for the 802.3ad (LAG) to split the traffic between ports

lagRecoveryMode.name: lagRecoveryMode
lagRecoveryMode.description: This object defines whether traffic will be returned to a port after its recovery. This object is applicable only when lagDistributionMethod= oneToOne (3).

lagWaitToRestore.name: lagWaitToRestore
lagWaitToRestore.description: This object defines traffic recovery time (in seconds) to the port after its recovery. This object is applicable only when lagRecoveryMode= revertive (3).

lagRowStatus.name: lagRowStatus
lagRowStatus.description: This object enables user to create/delete entries of this table. Note: When using LAG standard package, this table is static, hence, only the values active(1), notInService(2) are used.

lagShutDownDurationUponFlip.name: lagShutDownDurationUponFlip
lagShutDownDurationUponFlip.description: This object defines the duration (in seconds) the active port transmission is shut down after LAG Flip occurs. The transmission is shut down and then opened again (after the duration defined by this object), in order to cause the other side to flip to the new active port. 0=no shut-down. This object is applicable only when lagDistributionMethod=oneToOne(3) and mainly when each of the Links of our device is connected to a different device.

lagRdnMethod.name: lagRdnMethod
lagRdnMethod.description: This object defines the redundancy method.

lagLacpEnable.name: lagLacpEnable
lagLacpEnable.description: Enabling/Disabling the LACP for a LAG. The LACP will be enabled for all ports belonging to this LAG.

lagStatTable.name: lagStatTable
lagStatTable.description: A table defining Link Aggregation Groups Redundancy. This table is applicable only when lagDistributionMethod = oneToOne.

lagStatEntry.name: lagStatEntry
lagStatEntry.description: An entry in the LAG Status table.

lagStatForcePort.name: lagStatForcePort
lagStatForcePort.description: This object enables user to enforce the active port. 0 = No Enforcement; Otherwise the ifIndex of the port.

lagStatActivePort.name: lagStatActivePort
lagStatActivePort.description: This object indicates the current active port. It is applicable only when lagDistributionMethod = oneToOne. The value is the ifIndex of the port. 0 = none of the ports is active.

gfpCnfgTable.name: gfpCnfgTable
gfpCnfgTable.description: Configuration table for GFP (General Framing Protocol).

gfpCnfgEntry.name: gfpCnfgEntry
gfpCnfgEntry.description: An entry in the GFP configuration table.

gfpPayloadFcs.name: gfpPayloadFcs
gfpPayloadFcs.description: This object defines whether protocol header will include FCS.

gfpRxTxScramble.name: gfpRxTxScramble
gfpRxTxScramble.description: This object defines whether transmission will be scrambled.

gfpVcatHeader.name: gfpVcatHeader
gfpVcatHeader.description: VCAT header is LCAS CONTROL packet as described in the G-7043. one control packet is transmitted in a period of 16 Multi frame

agnGroupTable.name: agnGroupTable
agnGroupTable.description: A table that enables associating components to Group/s (or removing components of a group). The Group Idx can then be used in other tables (e.g alarmForwardingTable).

agnGroupCnfgIdx.name: agnGroupCnfgIdx
agnGroupCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

agnGroupIdx.name: agnGroupIdx
agnGroupIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Group Index.

agnGroupComponentIdx.name: agnGroupComponentIdx
agnGroupComponentIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Component Index that belongs to the Group defined by agnGroupIdx.

agnGroupRowStatus.name: agnGroupRowStatus
agnGroupRowStatus.description: This object enables user to create/delete entries of this table. destroy - If a Group is used in another table, Agent may not allow destroying the entry/ies that belong to this Group Index.

agnStatNoOfUploadedIntervals.name: agnStatNoOfUploadedIntervals
agnStatNoOfUploadedIntervals.description: This parameter indicates the Number of Intervals that were successfully collected and uploaded in the last statistics collection session.

agnSyslogDeviceUdpPort.name: agnSyslogDeviceUdpPort
agnSyslogDeviceUdpPort.description: The UDP Port of the device, from which Syslog messages are sent. Default=514.

agnSyslogFacility.name: agnSyslogFacility
agnSyslogFacility.description: A user defined SW module, task or function, from which Syslog messages are sent to the remote Server.

agnSyslogSeverityLevel.name: agnSyslogSeverityLevel
agnSyslogSeverityLevel.description: Device will send events equal or exceeding this severity level (configured by user).

agnNetworkInterfaceType.name: agnNetworkInterfaceType
agnNetworkInterfaceType.description: This MIB object indicates the network interface type to be used by the device. It is used for devices that use only one network port type.

agnTrapDelay.name: agnTrapDelay
agnTrapDelay.description: This variable enables the user to set a delay (in seconds) before a trap is sent. This delay will be used only for traps that need to be sent during device initialization. It is needed because the device connected to our device starts transmitting traps later. The delay starts from the end of the Boot process. The device will keep the init traps in the correct order, and cancel those which clear former ones in the list. After this init delay, traps will be sent without a delay.

agnStringToIndexTable.name: agnStringToIndexTable
agnStringToIndexTable.description: This table holds the conversions of tables from unique String to numeric index.

agnStringToIndexTableId.name: agnStringToIndexTableId
agnStringToIndexTableId.description: The OBJECT IDENTIFIER of the Table, having as index numeric values. In this table, the value of agnStringToIndexUserName is an attribute.

agnStringToIndexUserName.name: agnStringToIndexUserName
agnStringToIndexUserName.description: This object indicates a unique name used by agnStringToIndexTableId, although it is not it's index.

agnRowPointerTable.name: agnRowPointerTable
agnRowPointerTable.description: This table holds information about a specific entry in a table. For example, number of usages of this row.

agnRowPointerIndex.name: agnRowPointerIndex
agnRowPointerIndex.description: The OBJECT IDENTIFIER of an entry in a table.

agnRowPointerNoOfUsages.name: agnRowPointerNoOfUsages
agnRowPointerNoOfUsages.description: The number of usages of specific entry in a table, which is pointed by agnRowPointerIndex.Usually, when the value of this counter is greater than 0,the entry cannot be removed.

radTransportDomainSnmpEfmOam.name: radTransportDomainSnmpEfmOam
radTransportDomainSnmpEfmOam.description: The SNMP over EFM OAM transport domain. The corresponding transport address is of type RadTransportAddressEfmOam for EFM OAM addresses (port).

RadTransportAddressType.name: RadTransportAddressType
RadTransportAddressType.description: A value that represents a transport domain. This is the enumerated version of the transport domain registrations in this MIB module. It was added in RAD MIB due to the fact that it is not defined in Standard MIB. The enumerated values have the following meaning: unknown(0) unknown transport address type efmOam (1) radTransportDomainSnmpEfmOam This textual convention can be used to represent transport domains in situations where a syntax of TransportDomain is unwieldy (for example, when used as an index). The usage of this textual convention implies that additional transport domains can only be supported by updating this MIB module.

RadTransportAddressEfmOam.name: RadTransportAddressEfmOam
RadTransportAddressEfmOam.description: Represents a transport address consisting of an EFM OAM port number.

tftpStatusChangeTrap.name: tftpStatusChangeTrap
tftpStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the status of tftp changed.

agnStatusChangeTrap.name: agnStatusChangeTrap
agnStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the state of the entity the agent is responsible for changed. TDM devices will send agnTestStatus variable to indicate the current test status.

prtStatusChangeTrap.name: prtStatusChangeTrap
prtStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the state of a port changed. Attached, will be parameter/s that indicate the new port status. The attached variables will be specified in the specifications of the products supporting this trap.

swdlStatusResult.name: swdlStatusResult
swdlStatusResult.description: This notification is sent when Software Down Load is finished. The attached object indicates the File Name.

intSwdlSlotFileMismatch.name: intSwdlSlotFileMismatch
intSwdlSlotFileMismatch.description: This notification is sent when the card in the chosen slot doesn't match the chosen file. The attached object indicates the File Name.

agnCounterChange.name: agnCounterChange
agnCounterChange.description: This notification is sent when the value of a specific Counter is changed. Agent can send as attached object the updated Counter. For details about this Counter and attached object, see spec of the relevant application.

prtClkSrcChangeTrap.name: prtClkSrcChangeTrap
prtClkSrcChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any port clock change.

moduleFailTrap.name: moduleFailTrap
moduleFailTrap.description: This trap is sent upon a module failure.

moduleInitFailTrap.name: moduleInitFailTrap
moduleInitFailTrap.description: This trap is sent upon a module initialization failure.

clkSrcChangeTrap.name: clkSrcChangeTrap
clkSrcChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change in Clock Source.

agnUploadDataTrap.name: agnUploadDataTrap
agnUploadDataTrap.description: This trap is sent upon an upload data session termination. For more details see product specification.

enrollmentTrap.name: enrollmentTrap
enrollmentTrap.description: This trap is a periodically trap, which sent to manager untill Agent get any response (Get or Set) from this manager.

agnPowerFailureTrap.name: agnPowerFailureTrap
agnPowerFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent upon power failure. It is applicable for the following devices: 1. Devices having one PS unit, which sense the failure in advance, and still have time to send this trap before it goes off. 2. Devices having 2 PS units and send this trap in order to notify a failure in one of the units.

agnFanFailureTrap.name: agnFanFailureTrap
agnFanFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent upon fan failure/recovery.

agnSystemParameterChangeTrap.name: agnSystemParameterChangeTrap
agnSystemParameterChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change of the systemParameter value.

agnConfigDBChecksumError.name: agnConfigDBChecksumError
agnConfigDBChecksumError.description: This trap indicates that the database currently stored in the non-volatile memory of the device is corrupted

agnAlarmBufferOverflow.name: agnAlarmBufferOverflow
agnAlarmBufferOverflow.description: This trap indicates that the quantity of alarm messages which have been written in the alarm buffer, since the last clear command, exceeds predefined threshold. (Buffer size) The new alarms are overwriting the oldest alarms (the first alarms written in the buffer). For LA-110,threshold value is 200 alarms.

agnAlarmBufferClear.name: agnAlarmBufferClear
agnAlarmBufferClear.description: This trap indicates that alarm buffer has been cleared.

agnParametersValueChanged.name: agnParametersValueChanged
agnParametersValueChanged.description: This trap indicates that due to software upgrade, some of the parameters are assigned new values

agnDriverSwMismatch.name: agnDriverSwMismatch
agnDriverSwMismatch.description: There is mismatch between the SW driver and the HW of the device uplink interface.

agnActualLowRate.name: agnActualLowRate
agnActualLowRate.description: The main link is synchronized at a rate lower than expected.

xModemFileTransferStatusTrap.name: xModemFileTransferStatusTrap
xModemFileTransferStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent in the following cases: - When an xModem File Transfer Session begins. In this case, the trapVal.1 string sent will be: 'Start'. - When an xModem File Transfer Session ends. In this case, the trapVal.1 string sent will be one of the following, according to the way the session ended : - 'End: OK' - 'End: Failed'

agnStationClkFailureTrap.name: agnStationClkFailureTrap
agnStationClkFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent upon Station Clock failure.

successfulLogin.name: successfulLogin
successfulLogin.description: This trap is sent when a user performed successful Login via Terminal/Telnet/Web. This trap is used when the device is located at End-User's premises while management is at Service Provider's premises.

failedLogin.name: failedLogin
failedLogin.description: This trap is sent when a user tried to Login via Terminal/Telnet/Web and failed. This trap is used when the device is located at End-User's premises while management is at Service Provider's premises.

modlChangeTrap.name: modlChangeTrap
modlChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever a module is inserted or removed. The trap should include the new module type (e.g. modlParamType).

licenseUpdateTrap.name: licenseUpdateTrap
licenseUpdateTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever a license is successfully downloaded or whenever a license's demo duration is expired.

agnClkSrcStateChangeTrap.name: agnClkSrcStateChangeTrap
agnClkSrcStateChangeTrap.description: The trap is sent upon change in Recovery Clock State.

agnSelfTestResultChangeTrap.name: agnSelfTestResultChangeTrap
agnSelfTestResultChangeTrap.description: The trap is sent upon each change in the result of a Self State operation.

agnClkSrcFrequencyAlarmTrap.name: agnClkSrcFrequencyAlarmTrap
agnClkSrcFrequencyAlarmTrap.description: The trap is sent upon Recovered Clock Frequency alarm.

radBridgeAction.name: radBridgeAction
radBridgeAction.description: This variable enables the operator to perform one of the specified actions on the tables maintained by the network device. Send actions are not currently implemented. Not all actions can be performed on all bridges.

radBridgeInactiveArpTimeOut.name: radBridgeInactiveArpTimeOut
radBridgeInactiveArpTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum time period that can pass between ARP requests concerning an entry in the ARP table. After this time period, the entry is deleted from the table.

radBridgeMaskTable.name: radBridgeMaskTable
radBridgeMaskTable.description: Mask tables enable definition of forwarding restrictions and control of message flow in the internetwork. Each entry in this table defines a mask statement consisting of up to three mask definitions and an action defined by radBridgeMaskOper. Different types of mask entries are supported, as defined by radBridgeMaskType.

radBridgeMaskType.name: radBridgeMaskType
radBridgeMaskType.description: Defines the type of mask entry.

radBridgeMaskIfIndex.name: radBridgeMaskIfIndex
radBridgeMaskIfIndex.description: Specifies the if Index of the interface to which the mask is applied.

radBridgeMaskNum.name: radBridgeMaskNum
radBridgeMaskNum.description: The Mask entry number, defined by its line number in the mask table.

radBridgeMaskDest.name: radBridgeMaskDest
radBridgeMaskDest.description: Specifies the type of destination address carried by the frame to which the mask will be applied. Unassigned-condition deactivates the mask entry.

radBridgeMaskPat1.name: radBridgeMaskPat1
radBridgeMaskPat1.description: Describes the mask field which is either a 16 bit binary pattern, or four digit hexadecimal pattern.

radBridgeMaskActiveBit1.name: radBridgeMaskActiveBit1
radBridgeMaskActiveBit1.description: Specifies the positions of the wild card characters (*) in the radBridgeMaskPat1 field.

radBridgeMaskFrom1.name: radBridgeMaskFrom1
radBridgeMaskFrom1.description: Offset base of radBridgeMaskPat1 within the frame. Net can be in some cases the data start point.

radBridgeMaskOffset1.name: radBridgeMaskOffset1
radBridgeMaskOffset1.description: Specifies the radBridgeMaskPat1 offset within the frame (in bytes) from the base defined in by radBridgeMaskForm1.The mask offset is an even decimal number in the range of 0 to 1518.

radBridgeMaskCond1.name: radBridgeMaskCond1
radBridgeMaskCond1.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset1 the packet contains data that matches the content of radBridgeMaskPat1. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset1 the packet contains data that does not match the content of radBridgeMaskPat1.

radBridgeMaskPat2.name: radBridgeMaskPat2
radBridgeMaskPat2.description: Describes the mask field which is either a 16 bit binary pattern, or four digit hexadecimal pattern.

radBridgeMaskActiveBit2.name: radBridgeMaskActiveBit2
radBridgeMaskActiveBit2.description: Specifies the positions of the wild card characters (*) in the radBridgeMaskPat2 field.

radBridgeMaskFrom2.name: radBridgeMaskFrom2
radBridgeMaskFrom2.description: Offset base of radBridgeMaskPat2 within the frame. Net can be in some cases the data start point.

radBridgeMaskOffset2.name: radBridgeMaskOffset2
radBridgeMaskOffset2.description: Specifies the radBridgeMaskPat2 offset within the frame (in bytes) from the base defined in by radBridgeMaskForm2.The mask offset is an even decimal number in the range of 0 to 1518.

radBridgeMaskCond2.name: radBridgeMaskCond2
radBridgeMaskCond2.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset2 the packet contains data that matches the content of radBridgeMaskPat2. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset2 the packet contains data that does not match the content of radBridgeMaskPat2.

radBridgeMaskPat3.name: radBridgeMaskPat3
radBridgeMaskPat3.description: Describes the mask field which is either a 16 bit binary pattern, or four digit hexadecimal pattern.

radBridgeMaskActiveBit3.name: radBridgeMaskActiveBit3
radBridgeMaskActiveBit3.description: Specifies the positions of the wild card characters (*) in the radBridgeMaskPat3 field.

radBridgeMaskFrom3.name: radBridgeMaskFrom3
radBridgeMaskFrom3.description: Offset base of radBridgeMaskPat3 within the frame. Net can be in some cases the data start point.

radBridgeMaskOffset3.name: radBridgeMaskOffset3
radBridgeMaskOffset3.description: Specifies the radBridgeMaskPat3 offset within the frame (in bytes) from the base defined in by radBridgeMaskForm3. The mask offset is an even decimal number in the range of 0 to 1518.

radBridgeMaskCond3.name: radBridgeMaskCond3
radBridgeMaskCond3.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset3 the packet contains data that matches the content of radBridgeMaskPat3 false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by radBridgeMaskOffset3 the packet contains data that does not match the content of radBridgeMaskPat3.

radBridgeMaskOper.name: radBridgeMaskOper
radBridgeMaskOper.description: The type of action to be taken if the frame meets the conditions of the mask. noOp = disabled (mask remains on list, but is not active) delete = mask is removed from the list.

radBridgeCODEntry.name: radBridgeCODEntry
radBridgeCODEntry.description: Each radBridgeCODEntry consists of the following parameters

radBridgeCODIfIndex.name: radBridgeCODIfIndex
radBridgeCODIfIndex.description: The interface to which this COD entry is applicable.

radBridgeCODManualConnect.name: radBridgeCODManualConnect
radBridgeCODManualConnect.description: The management station can start connection manually by setting this parameter

radBridgeCODMode.name: radBridgeCODMode
radBridgeCODMode.description: In answer mode only one incoming call may be accepted at a time. Other nodes attempting to access the local modem will receive a busy signal until the connection is terminated. (Answer mode has no difficulty supporting multiple remote connections to one local port, as blocking multiple incoming calls is just a modem function. Originate mode, on the other hand will only support a single local port to remote port connection). The disable parameter disables the COD utility for this interface. Choosing any other mode will enable the COD utility.

radBridgeCODConnectDelay.name: radBridgeCODConnectDelay
radBridgeCODConnectDelay.description: The connect delay defines the minimum time period that the link must stay disconnected, between 2 succesive connections (in seconds).

radBridgeCODisConnectDelay.name: radBridgeCODisConnectDelay
radBridgeCODisConnectDelay.description: The disconnect delay defines the minimum time period the link must stay connected, between 2 succesive disconnections (in seconds).

radBridgeCODImplicitSwitch.name: radBridgeCODImplicitSwitch
radBridgeCODImplicitSwitch.description: The inplicit switch allows the user to ignore implicit triggers provided by the COD software.

radBridgeCODNumAccess.name: radBridgeCODNumAccess
radBridgeCODNumAccess.description: The number of successful connections that have been established since the COD has been reset.

radBridgeCODTotalConnecTime.name: radBridgeCODTotalConnecTime
radBridgeCODTotalConnecTime.description: The sum of all the connect time intervals since the COD was reset.

radBridgeCODTimeTriggerEntry.name: radBridgeCODTimeTriggerEntry
radBridgeCODTimeTriggerEntry.description: Each radBridgeCODTimeTriggerEntry consists of the following parameters

radBridgeCODTimeIfIndex.name: radBridgeCODTimeIfIndex
radBridgeCODTimeIfIndex.description: The interface to which this COD Time Trigger entry is applicable.

radBridgeCODDay.name: radBridgeCODDay
radBridgeCODDay.description: The day of the week in which the dial up connection operates.

radBridgeCODTimeTriggerNum.name: radBridgeCODTimeTriggerNum
radBridgeCODTimeTriggerNum.description: Every day of the week the user can configure 3 dial up connections.

radBridgeCODTimeTriggerFrom.name: radBridgeCODTimeTriggerFrom
radBridgeCODTimeTriggerFrom.description: Time to start Dial Up connection, in format hh:mm.

radBridgeCODTimeTriggerTo.name: radBridgeCODTimeTriggerTo
radBridgeCODTimeTriggerTo.description: Time to terminate Dial Up connection, in format HH:MM.

radBridgeCODTimeTriggerStatus.name: radBridgeCODTimeTriggerStatus
radBridgeCODTimeTriggerStatus.description: The status of a table entry.

radBridgeCODTrafficTable.name: radBridgeCODTrafficTable
radBridgeCODTrafficTable.description: The table of COD Traffic trigger

radBridgeCODTrafficEntry.name: radBridgeCODTrafficEntry
radBridgeCODTrafficEntry.description: Each radBridgeCODTrafficEntry consists of the following parameters.

radBridgeCODProtocolType.name: radBridgeCODProtocolType
radBridgeCODProtocolType.description: The Protocol Type of the Traffic Table

radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerStatus.name: radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerStatus
radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerStatus.description: Command of Status of the Protocol Traffic Trigger

radBridgeCODRemoteIPAddr.name: radBridgeCODRemoteIPAddr
radBridgeCODRemoteIPAddr.description: This is the Remote IP Address

radBridgeCODIPMask.name: radBridgeCODIPMask
radBridgeCODIPMask.description: This is the Mask of the Remote IP Address

radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerProtType.name: radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerProtType
radBridgeCODTrafficTriggerProtType.description: Protocol Type for the User Defined Protocol Traffic Trigger (3).

radBridgeCODCondTable.name: radBridgeCODCondTable
radBridgeCODCondTable.description: The table of COD Condition parameters

radBridgeCODCondEntry.name: radBridgeCODCondEntry
radBridgeCODCondEntry.description: Each radBridgeCODCondEntry consists of the following parameters

radBridgeCODCondIfIndex.name: radBridgeCODCondIfIndex
radBridgeCODCondIfIndex.description: The interface, this COD entry is applicable to.

radBridgeCODOriginateConnectCondition.name: radBridgeCODOriginateConnectCondition
radBridgeCODOriginateConnectCondition.description: This condition, allows the user to specify the condition under which the link is connected. The options are onPowerOn - On power on. whenAnyStationOnLan - When any station on lan. onTraffic - On traffic. The user can specify the condition/s for connection. The connection will be defined in CODSpecificOnTrafficConditionOID . onManualConnect - depends on radBridgeCODManualConnect OBJECT-TYPE (=connect).

radBridgeCODOriginateDisConnectCondition.name: radBridgeCODOriginateDisConnectCondition
radBridgeCODOriginateDisConnectCondition.description: This condition allows the user to specify the condition under which the link is disconnected. The options are: noStationOnLan - When there is no station on lan. Counts 15 minutes from the point the last frame from lan has been received. If no frame have been transmitted on lan by the end of this period, disconnect the connection. onTraffic - On traffic. The user can specify the condition/s for disconnection. The disconnection will be defined in CODSpecificOnTrafficConditionOID . onDelayFromConnectionOnRequest - On Delay From Connection On Request . The delay time period will be defined in CODOriginateDisConnectDelay . onManualDisConnect - depends on radBridgeCODManualConnect OBJECT-TYPE (=disconnect).

radBridgeCODAnswerConnectCondition.name: radBridgeCODAnswerConnectCondition
radBridgeCODAnswerConnectCondition.description: CODCondAnswerConnect allows the user to specify the condition under which the link is connected. The options are: onPowerOn - On power on. whenAnyStationOnLan - When any station on lan. onTraffic - On traffic. The user can specify the condition/s for connection. The connection will be defined in CODSpecificOnTrafficConditionOID . onManualConnect - depends on radBridgeCODManualConnect OBJECT-TYPE .

radBridgeCODSpecificOnTrafficOIDConditio.name: radBridgeCODSpecificOnTrafficOIDCondition
radBridgeCODSpecificOnTrafficOIDConditio.description: A reference to a specific entry in the radBridgeMaskTable, which describes the particular COD condition . If Connect or Disconnect Conditions are not onTraffic, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

radBridgeIPXForwarding.name: radBridgeIPXForwarding
radBridgeIPXForwarding.description: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IPX gateway in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IPX gateways forward datagrams. IPX hosts do not. Note that changing this parameter requiers RESET of the router.

radBridgeIPXRipOutPackets.name: radBridgeIPXRipOutPackets
radBridgeIPXRipOutPackets.description: The total number of packets transmitted by RIP.

radBridgeIPXRipInPackets.name: radBridgeIPXRipInPackets
radBridgeIPXRipInPackets.description: The total number of packets received by RIP. This will include any packets that are subsequently discarded.

radBridgeIPXRipInDiscards.name: radBridgeIPXRipInDiscards
radBridgeIPXRipInDiscards.description: The number of received packets discarded by RIP.

radBridgeIPXRipTblNoOfEntries.name: radBridgeIPXRipTblNoOfEntries
radBridgeIPXRipTblNoOfEntries.description: The max number of entries that exist in the RIP routing table.

radBridgeIPXRipTblBcastTrigUpdateInterva.name: radBridgeIPXRipTblBcastTrigUpdateInterval
radBridgeIPXRipTblBcastTrigUpdateInterva.description: The default time interval (in seconds)between triggered RIP updates on a broadcast type interface. A triggered update occurs when a change is detected in the routing database. This time interval delays the broadcasting of these updates so that changes on the network will not result in a lot of triggered updates.

radBridgeIPXRipTable.name: radBridgeIPXRipTable
radBridgeIPXRipTable.description: The routing table used by RIP to calculate routes to remote desination networks.

radBridgeIPXRipTableEntry.name: radBridgeIPXRipTableEntry
radBridgeIPXRipTableEntry.description: The routing information for one of this entity's destination networks.

radBridgeIPXRipDestNetwork.name: radBridgeIPXRipDestNetwork
radBridgeIPXRipDestNetwork.description: The destination network address to which this entry's routing information pertains.

radBridgeIPXRipPolicy.name: radBridgeIPXRipPolicy
radBridgeIPXRipPolicy.description: A value specifying the precidence of the route. A value of zero means that the route is the best route, a value of one means that the route is the second best route and so on.

radBridgeIPXRipForwardingRouter.name: radBridgeIPXRipForwardingRouter
radBridgeIPXRipForwardingRouter.description: The IPX node address of the next hop (router) for the entry's associated destination network.

radBridgeIPXRipNIC.name: radBridgeIPXRipNIC
radBridgeIPXRipNIC.description: An interface identifier specifying what IPX interface the next hop can be found on.

radBridgeIPXRipTickMetric.name: radBridgeIPXRipTickMetric
radBridgeIPXRipTickMetric.description: The metric, in terms of transit time, associated with the route given by the entry. This time is in terms of 1/18ths of a second.

radBridgeIPXRipHopMetric.name: radBridgeIPXRipHopMetric
radBridgeIPXRipHopMetric.description: The metric, in terms of distance , associated with the route given by the entry.

radBridgeIPXRipAgingTime.name: radBridgeIPXRipAgingTime
radBridgeIPXRipAgingTime.description: The last time that the entry was updated. The time will be provided in terms of the MIB-I object sysUpTime.

radBridgeIPXRipValueStatus.name: radBridgeIPXRipValueStatus
radBridgeIPXRipValueStatus.description: The entry status value; whether the entry is permanent (added statically), reachable or unreachable. In the latter two cases it would be added by RIP. A semiDynamic entry is an entry enterd manualy by the user and can be updated by the router.

radBridgeIPXRipForwardType.name: radBridgeIPXRipForwardType
radBridgeIPXRipForwardType.description: The type of route. Note that local(2) refers to a route for which the next hop is the final destination; remote(3) refers to a route for which the next hop is not the final destination.

radBridgeIPXRipInfEntry.name: radBridgeIPXRipInfEntry
radBridgeIPXRipInfEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one ifindex.

radBridgeIPXRipInfIfIndex.name: radBridgeIPXRipInfIfIndex
radBridgeIPXRipInfIfIndex.description: This value of Ifindex is same as radBridgeIPXIfIndex in the IPX Interface Table.

radBridgeIPXRipInfBcastUpdate.name: radBridgeIPXRipInfBcastUpdate
radBridgeIPXRipInfBcastUpdate.description: The RIP periodic update interval, in seconds. Zero value corresponds to infinite interval.

radBridgeIPXRipInfAgeMultiplier.name: radBridgeIPXRipInfAgeMultiplier
radBridgeIPXRipInfAgeMultiplier.description: The holding multiplier for information received in RIP periodic updates. Zero value corresponds to infinite aging time.

radBridgeIPXSapOutPackets.name: radBridgeIPXSapOutPackets
radBridgeIPXSapOutPackets.description: The total number of packets transmitted by SAP.

radBridgeIPXSapInPackets.name: radBridgeIPXSapInPackets
radBridgeIPXSapInPackets.description: The total number of packets received by SAP. This will include any packets that are subsequently discarded.

radBridgeIPXSapInDiscards.name: radBridgeIPXSapInDiscards
radBridgeIPXSapInDiscards.description: The number of received packets discarded by SAP.

radBridgeIPXSapTblNoOfEntries.name: radBridgeIPXSapTblNoOfEntries
radBridgeIPXSapTblNoOfEntries.description: The max number of entries that exist in the SAP Server Information table.

radBridgeIPXSapTblBcastTrigUpdateInterva.name: radBridgeIPXSapTblBcastTrigUpdateInterval
radBridgeIPXSapTblBcastTrigUpdateInterva.description: The default time interval (in seconds) between triggered SAP updates on a broadcast style interface. A triggered update occurs when a change is detected in the service database. This time interval delays the transmission of these updates so that changes on the network will not result in a lot of triggered updates.

radBridgeIPXSapTable.name: radBridgeIPXSapTable
radBridgeIPXSapTable.description: The Server Information table is used by SAP to store information of services which are available on the internetwork.

radBridgeIPXSapTableEntry.name: radBridgeIPXSapTableEntry
radBridgeIPXSapTableEntry.description: The server information for one of this entity's server entries.

radBridgeIPXSapServerType.name: radBridgeIPXSapServerType
radBridgeIPXSapServerType.description: The type of the server for which this entry pertains.

radBridgeIPXSapName.name: radBridgeIPXSapName
radBridgeIPXSapName.description: The name of the server for which this entry pertains.

radBridgeIPXSapNetwork.name: radBridgeIPXSapNetwork
radBridgeIPXSapNetwork.description: The IPX network address of the host on which this server exists.

radBridgeIPXSapNode.name: radBridgeIPXSapNode
radBridgeIPXSapNode.description: The IPX node address of the host on which this server exists.

radBridgeIPXSapSocket.name: radBridgeIPXSapSocket
radBridgeIPXSapSocket.description: The IPX socket number that is being used by the server to which this entry pertains.

radBridgeIPXSapHopsToServer.name: radBridgeIPXSapHopsToServer
radBridgeIPXSapHopsToServer.description: The number of hops to the entity on which this server exists.

radBridgeIPXSapNIC.name: radBridgeIPXSapNIC
radBridgeIPXSapNIC.description: An Network Interface Card identifier specifying what IPX interface the next hop can be found on.

radBridgeIPXSapAgingTime.name: radBridgeIPXSapAgingTime
radBridgeIPXSapAgingTime.description: The last time that the entry was updated. The time will be provided in terms of the MIB-I object sysUpTime.

radBridgeIPXSapInfEntry.name: radBridgeIPXSapInfEntry
radBridgeIPXSapInfEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one ifindex.

radBridgeIPXSapInfIfIndex.name: radBridgeIPXSapInfIfIndex
radBridgeIPXSapInfIfIndex.description: This value of Ifindex is same as radBridgeIPXIfIndex in the IPX Interface Table.

radBridgeIPXSapInfBcastUpdate.name: radBridgeIPXSapInfBcastUpdate
radBridgeIPXSapInfBcastUpdate.description: The SAP periodic update interval, in seconds. Zero value corresponds to infinite interval.

radBridgeIPXSapInfAgeMultiplier.name: radBridgeIPXSapInfAgeMultiplier
radBridgeIPXSapInfAgeMultiplier.description: The holding multiplier for information received in SAP periodic updates. Zero value corresponds to infinite aging time.

maskingMaxEntries.name: maskingMaxEntries
maskingMaxEntries.description: The maximum number of entries in the masking table.

maskingCurrentEntries.name: maskingCurrentEntries
maskingCurrentEntries.description: The number of entries in the mask table.

maskingTable.name: maskingTable
maskingTable.description: This is the new masking scheme. Mask tables enable definition of forwarding restrictions and control of message flow in the internetwork. Each entry in this table defines a mask statement and an action defined by maskingOperation.

maskingEntry.name: maskingEntry
maskingEntry.description: Defines the contents of each line in the mask table.

maskingType.name: maskingType
maskingType.description: Defines the type of mask entry.

maskingIfIndex.name: maskingIfIndex
maskingIfIndex.description: Specifies the ifIndex of the interface to which the mask is applied.

maskingIndex.name: maskingIndex
maskingIndex.description: An index to the masking table. This number should not be greater than maskingMaxEntries

maskingProtocolType.name: maskingProtocolType
maskingProtocolType.description: The base protocol for masking. IPX, IP, others.

maskingSmartMaskOID.name: maskingSmartMaskOID
maskingSmartMaskOID.description: A reference to a specific Smart mask table (old radBridgeMaskTable) which enables a more specific mask type. If this information is not available, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

maskingFrameType.name: maskingFrameType
maskingFrameType.description: Enables the user to decide about frame type * all frame * just broadcast * just multicast.

maskingFrameTypeCondition.name: maskingFrameTypeCondition
maskingFrameTypeCondition.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingFrameType the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingFrameType. fa lse - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingFrameType the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingFrameType.

maskingSourceAddress.name: maskingSourceAddress
maskingSourceAddress.description: The source address is according to the maskingMacOrNet and maskingProtocolType variables. In case of 'MAC' enter 6 bytes (48 bit) of source address. In case of 'NET' if the maskingProtocolType is IP, this is the IP address if the maskingProtocolType is IPX, this is the IPX address (nnnnmmmmmmss) nnnn - IPX net address mmmmmm - Node address (Mac) ss - IPX socket In case of 'Apple' nn - net address (4 nibbles) ss - socket (4 nibbles).

maskingSourceActiveBits.name: maskingSourceActiveBits
maskingSourceActiveBits.description: Specifies the positions of the wild card characters (*) in the maskingSourceAddress field. Only the 1's bit will be taken in considerations.

maskingSourceMacOrNet.name: maskingSourceMacOrNet
maskingSourceMacOrNet.description: The variable maskingSourceAddress and maskingSourceActiveBits will be treated as MAC, or NET address. - If maskingProtocolType = 'all', 'sna', 'netbios', dec or 'unknown', the maskingSourceMacOrNet can be macAddress only! - If maskingProtocolType = 'ip' the maskingSourceMacOrNet can be macAddress or netAddress or appleAddress. - If maskingProtocolType = 'ipx', the maskingSourceMacOrNet can be either macAddress or netAddress. - If maskingProtocolType = 'apple', the maskingSourceMacOrNet can be either macAddress or appleAddress.

maskingSourceCondition.name: maskingSourceCondition
maskingSourceCondition.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingSourceAddress (in conjunction with maskingSourceActiveBits) the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingSourceAddress. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingSourceAddress (in conjunction with maskingSourceActiveBits) the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingSourceAddress.

maskingDestAddress.name: maskingDestAddress
maskingDestAddress.description: If maskingFrameType = broadcast or multicast, this object is NOT APPLICABLE. If maskingFrameType = all or unknown, this object is applicable. The destination address is according to the maskingMacOrNet and maskingProtocolType variables. In case of 'MAC' enter 6 bytes (48 bit) of source address. In case of 'NET' if the maskingProtocolType is IP, this is the IP address if the maskingProtocolType is IPX, this is the IPX address (nnnnmmmmmmss) nnnn - IPX net address mmmmmm - Node address (Mac) ss - IPX socket. In case of 'Apple' nn - net address (4 nibbles) ss - socket (4 nibbles). The IPX socket entered here has priority over the value of maskingLowLevelProt, when it is ipxRip, ipxSap or ipxSpx, unless the entered IPX socket is don't care.

maskingDestActiveBits.name: maskingDestActiveBits
maskingDestActiveBits.description: If maskingFrameType = broadcast or multicast, this object is NOT APPLICABLE. If maskingFrameType = all or unknown, this object is applicable. Specifies the positions of the wild card characters (*) in the maskingDestAddress field. Only the 1's bit will be taken in considerations.

maskingDestMacOrNet.name: maskingDestMacOrNet
maskingDestMacOrNet.description: If maskingFrameType = broadcast or multicast, this object is NOT APPLICABLE. If maskingFrameType = all or unknown, this object is applicable. - If maskingProtocolType = 'all', 'sna', 'netbios', dec or 'unknown', the maskingDestMacOrNet can be macAddress only! - If maskingProtocolType = 'ip' the maskingDestMacOrNet can be macAddress or netAddress or appleAddress. - If maskingProtocolType = 'ipx', the maskingDestMacOrNet can be either macAddress or netAddress. - If maskingProtocolType = 'apple', the maskingDestMacOrNet can be either macAddress or appleAddress. The variable maskingDestAddress and maskingDestActiveBits will be treated as MAC, or NET address.

maskingDestCondition.name: maskingDestCondition
maskingDestCondition.description: If maskingFrameType = broadcast or multicast, this object is NOT APPLICABLE. If maskingFrameType = all or unknown, this object is applicable. Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingDestAddress (in conjunction with maskingDestActiveBits) the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingDestAddress. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingDestAddress (in conjunction with maskingDestActiveBits) the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingDestAddress.

maskingLowLevelProt.name: maskingLowLevelProt
maskingLowLevelProt.description: This field is set in conjunction with the maskingProtocolType variable. This variable specifies the low level protocol. The IPX socket entered in maskingDestAddress has priority over the value of maskingLowLevelProt, when it is ipxRip, ipxSap or ipxSpx, unless the entered IPX socket is don't care.

maskingLowLevelProtCondition.name: maskingLowLevelProtCondition
maskingLowLevelProtCondition.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingLowLevelProt the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingLowLevelProt. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingLowLevelProt the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingLowLevelProt.

maskingHighLevelProt.name: maskingHighLevelProt
maskingHighLevelProt.description: This field is set in connection to the maskingProtocolType variable. This variable specifies the high level protocols (application). As for today it supports just IP protocol stack. The object's value is a sum of the following instances values (selected by user): none (0), -- don't care ftp (1), ftpC (2), telnet (4), smtp (8), tftp (16), snmp (32), snmpTrap (64), ipRip (128), www (256), email (512), dns (1024), For Apple Protocol only: rtmp (2048), nbp (4096), atp (8192), aep (16384), zip (32768), adsp (65536), pap (131072), asp (262144) Example: if ftp(1), snmp(32) and snmpTrap(64) instances were selected, the value should be 97 (=1+32+64).

maskingHighLevelProtCondition.name: maskingHighLevelProtCondition
maskingHighLevelProtCondition.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingHighLevelProt the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingHighLevelProt. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingHighLevelProt the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingHighLevelProt.

maskingPortNum.name: maskingPortNum
maskingPortNum.description: The port number is the same as in high level protocol. It specifies the dest. port in IP case or the dest. socket in case of IPX & apple protocols. IP - This object is applicable only if none (0) value was selected in maskingHighLevelProt. IPX - This object is applicable only if the socket entered in maskingDestAddress is 'don't care'(00) AND maskingLowLevelProt is NOT ipxRip or ipxSap. Apple - This option is applicable only if the socket entered in maskingDestAddress is 'don't care'(00).

maskingPortNumCondition.name: maskingPortNumCondition
maskingPortNumCondition.description: Specifies the logical condition of the mask pattern: true - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingPortNum the packet contains data that matches the content of maskingPortNum. false - Condition is valid if at the position specified by maskingPortNum the packet contains data that does not match the content of maskingPortNum. This object is applicable only when maskingPortNum is applicable.

maskingOperation.name: maskingOperation
maskingOperation.description: The type of action to be taken if the frame meets the conditions of the mask. noOp = disabled (mask remains on list, but is not active) delete = mask is removed from the list. smartMask = the operation and destination of the mask will be determined by the objects of the Smart Table (old masking table: radBridgeMaskTable). If maskingType is codConnect, the 'block' value is NOT allowed. If maskingType is codDisconnect, the 'forward' value is NOT allowed.

maskingSrcPortNum.name: maskingSrcPortNum
maskingSrcPortNum.description: The source port number. For IP: No Condition. For IPX: This object is applicable only if the socket entered in maskingSourceAddress is don't care (00) and maskingLowLevelProt is NOT ipxRip or ipxSap. For Apple:This object is applicable only if the socket entered in maskingSourceAddress is don't care (00).

maskingSrcPortNumCondition.name: maskingSrcPortNumCondition
maskingSrcPortNumCondition.description: The same as 'maskingPortNumCondition'. Relates to source port.

radBridgeCurrentEntry.name: radBridgeCurrentEntry
radBridgeCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the RAD Bridge Current table.

radBridgeCurrentIndex.name: radBridgeCurrentIndex
radBridgeCurrentIndex.description: The index of the Bridge interface or Bridge Port. It may be ifIndex.

radBridgeCurrentIngressFilteringDiscarde.name: radBridgeCurrentIngressFilteringDiscardedFrames
radBridgeCurrentIngressFilteringDiscarde.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded Frames upon Ingress Filtering, encountered by a Bridge interface in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentFrameTypeDiscardedFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentFrameTypeDiscardedFrames
radBridgeCurrentFrameTypeDiscardedFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded Frames upon Frame Type and Tagging Mismatch, encountered by a Bridge interface in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectFrames
radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Correct Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytes.name: radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytes
radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Correct Bytes, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytesHCOverflow.name: radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytesHCOverflow
radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytesHCOverflow.description: The counter associated with the number of times the associated radBridgeCurrentRxCorrectBytes counter has overflowed.

radBridgeCurrentRxBcastFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentRxBcastFrames
radBridgeCurrentRxBcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Broadcast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentRxMcastFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentRxMcastFrames
radBridgeCurrentRxMcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Multicast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectFrames
radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Correct Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytes.name: radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytes
radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Correct Bytes, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytesHCOverflow.name: radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytesHCOverflow
radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytesHCOverflow.description: The counter associated with the number of times the associated radBridgeCurrentTxCorrectBytes counter has overflowed.

radBridgeCurrentTxBcastFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentTxBcastFrames
radBridgeCurrentTxBcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Broadcast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentTxMcastFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentTxMcastFrames
radBridgeCurrentTxMcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Multicast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeCurrentTxDropFrames.name: radBridgeCurrentTxDropFrames
radBridgeCurrentTxDropFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Dropped Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in the current 15 minute interval.

radBridgeIntervalEntry.name: radBridgeIntervalEntry
radBridgeIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the RAD Bridge Interval table.

radBridgeIntervalIndex.name: radBridgeIntervalIndex
radBridgeIntervalIndex.description: The index of the bridge interface or Bridge Port. It may be ifIndex.

radBridgeIntervalNumber.name: radBridgeIntervalNumber
radBridgeIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals exist).

radBridgeIntervalIngressFilteringDiscard.name: radBridgeIntervalIngressFilteringDiscardedFrames
radBridgeIntervalIngressFilteringDiscard.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded Frames upon Ingress Filtering, encountered by a Bridge interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalFrameTypeDiscardedFrame.name: radBridgeIntervalFrameTypeDiscardedFrames
radBridgeIntervalFrameTypeDiscardedFrame.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded Frames upon Frame Type and Tagging Mismatch, encountered by a Bridge interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectFrames
radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Correct Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytes.name: radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytes
radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Correct Bytes, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytesHCOverflo.name: radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytesHCOverflow
radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytesHCOverflo.description: The counter associated with the number of times the associated radBridgeIntervalRxCorrectBytes counter has overflowed.

radBridgeIntervalRxBcastFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalRxBcastFrames
radBridgeIntervalRxBcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Broadcast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalRxMcastFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalRxMcastFrames
radBridgeIntervalRxMcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Received Multicast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectFrames
radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Correct Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytes.name: radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytes
radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Correct Bytes, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytesHCOverflo.name: radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytesHCOverflow
radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytesHCOverflo.description: The counter associated with the number of times the associated radBridgeIntervalTxCorrectBytes counter has overflowed.

radBridgeIntervalTxBcastFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalTxBcastFrames
radBridgeIntervalTxBcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Broadcast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalTxMcastFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalTxMcastFrames
radBridgeIntervalTxMcastFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Multicast Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgeIntervalTxDropFrames.name: radBridgeIntervalTxDropFrames
radBridgeIntervalTxDropFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of Transmitted Dropped Frames, encountered by a Bridge Port in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

radBridgePortBaseVlanTable.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanTable
radBridgePortBaseVlanTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

radBridgePortBaseVlanEntry.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanEntry
radBridgePortBaseVlanEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

radBridgePortBaseVlanCnfgIdx.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanCnfgIdx
radBridgePortBaseVlanCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Agent Cnfg the following objects refer. 255=Temporary Cnfg (when relevant, Set is done only to this configuration). For Agents that support only one configuration, this object will be constant=1.

radBridgePortBaseVlanIdx.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanIdx
radBridgePortBaseVlanIdx.description: Index of the port based VLAN.

radBridgePortBaseVlanName.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanName
radBridgePortBaseVlanName.description: An administratively assigned string, which may be used to identify the the port based VLAN.

radBridgePortBaseVlanEgressPorts.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanEgressPorts
radBridgePortBaseVlanEgressPorts.description: The set of ports which are permanently assigned to the egress list for this port based VLAN by management. The default value of this object is a string of zeros.

radBridgePortBaseVlanVirtualGroups.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanVirtualGroups
radBridgePortBaseVlanVirtualGroups.description: The set of Virtual Groups which are permanently assigned to this port based VLAN by management. (read Virtual Group instead of port in PortList Textual Convention) The default value of this object is a string of zeros.

radBridgePortBaseVlanRowStatus.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanRowStatus
radBridgePortBaseVlanRowStatus.description: This object enable user to create/delete entries in this table.

radBridgePortBaseVlanMng.name: radBridgePortBaseVlanMng
radBridgePortBaseVlanMng.description: This object allows user to enable/disable management traffic on this VLAN. disable - only non-management data is allowed. enable - mixture of management traffic 0with other types of data is allowed.

radBridgePortVlanMemberTable.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberTable
radBridgePortVlanMemberTable.description: The Bridge Ports-VLAN Membership table. This table enables the user to assign: - Several VLANs to a Port. - Several Ports to a VLAN.

radBridgePortVlanMemberEntry.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberEntry
radBridgePortVlanMemberEntry.description: An entry in the Bridge Ports-VLANs Memebership table.

radBridgePortVlanMemberBridgeIdx.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberBridgeIdx
radBridgePortVlanMemberBridgeIdx.description: This object indicates the Bridge Index.

radBridgePortVlanMemberPortIdx.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberPortIdx
radBridgePortVlanMemberPortIdx.description: This object indicates the Bridge's Port Index. For some cases, it can be used as the Port ofIndex.

radBridgePortVlanMemberVlanId.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberVlanId
radBridgePortVlanMemberVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID.

radBridgePortVlanMemberRowStatus.name: radBridgePortVlanMemberRowStatus
radBridgePortVlanMemberRowStatus.description: This object enables the user to create/delete entries in this table.

radBridgeGenFlowTable.name: radBridgeGenFlowTable
radBridgeGenFlowTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for Bridge configured into the device by (local or network) management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

radBridgeGenFlowEntry.name: radBridgeGenFlowEntry
radBridgeGenFlowEntry.description: Static information for a Bridge configured into the device by management.

radBridgeGenFlowCnfgIdx.name: radBridgeGenFlowCnfgIdx
radBridgeGenFlowCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Agent Cnfg the following objects refer. 255=Temporary Cnfg (when relevant Set is done only to this configuration). For Agents that support only one configuration, this object will be constant=1. This object can be used to carry additional indexing (e.g port index) when needed.

radBridgeGenFlowIdx.name: radBridgeGenFlowIdx
radBridgeGenFlowIdx.description: For Agent having more than one bridge, this index may be used as bridge index

radBridgeGenFlowRowStatus.name: radBridgeGenFlowRowStatus
radBridgeGenFlowRowStatus.description: This object enable user to create/delete entries in this table.

radBridgeGenFlowFloodOrBcastMaxRate.name: radBridgeGenFlowFloodOrBcastMaxRate
radBridgeGenFlowFloodOrBcastMaxRate.description: This object controls maximum Flooding or Broadcast Rate: Max number of multicast along with unknown or flooded unicast frames allowed to enter any port. The number can be presented either as percentage of bandwidth, or bandwidth in Kbps. Once the limit is exceeded, any multicast or flooded frame entering from the port is discarded For RIC-155, and FCD-155 valid values are 3% , 6%, 12% and 100% = No Limit

radBridgeGenFlowQosMode.name: radBridgeGenFlowQosMode
radBridgeGenFlowQosMode.description: This object controls Quality of Service mode. User may select which field(s) (in case of fields - which one has precedence) will affect prioritization of data between egress queues.

radBridgeGenFlowSchedulingMode.name: radBridgeGenFlowSchedulingMode
radBridgeGenFlowSchedulingMode.description: This object controls which scheduling mode is used: Weighted Fair Queuing (WFQ) scheme, Strict Priority (SP) or ATM CoS

radBridgeGenFlowBasicClassification.name: radBridgeGenFlowBasicClassification
radBridgeGenFlowBasicClassification.description: This object defines whether Classification based on Port should be taken into account (either as default, or in addition to other classifications).

radBridgeGenFlowMulticastTrafficClass.name: radBridgeGenFlowMulticastTrafficClass
radBridgeGenFlowMulticastTrafficClass.description: The Traffic Class the received Multicast frame is mapped to.

radBridgeGenFlowBroadcastTrafficClass.name: radBridgeGenFlowBroadcastTrafficClass
radBridgeGenFlowBroadcastTrafficClass.description: The Traffic Class the received Broadcast frame is mapped to.

radBridgeGenFlowUnkownUnicastTrafficClas.name: radBridgeGenFlowUnkownUnicastTrafficClass
radBridgeGenFlowUnkownUnicastTrafficClas.description: The Traffic Class the received Unkonwn Unicast frame is mapped to.

radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticTable.name: radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticTable
radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticEntry.name: radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticEntry
radBridgeDot1qVlanStaticEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

radBridgeDot1qVlanTaggedPorts.name: radBridgeDot1qVlanTaggedPorts
radBridgeDot1qVlanTaggedPorts.description: The set of ports which should transmit egress packets for this VLAN as tagged.

radBridgeDot1qVlanUnmodifiedPorts.name: radBridgeDot1qVlanUnmodifiedPorts
radBridgeDot1qVlanUnmodifiedPorts.description: The set of ports which should transmit egress packets for this VLAN as unmodified.

radBridgeDot1qVlanSplitHorizon.name: radBridgeDot1qVlanSplitHorizon
radBridgeDot1qVlanSplitHorizon.description: When 'enable (3)', packets having this VLAN will not be switched back to other bridge ports which are members of this VLAN.

radBridgeInvBasePortTable.name: radBridgeInvBasePortTable
radBridgeInvBasePortTable.description: An inversed table to dot1dBasePortTable from RFC1493 with reduced information. This table index is known to the NMS and this way the needed information can be received by just one Get command, instead of searching the entire dot1dBasePortTable (where it is an attribute).

radBridgeInvBasePortEntry.name: radBridgeInvBasePortEntry
radBridgeInvBasePortEntry.description: The bridge port number for each bridge port interface index.

radBridgeInvBasePortIfIndex.name: radBridgeInvBasePortIfIndex
radBridgeInvBasePortIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB-II, for the interface corresponding to this Bridge port.

radBridgeStpCnfgTable.name: radBridgeStpCnfgTable
radBridgeStpCnfgTable.description: STP Configuration table. STP=Spanning Tree Protocol. It includes STP configurable parameters that in BRIDGE-MIB are scalars, while we need them per card/bridge/interface and per different configurations.

radBridgeStpCnfgIdx1.name: radBridgeStpCnfgIdx1
radBridgeStpCnfgIdx1.description: This object indicates the Index of the Agent Configuration the following objects refer to. For Agents that support more than one configuration: 255=Temporary Cnfg ; Set can be done only to this configuration. For Agents that support only one configuration, this object will be constant=1.

radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2.name: radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2
radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2.description: For Agents having the table objects per Card/Bridge/Interface this will be the index of the Card/Bridge/Interface used.

radBridgeStpCnfgForwardDelay.name: radBridgeStpCnfgForwardDelay
radBridgeStpCnfgForwardDelay.description: The value that the bridge of radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2 uses for Forward Delay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that the range for this parameter is related to the value of radBridgeStpCnfgMaxAge (according to 802.1D-1990 for the similar scalars of BRIDGE-MIB). The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

radBridgeStpCnfgMaxAge.name: radBridgeStpCnfgMaxAge
radBridgeStpCnfgMaxAge.description: The value that the bridge of radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2 uses for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that the range for this parameter is related to the value of radBridgeStpCnfgHelloTime (according to 802.1D-1990 for the similar scalars of BRIDGE-MIB). The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

radBridgeStpCnfgHelloTime.name: radBridgeStpCnfgHelloTime
radBridgeStpCnfgHelloTime.description: The value that the bridge of radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2 uses for Hello Time when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

radBridgeStpCnfgPriority.name: radBridgeStpCnfgPriority
radBridgeStpCnfgPriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID, per radBridgeStpCnfgIdx2 instance.

radBridgeStpCnfgStpVersion.name: radBridgeStpCnfgStpVersion
radBridgeStpCnfgStpVersion.description: This object determines the STP version used: stp - usual Spanning Tree Protocol. rstp - Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol.

radBridgeStpStatTable.name: radBridgeStpStatTable
radBridgeStpStatTable.description: STP Status table. STP=Spanning Tree Protocol. It includes STP status parameters that in BRIDGE-MIB are scalars, while we need them per card/bridge/interface. For devices that have several configurations, this table is for Status of the Active configuration.

radBridgeStpStatIdx.name: radBridgeStpStatIdx
radBridgeStpStatIdx.description: For Agents having the table objects per Card/Bridge/Interface this will be the index of the Card/Bridge/Interface used.

radBridgeStpStatForwardDelay.name: radBridgeStpStatForwardDelay
radBridgeStpStatForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to radBridgeStpCnfgForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

radBridgeStpStatMaxAge.name: radBridgeStpStatMaxAge
radBridgeStpStatMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

radBridgeStpStatHelloTime.name: radBridgeStpStatHelloTime
radBridgeStpStatHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

radBridgeStpStatDesignatedRoot.name: radBridgeStpStatDesignatedRoot
radBridgeStpStatDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

radBridgeStpStatRootCost.name: radBridgeStpStatRootCost
radBridgeStpStatRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

radBridgeForwardingMode.name: radBridgeForwardingMode
radBridgeForwardingMode.description: This object determines the Bridge Forwarding Mode: transparent - Forward all frames received (not dependent on VLAN). filter - Filter frames received according to MAC Address. filterTagged = Filter frames received according to VLAN. transparentTagged = VLAN aware + Transparent.

radBridgePortCnfgIdx.name: radBridgePortCnfgIdx
radBridgePortCnfgIdx.description: The first index of the table. It can serve for Configuration index, Bridge index or other.

radBridgePortCnfgPrtIdx.name: radBridgePortCnfgPrtIdx
radBridgePortCnfgPrtIdx.description: This object indicates the Bridge Port index.

radBridgePortCnfgMaxMacAddr.name: radBridgePortCnfgMaxMacAddr
radBridgePortCnfgMaxMacAddr.description: This object indicates the maximum number of total MAC Addresses (static and learned) supported by this Bridge Port.

radBridgePortCnfgMngFlow.name: radBridgePortCnfgMngFlow
radBridgePortCnfgMngFlow.description: This object indicates whether this Bridge Port is dedicated for management flow.

radBridgePortCnfgMcastMode.name: radBridgePortCnfgMcastMode
radBridgePortCnfgMcastMode.description: This object indicates this Bridge Port's Multicast Mode: flooding (1) - flood multicast MAC addresses forwarding (2) - forward multicast MAC addresses to the subnet indicated.

radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVpi.name: radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVpi
radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVpi.description: This object indicates the VPI of this Bridge Port's Default VCL. An incoming frame with priority that is not assigned to any VCL will be transferred to the Default VCL.

radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVci.name: radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVci
radBridgePortCnfgDefaultVci.description: This object indicates the VCI of this Bridge Port's Default VCL. An incoming frame with priority that is not assigned to any VCL will be transferred to the Default VCL.

radBridgePortCnfgStatVlanId.name: radBridgePortCnfgStatVlanId
radBridgePortCnfgStatVlanId.description: This object indicates the selected VlanId of the bridge port on which statistics are being collected. 0=no Statistics collected for VLAN on this bridge port.

radBridgePortCnfgIngressMtu.name: radBridgePortCnfgIngressMtu
radBridgePortCnfgIngressMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be received on the interface, specified in octets.

radBridgePortCnfgEgressMtu.name: radBridgePortCnfgEgressMtu
radBridgePortCnfgEgressMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent on the interface, specified in octets.

radBridgePortCnfgDot1x.name: radBridgePortCnfgDot1x
radBridgePortCnfgDot1x.description: This feature is currently supported via the variable ethIfTable.ethDot1xEnable. Determnines if the Port-Based Network Access Protocol (IEEE-802.1x)is enabled for the bridge Port.

radDot1qPortVlanTable.name: radDot1qPortVlanTable
radDot1qPortVlanTable.description: A table containing control and status information for VLAN configuration per port.

radDot1qPortVlanEntry.name: radDot1qPortVlanEntry
radDot1qPortVlanEntry.description: Information controlling VLAN configuration for a port. This is indexed by dot1dBasePort.

radDot1qPortStacking.name: radDot1qPortStacking
radDot1qPortStacking.description: This object indicates the port stacking operation: unmodify (2) = Do not add Tag. tag (3) = Add Tag to Untagged Frames. stack (4) = Add Tag to all Frames.

radDot1qPortCopyOriginVlanPriority.name: radDot1qPortCopyOriginVlanPriority
radDot1qPortCopyOriginVlanPriority.description: This object indicates whether use the original VLAN Priority of the frame, as the priority of the VLAN added by this port.

radDot1qPortDefaultVlanPriority.name: radDot1qPortDefaultVlanPriority
radDot1qPortDefaultVlanPriority.description: Default VLAN Frame priority of the VLAN added by this port.

radDot1qPortTagStripping.name: radDot1qPortTagStripping
radDot1qPortTagStripping.description: This object indicates whether remove a tag from the frame on this port, frame with double tag will remain with one tag and frame with one tag will remain untagged.

radDot1qPortEgressTagHandling.name: radDot1qPortEgressTagHandling
radDot1qPortEgressTagHandling.description: This object indicates how is the Egress VLAN Tag processed. It is mainly for use with Double Tagging.

radDot1qPortIngressTagHandling.name: radDot1qPortIngressTagHandling
radDot1qPortIngressTagHandling.description: This object indicates how is the Ingress VLAN Tag processed. It is mainly for use with Double Tagging.

radDot1qPortReplaceVlanPriority.name: radDot1qPortReplaceVlanPriority
radDot1qPortReplaceVlanPriority.description: This object indicates whether for each received tagged frame on this Bridge Port - VLAN Priority will be replaced by another Priority. no(2) = no repacement yes(3) = VLAN Priority will be replaced For Egate-100: When value is 'yes', the original Priority is replaced by the Default Priority.

radDot1qPortVlanEthType.name: radDot1qPortVlanEthType
radDot1qPortVlanEthType.description: This object indicates the Ethernet Type. For some devices, it is applicable only when radDot1qPortStacking = stack.

radDot1qPortVlanCnodeLevel1Agent.name: radDot1qPortVlanCnodeLevel1Agent
radDot1qPortVlanCnodeLevel1Agent.description: Specify if a Level 1 cNode agent is enabled or not for the bridge port.

radBridgeGenCfgTable.name: radBridgeGenCfgTable
radBridgeGenCfgTable.description: A table containing Bridge configuration parameters.

radBridgeGenCfgEntry.name: radBridgeGenCfgEntry
radBridgeGenCfgEntry.description: Describes an entry in the radBridgeGenCfgTable.

radBridgeGenCfgIdx.name: radBridgeGenCfgIdx
radBridgeGenCfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Agent Cnfg the following objects refer. 255=Temporary Cnfg. For Agents that support only one Configuration, this object will be constant=1.

radBridgeGenCfgIdx2.name: radBridgeGenCfgIdx2
radBridgeGenCfgIdx2.description: For Agents having more than one bridge, this index may be used as bridge index

radBridgeGenCfgBridgeAction.name: radBridgeGenCfgBridgeAction
radBridgeGenCfgBridgeAction.description: This variable enables the operator to perform one of the specified actions on the tables maintained by the Bridge. After performing the action, Agent will automatically Set the value of this variable to noOp(255).

radBridgeAgingTimeSec.name: radBridgeAgingTimeSec
