prtIn1p6VcPbxRate.description: This object indicates the port Rate. For Normal mode (prtIn7p8VcPbxMode=normal), only part of the values are valid (constant rate). For Server mode (prtIn7p8VcPbxMode=server), all values are applicable (user can select the desired compression rate).

prtIn1p6VcPbxPabxTs.name: prtIn1p6VcPbxPabxTs
prtIn1p6VcPbxPabxTs.description: This object defines the PABX Time-Slot assigned to this internal port. For a T1 link, the valid values are: 1 .. 24. For an E1 link, the valid values are: 1 .. 31. This object is NOT applicable when prtIn1p6VcPbxConnect=no. This object is applicable for all cards of VC-PBX family. Default=the internal port index (1..6).

prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgTable.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgTable
prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgIdx.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgIdx
prtIn7p8VcPbxCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg

prtIn7p8VcPbxSltIdx.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxSltIdx
prtIn7p8VcPbxSltIdx.description: This object indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid.

prtIn7p8VcPbxPrtIdx.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxPrtIdx
prtIn7p8VcPbxPrtIdx.description: A unique identifier of the port, within the card.

prtIn7p8VcPbxConnect.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxConnect
prtIn7p8VcPbxConnect.description: This object indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtIn7p8VcPbxMode.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxMode
prtIn7p8VcPbxMode.description: This object indicates the working mode of the port: - normal - the compressed voice will be sent to an MTML card inside the Mux. - server - the compressed voice will be sent to the Digital Voice connector, as a service to an outside user.

prtIn7p8VcPbxRate.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxRate
prtIn7p8VcPbxRate.description: This object indicates the port Main Rate. For Server mode (prtIn7p8VcPbxMode=server), the value will be notApplicable.

prtIn7p8VcPbxSignalMode.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxSignalMode
prtIn7p8VcPbxSignalMode.description: This object indicates the Signal Mode. For Server mode (prtIn7p8VcPbxMode=server), the only valid values are: - none - aBit

prtIn7p8VcPbxLinkTo.name: prtIn7p8VcPbxLinkTo
prtIn7p8VcPbxLinkTo.description: This object indicates the slot of the ML card to which the VC card is mapped. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. For Server mode (prtIn7p8VcPbxMode=server), this object is not applicable. Both ports, 7 and 8 should be linked to the same Slot. STATUS deprecated - this object is replaced by prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot and prtGenCnfgLinkToPort.

prtExVcPbxTsTable.name: prtExVcPbxTsTable
prtExVcPbxTsTable.description: The write operation into the table objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExVcPbxTsCnfgIdx.name: prtExVcPbxTsCnfgIdx
prtExVcPbxTsCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExVcPbxTsSltIdx.name: prtExVcPbxTsSltIdx
prtExVcPbxTsSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid

prtExVcPbxTsPrtIdx.name: prtExVcPbxTsPrtIdx
prtExVcPbxTsPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. VCPBX/E1, VCPBX/T1, VFPBX/E1, VFPBX/T1, VF-24/T1 and VF-30 cards have only one external interface. VF-48/T1 and VF-60/E1 cards have two external interfaces. VFS cards have also internal ports.

prtExVcPbxTsIdx.name: prtExVcPbxTsIdx
prtExVcPbxTsIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique PABX time slot position. The valid time slots are 1..24 for T1 cards and 1..31 for E1 cards.

prtExVcPbxTsMode.name: prtExVcPbxTsMode
prtExVcPbxTsMode.description: This attribute indicates the usage, process and way of the specific PABX TS towards its destination: unused - the TS is not used (no processing, no destination). compressed - the TS is used, sent for compression to an internal port (for VF-PBX cards: 1..6 for of either the same card or a VF-PBX card of the same group). For VF-24/30/48/60 - 'compressed' represents 'compressed Voice' (to differentiate it from 'compressedCcs'). In this case, the TS is compressed by an internal port (1..8). transparent - the TS is used; no processing. It is sent directly for Bypass to a ML card the VF port/TS is linked to. compressedCcs - supported only by VF-24/30/48/60 cards. The TS is used; sent for compression to the CPU. mng - the TS is used for Management (this option is used when the external port is connected to another product that has to be managed via this dedicated TS. ccs1..ccs8 - supported only by VF-24/30/48/60 cards. Compressed TS that comes from a bundle of V5.1 or V5.2 PBX. ss7n1..ss7n8 - supported only by VF-24/30/48/60 cards. Compressed TS that comes from a bundle of V5.1 or V5.2 PBX. ss7n1 can work versus Vmux having prtExPh1MlTsType=ss7(6).

prtExVcPbxTsIConSlot.name: prtExVcPbxTsIConSlot
prtExVcPbxTsIConSlot.description: For VF-PBX cards, the io1..io12 values are applicable only when prtExVcPbxTsMode=compressed. Otherwise, its value should be noConnect. For VF-24/30/48/60 cards: - when prtExVcPbxTsMode=transparent or voiceTransparent, the io1..io12 values are applicable, indicating the ML Slot this TS is connected to. - when prtExVcPbxTsMode=compressed or compressedCcs, the value will be the same as prtExVcPbxTsSltIdx, since the compression is done within the same card. - for rest of the prtExVcPbxTsMode values, the value will be: noConnect. This object indicates whether the specified compressed/transparent time slot is connected/routed internally in the Agent and to which card it is connected. For VF-PBX card, the valid selectable slots are either the current one, (prtExVcPbxTsSltIdx), or a slot containing a VF-PBX card. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid.

prtExVcPbxTsIConPrt.name: prtExVcPbxTsIConPrt
prtExVcPbxTsIConPrt.description: This attribute indicates the port to which this TS is connected. For VF-PBX cards, only inPrt1..inPrt6 ports are valid. For VF-24/30/48/60 cards: - for prtExVcPbxTsMode=transparent or voiceTransparent, the valid ports are ML ports (exPrt1.. exPrt8, inPrt1.. inPrt8) - for prtExVcPbxTsMode=compressed or compressedCcs, the valid ports are internal ports of the same card (inPrt1..inPrt8) noConnect - when prtExVcPbxTsIConSlot=noConnect.

prtExVcPbxTsIConTs.name: prtExVcPbxTsIConTs
prtExVcPbxTsIConTs.description: This attribute indicates the ML TS to which this TS is connected. This object is not applicable for VF-PBX cards. For VF-24/30/48/60 cards it is applicable only when prtExVcPbxTsMode=transparent or voiceTransparent. The valid time slots are 1..24 for ML T1 cards and 1..31 for ML E1 cards. notApplicable - 255.

prtExVcPbxTsRemPrt.name: prtExVcPbxTsRemPrt
prtExVcPbxTsRemPrt.description: This attribute indicates the end-point port on the Remote unit. VF-24/T1 and VF-30/E1 cards have one external interface. VF-48/T1 and VF-60/E1 cards have two external interfaces. noConnect - when prtExVcPbxTsMode=unused, transparent, voiceTransparent or mng.

prtExVcPbxTsRemTs.name: prtExVcPbxTsRemTs
prtExVcPbxTsRemTs.description: This attribute indicates the end-point TS on the Remote unit. The valid time slots are 1..24 for T1 ports and 1..31 for E1 ports. notApplicable - 255.

prtExVcPbxTsRemConnID.name: prtExVcPbxTsRemConnID
prtExVcPbxTsRemConnID.description: This attribute indicates the Connection ID with the Remote unit. notApplicable = 0.

prtExVcPbxTsSourceSlot.name: prtExVcPbxTsSourceSlot
prtExVcPbxTsSourceSlot.description: For VFS cards. These cards offer Compresed Voice Services for Analog Voice ports of the MP. This object indicates the Source Slot of the Analog Voice port we want to compress. io1..io12 values are applicable only when prtExVcPbxTsMode=compressed(voice). Otherwise, its value should be noConnect. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid.

prtExVcPbxTsSourcePrt.name: prtExVcPbxTsSourcePrt
prtExVcPbxTsSourcePrt.description: For VFS cards. These cards offer Compresed Voice Services for Analog Voice ports of the MP. This object indicates the Source Port within the Slot of the Analog Voice Card, we want to compress. exPrt1 - exPrt16 = 1 - 16 noConnect=100 - when prtExVcPbxTsCvServiceSlot=noConnect.

prtIsdnCnfgTable.name: prtIsdnCnfgTable
prtIsdnCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the table objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtIsdnCnfgIdx.name: prtIsdnCnfgIdx
prtIsdnCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtIsdnSltIdx.name: prtIsdnSltIdx
prtIsdnSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid For KM2100/4 Valid entries are 'kmxMlA ' or 'kmxMlB'

prtIsdnPrtIdx.name: prtIsdnPrtIdx
prtIsdnPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. For MAXcess the values will be: exPrt1(1), exPrt2(2), exPrt3(3), exPrt4(4), For KM-2100 the port index is calculated as follows: 100*Slot+Ch

prtIsdnConnect.name: prtIsdnConnect
prtIsdnConnect.description: This attribute indicates if the port is connected.

prtIsdnSignalingProtocol.name: prtIsdnSignalingProtocol
prtIsdnSignalingProtocol.description: This attribute fixes which signaling protocol is used at this port (D-Channel). It is equivalent to isdnSignalingProtocol in the isdn MIB.

prtIsdnBasicRateLineTopology.name: prtIsdnBasicRateLineTopology
prtIsdnBasicRateLineTopology.description: This attribute is relevant for ISDN BRI only. It is equivalent to isdnBasicRateLineTopology in the isdn MIB.

prtIsdnMode.name: prtIsdnMode
prtIsdnMode.description: This attribute allows the user to configure the port as leased(2) in case of connection to a TDM network.

prtIsdnFilter.name: prtIsdnFilter
prtIsdnFilter.description: This attribute allows the user to configure the port: answerAll(2): accept all incoming calls, rejectAll(3): reject all incoming calls, selective(4): accept or reject according directory table. callBack (5): In this mode the ISDN Ch will reject incoming calls and will initiate call back to the rejected phone number.

prtIsdnSimultaneousCall.name: prtIsdnSimultaneousCall
prtIsdnSimultaneousCall.description: In case of simultaneous call (local,remote and remote,local): accept(2): accept the incoming call, reject(3): reject the incoming call.

prtIsdnNumOfAbstractTerm.name: prtIsdnNumOfAbstractTerm
prtIsdnNumOfAbstractTerm.description: An object for KM2100/4 agents. 255=Not Applicable When ISDN Standard = ETSI or NTT (European) the value should be 255 (NotApplicable) else If ML speed is 64Kbps value should be 1. If ML speed is 128Kbps value can be either 1 or 2 (user selection).

prtIsdnSwitchMode.name: prtIsdnSwitchMode
prtIsdnSwitchMode.description: For KM2100. auto - The call is initiated automatically by one of the IO cards connected to KML.10(ISDN card) having ISDN Switch Mode. manual - The call is initiated by the user manually, for KML.10 having ISDN Switch Mode (via mdlSCmd). connect- The call is initiated 'immediately', for KML.10 having ISDN Switch Mode. 'immediately'- means: immediately after power-up (when product performed Reset) OR, since this value appears in the active configuration. In this case, the call can be disconnected only by power-off of the product or by changing this object to another value (or actual Remove of the KML.10 relevant card). notApplicable - For other card types.

prtIsdnAbSide.name: prtIsdnAbSide
prtIsdnAbSide.description: This parameter indicates the QSIG side in layer 3. This definition is from the QSIG Standard.

prtIsdnQsigRole.name: prtIsdnQsigRole
prtIsdnQsigRole.description: This parameter indicates the QSIG side in layer 1 & 2.

prtIsdnInterface.name: prtIsdnInterface
prtIsdnInterface.description: It indicates the interface type: lt = line termination nt = network termination te = terminal equipment.

prtIsdnCallMode.name: prtIsdnCallMode
prtIsdnCallMode.description: This object indicates the acceptance of incoming calls. Initiate - Callout Listen - Callin.

prtIsdnCallBackTimeout.name: prtIsdnCallBackTimeout
prtIsdnCallBackTimeout.description: This object is applicable only if 'prtIsdnFilter' is 'CallBack' and determines how long to wait from receiving the incoming call until initiating the call back call. The vaules range should be '1..20 sec' and the default 10 sec.

prtIsdnEndpointTable.name: prtIsdnEndpointTable
prtIsdnEndpointTable.description: The write operation into the table objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtIsdnEndpointCnfgIdx.name: prtIsdnEndpointCnfgIdx
prtIsdnEndpointCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtIsdnEndpointSltIdx.name: prtIsdnEndpointSltIdx
prtIsdnEndpointSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid For KM2100/4 Valid entries are 'kmxMlA ' or 'kmxMlB'

prtIsdnEndpointPrtIdx.name: prtIsdnEndpointPrtIdx
prtIsdnEndpointPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. For MAXcess the values will be: exPrt1(1), exPrt2(2), exPrt3(3), exPrt4(4), For KM-2100 the port index is calculated as follows: 100*Slot+Ch

prtIsdnEndpointIdx.name: prtIsdnEndpointIdx
prtIsdnEndpointIdx.description: Since more than one endpoint may be defined per isdn entity, this field is a simple index. It corresponds to isdnEndpointIdx in the isdn MIB.

prtIsdnEndpointTeiType.name: prtIsdnEndpointTeiType
prtIsdnEndpointTeiType.description: The type of TEI (Terminal Endpoint Identifier) used for this Terminal Endpoint. In case of dynamic(1), the TEI value is selected by the switch. In case of static(2), a valid TEI value has to be entered in the isdnEndpointTeiValue object. interface type as well as the Terminal Endpoint type. static(2). On Basic Rate interfaces the default value is dynamic(1) for isdn(63) Terminal Endpoints. It corresponds to isdnEndpointTeiType in the isdn MIB.

prtIsdnEndpointTeiValue.name: prtIsdnEndpointTeiValue
prtIsdnEndpointTeiValue.description: When the TEI Type is static, the value of the TEI should be between 0 and 63. Else, it is not selectable by user. 255 = notApplicable. It corresponds to isdnEndpointTeiValue in the isdn MIB

prtIsdnEndpointSpid.name: prtIsdnEndpointSpid
prtIsdnEndpointSpid.description: The Service profile IDentifier (SPID) information for this Terminal Endpoint. It is is composed of 9-20 numeric characters. It corresponds to isdnEndpointSpid in the isdn MIB.

prtIsdnEndpointBearerCh.name: prtIsdnEndpointBearerCh
prtIsdnEndpointBearerCh.description: This is the selected dialing channel. anyChannel - the system selects the dialing channel.

prtIsdnEndpointRowStatus.name: prtIsdnEndpointRowStatus
prtIsdnEndpointRowStatus.description: This field indicates whether to consider this endpoint or not. The only possible supported RowStatus vaules are active (1) and destroy (6).

prtIsdnDirectoryTable.name: prtIsdnDirectoryTable
prtIsdnDirectoryTable.description: The write operation into the table objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtIsdnDirectoryCnfgIdx.name: prtIsdnDirectoryCnfgIdx
prtIsdnDirectoryCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtIsdnDirectorySltIdx.name: prtIsdnDirectorySltIdx
prtIsdnDirectorySltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. For MX300/30 ports: io1(5) = isdn1(5) and io2(6) = isdn2(6). In ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid For KM2100/4 Valid entries are 'kmxMlA ' or 'kmxMlB'

prtIsdnDirectoryPrtIdx.name: prtIsdnDirectoryPrtIdx
prtIsdnDirectoryPrtIdx.description: For MAXcess this is the internal port number: 101, 102,.... For KM-2100 the port index is calculated as follows: 100*Slot+Ch

prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr.name: prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr
prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr.description: This is the local address associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=17 , Default=0 (17 characters) - For KM: Size=20, Default=blank (20 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr.name: prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr
prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr.description: This is the local subaddress associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=6 , Default=0 (6 characters) - For KM: Size=4 , Default=blank (4 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr.name: prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr
prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr.description: This is the remote address associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=17 , Default=0 (17 characters) - For KM: Size=20, Default=blank (20 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr.name: prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr
prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr.description: This is the remote subaddress associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=6 , Default=0 (6 characters) - For KM: Size=4 , Default=blank (4 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryPrtNu.name: prtIsdnDirectoryPrtNu
prtIsdnDirectoryPrtNu.description: This is the external port number connected to this entry.

prtIsdnDirectoryTeiId.name: prtIsdnDirectoryTeiId
prtIsdnDirectoryTeiId.description: This is the abstract terminal id if relevant, connected to this entry.

prtIsdnDirectoryRowStatus.name: prtIsdnDirectoryRowStatus
prtIsdnDirectoryRowStatus.description: This is the status for the row. It allows to know whether to consider this row or not. The only possible supported RowStatus vaules are active (1) and destroy (6).

prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr2.name: prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr2
prtIsdnDirectoryLocalAddr2.description: This is the second local address associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=17 , Default=0 (17 characters) - For KM: Size=20, Default=blank (20 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr2.name: prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr2
prtIsdnDirectoryLocalSubAddr2.description: This is the second local subaddress associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=6 , Default=0 (6 characters) - For KM: Size=4 , Default=blank (4 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr2.name: prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr2
prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteAddr2.description: This is the second remote address associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=17 , Default=0 (17 characters) - For KM: Size=20, Default=blank(20 characters)

prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr2.name: prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr2
prtIsdnDirectoryRemoteSubAddr2.description: This is the second remote subaddress associated with this entry. - For MX: Size=6 , Default=0 (6 characters) - For KM: Size=4 , Default=blank (4 characters)

prtFrPlusCnfgTable.name: prtFrPlusCnfgTable
prtFrPlusCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtFrPlusCnfgIdx.name: prtFrPlusCnfgIdx
prtFrPlusCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtFrPlusSltIdx.name: prtFrPlusSltIdx
prtFrPlusSltIdx.description: Slot Index. For ISDN BRI Ports of MX300/30, io1(5) = isdn1(5) and io2(6) = isdn2(6).

prtFrPlusPrtIdx.name: prtFrPlusPrtIdx
prtFrPlusPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. This port number should be: - for ISDN cards: inPrt1(101)->inPrt50(150) - for MHS1 card : exPrt1(1) - for MHS3, MLS3 cards: exPrt1(1)->exPrt3(3) - for MLS6 cards: exPrt1(1)->exPrt6(6).

prtFrPlusNotSegmentedPriorities.name: prtFrPlusNotSegmentedPriorities
prtFrPlusNotSegmentedPriorities.description: This parameter is relevant only for FR+ protocol and asks the MXcess NOT to segment data with specified priorities: from LSB: bit 1 is for priority 1, bit 2 is for priority 2, .... till bit 7 for priority 7. - a priority selected to be segmented : its bit will be '0' - a priority not to be segmented : its bit will be '1' Default is 00000000; i.e, segment all priorities.

prtMl4CnfgTable.name: prtMl4CnfgTable
prtMl4CnfgTable.description: This is an extension table for MTML-4 card parameters.

prtMl4CnfgIdx.name: prtMl4CnfgIdx
prtMl4CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. The write operation is valid only to the TmpCnfg.

prtMl4SltIdx.name: prtMl4SltIdx
prtMl4SltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted.

prtMl4PrtIdx.name: prtMl4PrtIdx
prtMl4PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtMl4SigProfile.name: prtMl4SigProfile
prtMl4SigProfile.description: This object indicates the Signaling Profile of the port. none - when the Frame is G732N (no MF) or Unframed. p1 = profile 1 p2 = profile 2 p3 = profile 3 p4 = profile 4 p5 = profile 5 perTS = when Signaling Profile is selected per TS.

prtMl4CGA.name: prtMl4CGA
prtMl4CGA.description: This object selects the method used to signal the CGA state to the other end, through the main link. 'none' - non-transparent mode. When one of the links (main) will be in Out Of Service state, both 'Data/Voice Oos' and 'Oos' will be transmitted to the other end. 'trans' - when one of the links (main) will be in Out Of Service state, 'Data/Voice Oos' will be transmitted to the other end. 'full' - fully-transparent mode. When one of the links (main) will be in Out Of Service state, neither 'Data/Voice Oos' nor 'Oos' will be transmitted to the other end.

prtMl4Oos.name: prtMl4Oos
prtMl4Oos.description: 'idle' = '0' = on-hook, idle state 'busy' = '1' = off-hook, busy state 'forcedIdle' = SP = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '0' during out-of-service periods. 'forcedBusy' = MK = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '1' during out-of-service periods. 'busyIdle' = MK_SP = A and B bits are forced to '1' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '0' until out-of-service condition disappears. 'idleBusy' = SP_MK = A and B bits are forced to '0' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '1' until out-of-service condition disappears. - for T1: '0'=0 ; '1'=1 - for E1: '0'=1 ; '1'=0

prtMl4VoiceOos.name: prtMl4VoiceOos
prtMl4VoiceOos.description: Voice Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

prtMl4DataOos.name: prtMl4DataOos
prtMl4DataOos.description: Data Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

prtMl4Service.name: prtMl4Service
prtMl4Service.description: Link Service. leasedLine - usual TDM interface. v51 - V5.1 interface. v52Master - V5.2 Link to Local Exchange. v52Slave - a ML that is transferred to the v52Master.

prtMl4IpMask.name: prtMl4IpMask
prtMl4IpMask.description: IP subnet mask of the port.

prtMl4SignalingMode.name: prtMl4SignalingMode
prtMl4SignalingMode.description: Refers to the signaling mode of the port (or framer module). notApplicable(1)- means that no framer is needed for this port (no signaling), or that this object is not relevant. cas(2) means Channel Associated Signaling. Used for E1 Links. ccs(3) is the Common Channel Signaling (the signaling is not within the channels time slot - a TS for signaling is used). robbedBit(4) is a method implementing 7 bits for the voice and 1 bit dedicated for signaling. Used for T1 Links. other (5)- Signaling generally exists though not specifically according to one of the values listed ; this port uses a framer in this case.

prtMl4OosErrorSource.name: prtMl4OosErrorSource
prtMl4OosErrorSource.description: OOS (Out-of-Service) Error Source. This object is applicable for T1 ports only.

prtMl4OosEntryThreshold.name: prtMl4OosEntryThreshold
prtMl4OosEntryThreshold.description: This object defines the number of Errors per Second that determine the minimum unacceptable noise level. This value will be the Entry Threshold to the OOS (Out-of-Service) state. This object is applicable only when prtMl4OosErrorSource=framing(3) or bpv(4). 0=notApplicable.

prtMl4OosExitThreshold.name: prtMl4OosExitThreshold
prtMl4OosExitThreshold.description: This object defines the number of consecutive Error-Free-Seconds before going from OOS state to Normal state. This value will be the Exit Threshold from the OOS (Out-of-Service) state. Units=seconds This object is applicable only when prtMl4OosErrorSource=framing(3) or bpv(4). 0=notApplicable.

prtMl4LogicalLinkId.name: prtMl4LogicalLinkId
prtMl4LogicalLinkId.description: This object defines for a V5.2 Master ML the Logical Link Id. Valid values are: 0..256. NA=257.

prtMl4DedicatedTs.name: prtMl4DedicatedTs
prtMl4DedicatedTs.description: A unique number to identify Dedicated TS of the E1 port (V5.2). It is applicable only when prtMl4Service=v52Slave and prtExPh1MlInbandMng selected is dedicatedTs, dedicatedPpp or dedicatedFr. 1..31 - Dedicated TS of E1 255 - notApplicable Other values are invalid.

prtMl4RemCrc.name: prtMl4RemCrc
prtMl4RemCrc.description: This object indicates whether the E1 of the Remote device connected to this E1 port, will have CRC-4 or not.

prtMl4CrossConnectLevel.name: prtMl4CrossConnectLevel
prtMl4CrossConnectLevel.description: This object indicates whether the cross connect is on DS1 or DS0 (time-slots) level. When cross connect level is ds1, Destination Slot is indicated by prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot, Destination Port is indicated by prtGenCnfgLinkToPort. For Unframed Line Type, cross connect level can be either notApplicable (NC=not connected) or DS1. Otherwise, default value is ds0.

prtMl4PppEchoFailDetection.name: prtMl4PppEchoFailDetection
prtMl4PppEchoFailDetection.description: This object indicates whether the PPP Echo is taken into account for its Fail Detection. This object is relevant when Inband Mng between devices is Dedicated TS PPP. Default=Disable. Enable - will be selected mainly when a T1/E1 Ring exists and between 2 adjacent Ring devices there is another device or Net, that causes these Ring devices not to sense that the PPP connection between them is lost. In this case, Echo Request should be initiated by the port.

prtAcmCnfgTable.name: prtAcmCnfgTable
prtAcmCnfgTable.description: This is a table for ACM port parameters.

prtAcmCnfgIdx.name: prtAcmCnfgIdx
prtAcmCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. The write operation is valid only to the TmpCnfg.

prtAcmSltIdx.name: prtAcmSltIdx
prtAcmSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted.

prtAcmPrtIdx.name: prtAcmPrtIdx
prtAcmPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtAcmConnect.name: prtAcmConnect
prtAcmConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be connected or not. Only a connected port can perform activity.

prtAcmActiveState.name: prtAcmActiveState
prtAcmActiveState.description: This attribute indicates the Electric Active State of the port.

prtAcmAlrString.name: prtAcmAlrString
prtAcmAlrString.description: Alarm string selected by user for the Inbound ports. This object is applicable only for the Inbound Ports: ext-5..ext-12. For the Outbound Ports (ext-1..ext-4), the size of this string will be 0.

prtE2CnfgTable.name: prtE2CnfgTable
prtE2CnfgTable.description: This is a table for E2 port parameters.

prtE2CnfgIdx.name: prtE2CnfgIdx
prtE2CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. The write operation is valid only to the TmpCnfg.

prtE2SltIdx.name: prtE2SltIdx
prtE2SltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted.

prtE2PrtIdx.name: prtE2PrtIdx
prtE2PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtE2Connect.name: prtE2Connect
prtE2Connect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be connected or not. Only a connected port can perform activity.

prtE2MngOnNationalBit.name: prtE2MngOnNationalBit
prtE2MngOnNationalBit.description: This attribute indicates whether National Bit will be used for Management or not.

prtLanWanCnfgTable.name: prtLanWanCnfgTable
prtLanWanCnfgTable.description: This is a table for Lan-Wan port parameters.

prtLanWanCnfgIdx.name: prtLanWanCnfgIdx
prtLanWanCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. The write operation is valid only to the TmpCnfg.

prtLanWanSltIdx.name: prtLanWanSltIdx
prtLanWanSltIdx.description: This object indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted.

prtLanWanPrtIdx.name: prtLanWanPrtIdx
prtLanWanPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique number to identify a port in a specific card. Generally, for MP-210X/2200, the Port Index will be according to the external/internal port number: - exPrtX : X - inPrtX : 100 + X For FCD-155, refer to device specification

prtLanWanMode.name: prtLanWanMode
prtLanWanMode.description: This object determines the working mode of this port. For FCD155, layer3SubnetSwitch is not applicable

prtLanWanDestIf.name: prtLanWanDestIf
prtLanWanDestIf.description: This object determines the Destination Interface for the frames received by this port. - Switching Table = 100 (it means that the destination interface will be determined by the Switching Table) - inPrtX (internal-X port): 100 + X . For FCD-155 this object is not applicable =0

prtLanWanEgressVlanMode.name: prtLanWanEgressVlanMode
prtLanWanEgressVlanMode.description: This object determines what to do with the VLAN frames that exit via the WAN side of the port. This object is not applicable when prtLanWanMode=l3SubnetSwitch(4).

prtLanWanL2Protocol.name: prtLanWanL2Protocol
prtLanWanL2Protocol.description: L2 Protocol. When prtLanWanMode=l3SubnetSwitch(4), the only valid value is ppp(3).

prtLanWanStpPriority.name: prtLanWanStpPriority
prtLanWanStpPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID.

prtLanWanStpCost.name: prtLanWanStpCost
prtLanWanStpCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN.

prtLanWanToLanVlanMode.name: prtLanWanToLanVlanMode
prtLanWanToLanVlanMode.description: This object determines what to do with the VLAN frames that come from WAN side of the port and exit towards one of the LAN ports. This object is applicable only when prtLanWanDestIf=100 or 101 (Switching Table or inPrt1).

prtLanWanVlanId.name: prtLanWanVlanId
prtLanWanVlanId.description: This is the VLAN Id attached to a frame, when the relevant Vlan Mode (prtLanWanEgressVlanMode or prtLanWanToLanVlanMode) is tag or doubleTag. 0=not applicable.

prtLanWanVlanPriority.name: prtLanWanVlanPriority
prtLanWanVlanPriority.description: This is the VLAN Priority attached to a frame, when the relevant Vlan Mode (prtLanWanEgressVlanMode or prtLanWanToLanVlanMode) is tag or doubleTag. Valid values: 0..7 255=not applicable.

prtLanWanMtu.name: prtLanWanMtu
prtLanWanMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. Valid values change per device. 0=not applicable.

prtLanWanVlanType.name: prtLanWanVlanType
prtLanWanVlanType.description: This oject indicates type of VLAN this port is assigned to. Port Base Vlan parameters are defined by objects under radBridgePortBaseVlan

alarmsTrap.name: alarmsTrap
alarmsTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever alarm occurs in the agent.

sanityTrap.name: sanityTrap
sanityTrap.description: This trap is sent after a data base update. It returns the sanity result status and the configuration no. checked. If the result is of Flip DB Sanity Check, the configuration no. sent will be 0. If the result is of Variant Sanity Check, the configuration no. sent will be 100.

cnfgFlipTrap.name: cnfgFlipTrap
cnfgFlipTrap.description: This trap is sent upon change of the active Configuration DB. Attached, is the new active Configuration no.

flipDbChangeTrap.name: flipDbChangeTrap
flipDbChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon change of the active Flip tables (Flip DB).

statusChangedTrap.name: statusChangedTrap
statusChangedTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change of the LEDs status.

dsx1XCurrentTable.name: dsx1XCurrentTable
dsx1XCurrentTable.description: A list of current statistics entries. This table contains additional objects for the current table.

dsx1XCurrentEntry.name: dsx1XCurrentEntry
dsx1XCurrentEntry.description: An entry containing additional statistical counters applicable to a particular current table.

dsx1CurrentLOS.name: dsx1CurrentLOS
dsx1CurrentLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds, encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1CurrentLOF.name: dsx1CurrentLOF
dsx1CurrentLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of LOF seconds, encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1CurrentLOC.name: dsx1CurrentLOC
dsx1CurrentLOC.description: Loss Of Cell delineation. Counts number of cells the ATM UNI cells receiver lost cells delineation .

dsx1CurrentAIS.name: dsx1CurrentAIS
dsx1CurrentAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1CurrentRAI.name: dsx1CurrentRAI
dsx1CurrentRAI.description: Remote Alarm Indication: Transmitted in the outgoing direction (toward the PABX) over FDL bits when the DS1 device detected an incoming Loss Of Frame. Received from the far end (PABX) over FDL when it detects a Loss of frame.

dsx1CurrentLOMF.name: dsx1CurrentLOMF
dsx1CurrentLOMF.description: Loss of Multi-Frame sequence in E1 time slot 16.

dsx1CurrentFEBE.name: dsx1CurrentFEBE
dsx1CurrentFEBE.description: Far End Block Errors, as reported in the first bit of frames 13 and 15, on multiframe E1 lines with CRC4, in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1CurrentStatus.name: dsx1CurrentStatus
dsx1CurrentStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

dsx1CurrentBPV.name: dsx1CurrentBPV
dsx1CurrentBPV.description: The counter associated with the number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1CurrentLOCRCMF.name: dsx1CurrentLOCRCMF
dsx1CurrentLOCRCMF.description: Loss of CRC4 Multi-Frame sequence in E1. encountered in the current 15 minute interval

dsx1CurrentLOFC.name: dsx1CurrentLOFC
dsx1CurrentLOFC.description: Counts the number of loss of frame events measured. encountered in the current 15 minute interval

dsx1CurrentCRCErrors.name: dsx1CurrentCRCErrors
dsx1CurrentCRCErrors.description: Counts the number of CRC error events, encountered in the current 15 minute interval.

dsx1XIntervalTable.name: dsx1XIntervalTable
dsx1XIntervalTable.description: A list of Interval entries. This table contains additional objects for the interval table.

dsx1XIntervalEntry.name: dsx1XIntervalEntry
dsx1XIntervalEntry.description: An entry containing additional statistical counters applicable to a particular interval table.

dsx1IntervalLOS.name: dsx1IntervalLOS
dsx1IntervalLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds , encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOF.name: dsx1IntervalLOF
dsx1IntervalLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of OOF seconds, encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOC.name: dsx1IntervalLOC
dsx1IntervalLOC.description: Loss Of Cell delineation. Counts number of cells the ATM UNI cells receiver lost cells delineation .

dsx1IntervalAIS.name: dsx1IntervalAIS
dsx1IntervalAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a SONET interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalRAI.name: dsx1IntervalRAI
dsx1IntervalRAI.description: Remote Alarm Indication: Transmitted in the outgoing direction (toward the PABX) over FDL bits when the DS1 device detected an incoming Loss Of Frame. Received from the far end (PABX) over FDL when it detects a Loss of frame.

dsx1IntervalLOMF.name: dsx1IntervalLOMF
dsx1IntervalLOMF.description: Loss of Multi-Frame sequence in E1 time slot 16.

dsx1IntervalFEBE.name: dsx1IntervalFEBE
dsx1IntervalFEBE.description: Far End Block Errors, as reported in the first bit of frames 13 and 15, on multiframe E1 lines with CRC4, in one of the previous 96, individual, 15 minute intervals.

dsx1IntervalStatus.name: dsx1IntervalStatus
dsx1IntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

dsx1IntervalBPV.name: dsx1IntervalBPV
dsx1IntervalBPV.description: The counter associated with the number of BPV (Bi-Polar Violations) encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF.name: dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF
dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF.description: Loss of CRC4 Multi-Frame sequence in E1.

dsx1IntervalLOFC.name: dsx1IntervalLOFC
dsx1IntervalLOFC.description: Counts the number of loss of frame events measured in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1XTotalTable.name: dsx1XTotalTable
dsx1XTotalTable.description: A list of Total statistics entries. This table contains additional objects for the Total table.

dsx1XTotalEntry.name: dsx1XTotalEntry
dsx1XTotalEntry.description: An entry containing additional statistical counters applicable to a particular current table.

dsx1TotalLOS.name: dsx1TotalLOS
dsx1TotalLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS (Loss of Signal) seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx1TotalBPV.name: dsx1TotalBPV
dsx1TotalBPV.description: The counter associated with the number of BPV (Bi-Polar Violations) encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx1TotalLOFC.name: dsx1TotalLOFC
dsx1TotalLOFC.description: The counter associated with the number loss of frames encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx1DataStreamStatTable.name: dsx1DataStreamStatTable
dsx1DataStreamStatTable.description: The DS1 Data Stream Statistics table.

dsx1DataStreamStatEntry.name: dsx1DataStreamStatEntry
dsx1DataStreamStatEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Data Stream Statistics table.

dsx1DataStreamStatIfIndex.name: dsx1DataStreamStatIfIndex
dsx1DataStreamStatIfIndex.description: The index of the DS1 interface. It may be ifIndex.

dsx1DataStreamStatIndex.name: dsx1DataStreamStatIndex
dsx1DataStreamStatIndex.description: The DS1 Data Stream Index. For Vmux - the following indices are used: 1 for Transparent 2-3 for SS71-SS72 (respectively) 4-7 for Data1-Data4 (respectively) 8 for HDLC Ph2 Compatible 9-16 for Sub-CH1-1...Sub-CH1-8 (respectively).

dsx1DataStreamStatValid.name: dsx1DataStreamStatValid
dsx1DataStreamStatValid.description: Indicates whether this Data Stream is valid or not. When invalid - all counters are irrelevant.

dsx1DataStreamStatInFrames.name: dsx1DataStreamStatInFrames
dsx1DataStreamStatInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatInBytes.name: dsx1DataStreamStatInBytes
dsx1DataStreamStatInBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of received bytes, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatInDiscards.name: dsx1DataStreamStatInDiscards
dsx1DataStreamStatInDiscards.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded incoming frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatInErrors.name: dsx1DataStreamStatInErrors
dsx1DataStreamStatInErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received Errored frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatOutFrames.name: dsx1DataStreamStatOutFrames
dsx1DataStreamStatOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatOutBytes.name: dsx1DataStreamStatOutBytes
dsx1DataStreamStatOutBytes.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted bytes, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatOutDiscards.name: dsx1DataStreamStatOutDiscards
dsx1DataStreamStatOutDiscards.description: The counter associated with the number of Discarded outgoing frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1DataStreamStatOutErrors.name: dsx1DataStreamStatOutErrors
dsx1DataStreamStatOutErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of errored transmitted frames, encountered by the DS1 Data Stream.

dsx1XConfigTable.name: dsx1XConfigTable
dsx1XConfigTable.description: An extension to the DS1 Configuration table.

dsx1XConfigEntry.name: dsx1XConfigEntry
dsx1XConfigEntry.description: An entry containing additional configuration parameters.

dsx1IdleCode.name: dsx1IdleCode
dsx1IdleCode.description: Byte pattern of the data received/transmitted in the E1T1 framer idle timeslots. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX).

dsx1LineMode.name: dsx1LineMode
dsx1LineMode.description: T1 device operation mode. Valid for T1 only.

dsx1dBTxGain.name: dsx1dBTxGain
dsx1dBTxGain.description: Transmit line Gain for T1 CSU line mode.

dsx1RxSensitivity.name: dsx1RxSensitivity
dsx1RxSensitivity.description: Low Sensitivity is considered Short Haul while High Sensitivity is considered Long Haul. The actual values depend on the LIU. Examples: - E1: -12dB is considered Short Haul ; -43dB is considered Long Haul - T1: -12dB is considered Short Haul ; -36dB is considered Long Haul.

dsx1RestoreTime.name: dsx1RestoreTime
dsx1RestoreTime.description: Used to change the sync. algorithms to reduce the time required for the port to return to normal operation after a RED alarm. 'sec1' = Fast, 'sec10' = TR-6211, 'immediate' = CCITT

dsx1TcFirstSignal.name: dsx1TcFirstSignal
dsx1TcFirstSignal.description: Trunk conditioning signal - value to be sent as a signal during the first 2.5 seconds after alarm detection. Range is 0x0..0xF. 0xFF is a NULL value. This variable is used also for Space Signaling Code (in this case 0xFF is not NULL).

dsx1TcSignal.name: dsx1TcSignal
dsx1TcSignal.description: Trunk conditioning signal value after alarm detection. Range is 0x1..0xF for E1, and 0x0..0xF for T1. This variable is used also for Space Signaling Code (E1 and T1).

dsx1TcPattern.name: dsx1TcPattern
dsx1TcPattern.description: Trunk conditioning data pattern to be sent upon a DS0 fail. Range is 0x0..0xFF. This variable used also for Out of Service Code.

dsx1Scramble.name: dsx1Scramble
dsx1Scramble.description: Scrambling is an operation that randomizes the bits of the payload of the ATM cell by a polynom. This operation helps with the error detection mechanism of the HEC. Not applicable for E1. active - will scramble/descramble the payload ATM cell notActive - will not scramble/descramble.

dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode.name: dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode
dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode.description: Enables end to end clock synchronization. Default value - off.

dsx1TxClockSource.name: dsx1TxClockSource
dsx1TxClockSource.description: The source of Transmit Clock. 'loopTiming' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'localTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used or when an external clock is attached to the box containing the interface. 'throughTiming' indicates that recovered receive clock from another interface is used as the transmit clock. 'adaptive' indicates that the clock is recovered according to the received data flow rate. 'system' indicates that the system clock is used as the transmit clock.

dsx1AisEnable.name: dsx1AisEnable
dsx1AisEnable.description: Enable/ disable AIS transmit when Ethernet cable (for TDMoIP) is out (disconnected).

dsx1TsEchoCancel.name: dsx1TsEchoCancel
dsx1TsEchoCancel.description: This parameter defines for each TS whether Echo-Cancellation is on. Each bit represents one TS as follow: First octet bit'0' = TS#1, bit'7' = TS#8, .. 2nd octet bit'0' = TS#9,.., 4th octet bit'7' = TS#32. Octets and bits order is from left to right: [31,30,..24] [23..16] [15..8] [7..0] MSB LSB MSB LSB MSB LSB MSB LSB For each bit values are: 0 - Echo-Cancellation off. 1 - Echo-Cancellation on.

dsx1EchoCancelerModule.name: dsx1EchoCancelerModule
dsx1EchoCancelerModule.description: This parameter indicates whether echo-cancellation module exists for this line.

dsx1PortFunction.name: dsx1PortFunction
dsx1PortFunction.description: This object determines the ATM Mode over the physical port. uni - The port will function as an ATM UNI. ces - The port will function as a CES. ima - The port will function as an IMA-ATM. cesPsn - The port will function as a CES-PSN. abis - The port will function as an Abis.

dsx1PortMultiplier.name: dsx1PortMultiplier
dsx1PortMultiplier.description: This object determines the data rate of each TS (Kbps units). This parameter is applicable for T1 only.

dsx1LeasedLine.name: dsx1LeasedLine
dsx1LeasedLine.description: This parameter defines whether Line mode is regular (non Leased Line mode) or transparent (Leased Line mode).

dsx1CsuLoop.name: dsx1CsuLoop
dsx1CsuLoop.description: This parameter defines where the CSU loop will be done: local - locally (by IPmux) towards the TDM device transparent - transferred to Remote Device that will send it to its connected TDM device. remote - Remote Device will close the loop towards the Local Device.

dsx1ClockSource.name: dsx1ClockSource
dsx1ClockSource.description: This entry specifies the source from which the clock will be taken. Refer to device specification for source Index

dsx1OosSignal.name: dsx1OosSignal
dsx1OosSignal.description: This parameter defines the value to be sent as a signal after alarm detection: 'Space' = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '0' during out-of-service periods. 'Mark' = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '1' during out-of-service periods. 'spaceMark' = A and B bits are forced to '0' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '1' until out-of-service condition disappears. 'markSpace' = A and B bits are forced to '1' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '0' until out-of-service condition disappears. - '0'= 0 for T1, 1 for E1, or user defined value for Space - '1'= 1 for T1, 0 for E1, or user defined value for Mark.

dsx1BundleNextIndex.name: dsx1BundleNextIndex
dsx1BundleNextIndex.description: This parameter indicates the Next free Bundle Index for this DS1 port.

dsx1CRC6CalcMode.name: dsx1CRC6CalcMode
dsx1CRC6CalcMode.description: This object determines the CRC6 Calculation mode. jtG704 =JT-G704 = the Japanese standard ituG704=ITU-G704 = the International standard This parameter is applicable for J1 only.

dsx1SendUponFail.name: dsx1SendUponFail
dsx1SendUponFail.description: This object determines which notification will be sent to the other side upon fail of another interface. In Ipmux14 the notification is sent upon failure of the Ethernet link.

ds1LocalMultiframeAlarmTrap.name: ds1LocalMultiframeAlarmTrap
ds1LocalMultiframeAlarmTrap.description: This trap indicates near end (Local) Loss of Multiframe Alignment, of the user E1 interface.

ds1RemoteMultiframeAlarmTrap.name: ds1RemoteMultiframeAlarmTrap
ds1RemoteMultiframeAlarmTrap.description: This trap indicates that the far end (remote) unit, connected to the user E1 interface, reports Loss of Multiframe Alignment.

ds1LinkFrameSlipTrap.name: ds1LinkFrameSlipTrap
ds1LinkFrameSlipTrap.description: This trap indicates that a Frame Slip occurred at the user DS1 interface. This usually indicates timing problems (incorrect selection of timing reference), on the user DS1 link.

ds1BpvErrorTrap.name: ds1BpvErrorTrap
ds1BpvErrorTrap.description: This trap indicates a Bipolar Violation (BPV) error has been detected at the user DS1 interface.

ds1ExcessiveBpvTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveBpvTrap
ds1ExcessiveBpvTrap.description: This trap indicates excessive number of Bipolar Violation errors (BPV) detected by the user DS1 interface

ds1Crc4ErrorTrap.name: ds1Crc4ErrorTrap
ds1Crc4ErrorTrap.description: This trap indicates that a frame with CRC-4 error has been detected at the user DS1 interface.

ds1ExcessiveErrorRatioTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveErrorRatioTrap
ds1ExcessiveErrorRatioTrap.description: This trap indicates that the error rate, detected at the user DS1 interface, on the frame synchronization bits is high, as defined by ITU-T Rec. G.732.

ds1RemoteSyncLossTrap.name: ds1RemoteSyncLossTrap
ds1RemoteSyncLossTrap.description: This trap indicates that the far-end (remote) unit, connected to user DS1 interface, reports Loss of Frame Alignment (Sync Loss).

ds1LocalSyncLossTrap.name: ds1LocalSyncLossTrap
ds1LocalSyncLossTrap.description: This trap indicates near end (Local) Loss of Frame Alignment failure (Sync Loss), of the user DS1 interface

ds1AisSyncLossTrap.name: ds1AisSyncLossTrap
ds1AisSyncLossTrap.description: This trap indicates near end (Local) Loss of Frame Alignment (Sync Loss), caused by the reception of AIS at the user DS1 interface.

ds1AisTrap.name: ds1AisTrap
ds1AisTrap.description: This trap indicates AIS being received at the user DS1 interface.

ds1NetworkRemoteLoopTrap.name: ds1NetworkRemoteLoopTrap
ds1NetworkRemoteLoopTrap.description: This trap indicates that a remote loopback has been activated, on the local uplink interface.

ds1RemoteLoopTrap.name: ds1RemoteLoopTrap
ds1RemoteLoopTrap.description: This trap indicates that a remote loopback has been activated, on the local user port.

ds1LocalLoopTrap.name: ds1LocalLoopTrap
ds1LocalLoopTrap.description: This trap indicates that a local loopback has been activated on the user port.

ds1ExcessiveFrameSlipTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveFrameSlipTrap
ds1ExcessiveFrameSlipTrap.description: This trap indicates that the number of Frame Slips detected at the user DS1 interface, during the last minute exceeds threshold. For LA-110, threshold value is 10. This usually indicates timing problems (incorrect selection of timing reference) on the user DS1.

ds1ExcessiveCrc4ErrorTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveCrc4ErrorTrap
ds1ExcessiveCrc4ErrorTrap.description: This trap indicates that the error rate detected on the CRC-4 bits at the user DS1 interface, is high.

ds1ExcessiveLocalMfAlarmTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveLocalMfAlarmTrap
ds1ExcessiveLocalMfAlarmTrap.description: This trap indicates that the number of local Loss of Multiframe Alignment events, detected at the user E1 interface during the last minute exceeds threshold. For LA-110, threshold value is 10.

ds1ExcessiveRemoteMfAlarmTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveRemoteMfAlarmTrap
ds1ExcessiveRemoteMfAlarmTrap.description: This trap indicates that the number of Loss of multiframe alignment events reported by the remote unit connected to the user E1 interface during the last minute exceeds threshold. For LA-110, threshold value is 10.

ds1ExcessiveRemoteSyncLossTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveRemoteSyncLossTrap
ds1ExcessiveRemoteSyncLossTrap.description: This trap indicates that the number of far end (remote) Loss of Synchronization alarms, reported by the user DS1 interface during the last minute, exceeds threshold. For LA-110, threshold value is 10.

ds1ExcessiveLocalSyncLossTrap.name: ds1ExcessiveLocalSyncLossTrap
ds1ExcessiveLocalSyncLossTrap.description: This trap indicates that the number of Loss of local Synchronization alarms reported by the user DS1 interface during the last minute, exceeds threshold. For LA-110, threshold value is 10.

ds1SignalLossTrap.name: ds1SignalLossTrap
ds1SignalLossTrap.description: This trap indicates Signal Loss. (possible reason - cable disconnection. etc.)

prtDs3IfEntry.name: prtDs3IfEntry
prtDs3IfEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 interface table.

prtDs3IfTimeElapsed.name: prtDs3IfTimeElapsed
prtDs3IfTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the near end current error- measurement period.

prtDs3IfValidIntervals.name: prtDs3IfValidIntervals
prtDs3IfValidIntervals.description: The number of previous near end intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought online within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute near end intervals since the interface has been online.

prtDs3CurrentEntry.name: prtDs3CurrentEntry
prtDs3CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Current table.

prtDs3CurrentLOS.name: prtDs3CurrentLOS
prtDs3CurrentLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentOOF.name: prtDs3CurrentOOF
prtDs3CurrentOOF.description: The counter associated with the number of OOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentLOC.name: prtDs3CurrentLOC
prtDs3CurrentLOC.description: The counter associated with the number of LOC seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentAIS.name: prtDs3CurrentAIS
prtDs3CurrentAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentRDI.name: prtDs3CurrentRDI
prtDs3CurrentRDI.description: The counter associated with the number of RDI seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface.

prtDs3CurrentUAS.name: prtDs3CurrentUAS
prtDs3CurrentUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of UAS, encountered by a SONET interface.

prtDs3CurrentBIP.name: prtDs3CurrentBIP
prtDs3CurrentBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentFEBE.name: prtDs3CurrentFEBE
prtDs3CurrentFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentSLM.name: prtDs3CurrentSLM
prtDs3CurrentSLM.description: The counter associated with the number of SLM seconds, encountered by an E3 (only ) interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentSES.name: prtDs3CurrentSES
prtDs3CurrentSES.description: The counter associated with the number of SES encountered by a E3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentES.name: prtDs3CurrentES
prtDs3CurrentES.description: The number of Errored Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval.

prtDs3CurrentBitParity.name: prtDs3CurrentBitParity
prtDs3CurrentBitParity.description: Bit Parity Error counter. Relevant to T3 only.

prtDs3CurrentPlcpLOF.name: prtDs3CurrentPlcpLOF
prtDs3CurrentPlcpLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of LOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. This counter is relevant for plcpInternal(5) or plcpExternal(6) configuration If frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentPlcpRAI.name: prtDs3CurrentPlcpRAI
prtDs3CurrentPlcpRAI.description: Receiving Yellow/Remote Alarm Indication. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentPlcpBIP.name: prtDs3CurrentPlcpBIP
prtDs3CurrentPlcpBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE.name: prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE
prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentBPV.name: prtDs3CurrentBPV
prtDs3CurrentBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Electrical Line of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3CurrentLCE.name: prtDs3CurrentLCE
prtDs3CurrentLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Optical Links of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3CurrentStatus.name: prtDs3CurrentStatus
prtDs3CurrentStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

prtDs3IntervalEntry.name: prtDs3IntervalEntry
prtDs3IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Interval table.

prtDs3IntervalNumber.name: prtDs3IntervalNumber
prtDs3IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

prtDs3IntervalLOS.name: prtDs3IntervalLOS
prtDs3IntervalLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds , encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalOOF.name: prtDs3IntervalOOF
prtDs3IntervalOOF.description: The counter associated with the number of OOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalLOC.name: prtDs3IntervalLOC
prtDs3IntervalLOC.description: The counter associated with the number of LOC seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalAIS.name: prtDs3IntervalAIS
prtDs3IntervalAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a SONET interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalRDI.name: prtDs3IntervalRDI
prtDs3IntervalRDI.description: The counter associated with the number of RDI seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalUAS.name: prtDs3IntervalUAS
prtDs3IntervalUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of UAS, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalBIP.name: prtDs3IntervalBIP
prtDs3IntervalBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalFEBE.name: prtDs3IntervalFEBE
prtDs3IntervalFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalSLM.name: prtDs3IntervalSLM
prtDs3IntervalSLM.description: The counter associated with the number of SLM seconds, encountered by an E3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalSES.name: prtDs3IntervalSES
prtDs3IntervalSES.description: The counter associated with the number of SES encountered by a E3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalES.name: prtDs3IntervalES
prtDs3IntervalES.description: The number of Errored Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalBitParity.name: prtDs3IntervalBitParity
prtDs3IntervalBitParity.description: Bit Parity Error counter. Relevant to T3 only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF
prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of LOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. This counter is relevant for plcpInternal(5) or plcpExternal(6) configuration If frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI
prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI.description: Receiving Yellow/Remote Alarm Indication. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP
prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE
prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalBPV.name: prtDs3IntervalBPV
prtDs3IntervalBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the specified 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Electrical Line of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3IntervalLCE.name: prtDs3IntervalLCE
prtDs3IntervalLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the specified 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Optical Links of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3IntervalStatus.name: prtDs3IntervalStatus
prtDs3IntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

prtDs3TotalUAS.name: prtDs3TotalUAS
prtDs3TotalUAS.description: Number of UASs (Unavailable Seconds) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalBPV.name: prtDs3TotalBPV
prtDs3TotalBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalLCE.name: prtDs3TotalLCE
prtDs3TotalLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalSES.name: prtDs3TotalSES
prtDs3TotalSES.description: Number of SES (Severely Errored Seconds) encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx3XConfigTable.name: dsx3XConfigTable
dsx3XConfigTable.description: An extension to the DS3 Configuration table.

dsx3XConfigEntry.name: dsx3XConfigEntry
dsx3XConfigEntry.description: An entry containing additional configuration parameters.

dsx3AisEnable.name: dsx3AisEnable
dsx3AisEnable.description: Enable/ disable AIS transmit when Ethernet (for TDMoIP) line is disconnected.

dsx3TxClockSource.name: dsx3TxClockSource
dsx3TxClockSource.description: The source of Transmit Clock. loopTiming indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. localTiming indicates that a local clock source is used or that an external clock is attached to the box containing the interface. throughTiming indicates that transmit clock is derived from the recovered receive clock of another DS3 interface. 'system' indicates that the system clock is used as the transmit clock.

dsx3MappingTable.name: dsx3MappingTable
dsx3MappingTable.description: The DS3/E3 mapping table associates DS3/E3 channels with logical or physical interfaces. For example, consider a DS3 device with 16 T1's and 1 VCG. There are 28 logical/internal channels, numbered 1 through 28 but only 17 are actually connected. We might describe the allocation of channels, in the dsx3MappingTable, as follows: dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 1 = 1001 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.15 = 1015 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 2 = 1002 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.16 = 1016 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 3 = 1003 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.17 = 1017 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 4 = 1004 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.18 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 5 = 1005 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.19 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 6 = 1006 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.20 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 7 = 1007 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.21 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 8 = 1008 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.22 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1. 9 = 1009 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.23 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.10 = 1010 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.24 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.11 = 1011 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.25 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.12 = 1012 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.26 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.13 = 1013 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.27 = 0 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.14 = 1014 dsx3MappingIfIndex.1.28 = 0 Note that in the case above all channels are mapped to one T3 port with ifIndex = 1. The Channels 1...28 are represented via the 2nd index. The values of 1001...1016 are the T1 interface ifIndexes. The value of 1017 is the ifIndex of the VCG. Unconnected channels have a value of 0.

dsx3MappingEntry.name: dsx3MappingEntry
dsx3MappingEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 mapping table.

dsx3MappingDs3Index.name: dsx3MappingDs3Index
dsx3MappingDs3Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS3/E3 interface to which this entry is applicable. This value is also equal to dsx3LineIndex used in dsx3ConfigEntry. For RICi-16 this is the ifIndex of the T3 interface.

dsx3MappingNumber.name: dsx3MappingNumber
dsx3MappingNumber.description: The channel number for this entry. For RICi-16 this is the channel number 1...28.

dsx3MappingIfIndex.name: dsx3MappingIfIndex
dsx3MappingIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a logical or physical interface mapped to a DS3/E3 channel. If no interface is currently using a channel, the value should be zero. If a single interface occupies more than one channel, that ifIndex value will be found in multiple channels. For RICi-16 this is the ifIndex of the T1 or VCG interface.

atmNteEvents.name: atmNteEvents
atmNteEvents.description: The events for RAD ATM products.

atmNteConfIfEntry.name: atmNteConfIfEntry
atmNteConfIfEntry.description: An entry in the Physical interface configuration table. The ifIndex is of the lowest physical layer.

atmConfIfTransmitClk.name: atmConfIfTransmitClk
atmConfIfTransmitClk.description: The transmit clock of the port.

atmConfIfFrameType.name: atmConfIfFrameType
atmConfIfFrameType.description: The frame type. Valid values for a 155M interface: sonet(2), sdh(3). Valid values for a T3 interface: direct(4), plcpInternal(5), plcpExternal(6), directNoScrmbling(10), plcpInternalNoScrmbling(11), plcpExternalNoScrmbling(12). Valid values for Ethernet interface: ethCrcTrans (8), ethCrcNotTrans(9). (DS1 interfaces frame type is specified in the DSX1 mib).

atmConfAtmIfVpiVciLimit.name: atmConfAtmIfVpiVciLimit
atmConfAtmIfVpiVciLimit.description: The limit on the sum of the VPI+VCI bits for this interface.

atmConfIfOutputRate.name: atmConfIfOutputRate
atmConfIfOutputRate.description: This parameter indicates the output rate in cells/sec, which is supported per port. Successfully setting this parameter is dependent on all other ports values calculations, which are described in the NMS SRS.

atmConfIfInputRate.name: atmConfIfInputRate
atmConfIfInputRate.description: This parameter indicates the input rate in cells/sec, which is supported per port. Successfully setting this parameter is dependent on all other ports values calculations, which are described in the NMS SRS.

atmConfAlarmForwarding.name: atmConfAlarmForwarding
atmConfAlarmForwarding.description: Enables Path AIS Alarm forwarding upon a failure detection. The following might be considered as a failure: LOS, LOF, LOC, SLM, LOP, Path AIS and Line AIS. disable(2) - will not forward an alarm upon a failure on this port. enable(3) - will forward an alarm upon a failure on this port.

atmConfIfOamMode.name: atmConfIfOamMode
atmConfIfOamMode.description: OAM support Mode, which determines the interface's location in a segment wise.

atmConfIfOamFailureInd.name: atmConfIfOamFailureInd
atmConfIfOamFailureInd.description: This object allows user to define the type of indication (if any) that will be created upon a LB cell failure, for all VCs on which OAM loopback traffic is activated. disabled(2) - no indication will be created. ais(3) - will cause Tx of AIS. rdi(4) - will cause Tx of RDI. aisAndRdi(5) - will cause Tx of AIS & RDI. For LA-110, indication will be sent only for VCs with atmConfVcLoopbackFailureInd <> disabled

atmNteAlarmIfEntry.name: atmNteAlarmIfEntry
atmNteAlarmIfEntry.description: An entry in the interface Alarm table.

atmInterfaceActiveAlarms.name: atmInterfaceActiveAlarms
atmInterfaceActiveAlarms.description: A Bit String of the active alarms on this interface. An up bit (1) means there is an active alarm of this type. A down bit (0) means there is no such alarm. The meaning of the bits is as follows: 1 - LOS 2 - LOF 3 - Line AIS (SONET)/ PLCP LOF (DS3) 4 - LOP 5 - Path AIS 6 - SLM 7 - LCD 8 - Line RDI (SONET)/ PLCP Yellow (DS3) 9 - Path RDI (SONET)/ RDI (DS3) 10 - Section BIP (SONET)/ P1/P2 (DS3) > Threshold 11 - Line BIP (SONET)/ PLCP BIP (DS3) > Threshold 12 - Line FEBE (SONET)/ PLCP FEBE (DS3) > Threshold 13 - Path BIP > Threshold 14 - Path FEBE > Threshold 15 - HW Failure

atmThresholdSectionBIP.name: atmThresholdSectionBIP
atmThresholdSectionBIP.description: When Section BIPs are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised. N/A for ds3/e3 interface.

atmThresholdLineBIP.name: atmThresholdLineBIP
atmThresholdLineBIP.description: When Line BIPs are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised. N/A for ds3/e3 interface.

atmThresholdLineFEBE.name: atmThresholdLineFEBE
atmThresholdLineFEBE.description: When Line FEBEs are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised. N/A for ds3/e3 interface.

atmThresholdPathBIP.name: atmThresholdPathBIP
atmThresholdPathBIP.description: When Path BIPs are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised.

atmThresholdPathFEBE.name: atmThresholdPathFEBE
atmThresholdPathFEBE.description: When Path FEBEs are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised.

atmThresholdErroredCells.name: atmThresholdErroredCells
atmThresholdErroredCells.description: When Errored Cells are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised.

atmThresholdLostCells.name: atmThresholdLostCells
atmThresholdLostCells.description: When Lost Cells are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised.

atmThresholdMisinsertedCells.name: atmThresholdMisinsertedCells
atmThresholdMisinsertedCells.description: When Misinserted Cells are greater than this threshold, an active alarm is raised.

atmInterfaceAlarmStatus.name: atmInterfaceAlarmStatus
atmInterfaceAlarmStatus.description: The variable is on(3) when there is any active alarm on this interface.

atmInterfaceMaskAlarms.name: atmInterfaceMaskAlarms
atmInterfaceMaskAlarms.description: A Bit String of alarms mask on this interface. An up bit (1) means that the respective alarm is masked. A down bit (0) means no mask. The mask is supported for the following alarms: 1 - LOS

atmNteConfVpTable.name: atmNteConfVpTable
atmNteConfVpTable.description: The ATM VP configuration table. The table is an extension to the atmVplTable of RFC-1695.

atmNteConfVpEntry.name: atmNteConfVpEntry
atmNteConfVpEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VP configuration table. ifIndex of the ATM layer.

atmConfVpPolicing.name: atmConfVpPolicing
atmConfVpPolicing.description: Policing method desired for this VPL.

atmConfVpCCAdminStatus.name: atmConfVpCCAdminStatus
atmConfVpCCAdminStatus.description: up(2) - Activate Continuity Check (CC). down(3) - Deactivate CC. source(4) - Activate OAM CC(Continuity Check) of local agent ( start sending Oam cells to the remote side ). sink(5) - Activate CC of remote agent ( start receiving Oam cells from remote side ). listenToActivationCells (6) - Passive listener till gets an activation request originateActivationCells(7) - Sands Activation cell according to atmConfVcCCDirection.

atmConfVpLoopbackAdminStatus.name: atmConfVpLoopbackAdminStatus
atmConfVpLoopbackAdminStatus.description: up(2) - Start loopback OAM cells. down(3) - Stop sending loopback OAM cells. For ace2002: up(2) - Transmitting LB cells with llid all ones (i.e. FFFF..FF) down(3) - Not transmitting LB cells. llid(4) - Transmitting LB cells with llid indicated in the address field. segment(5) - Transmitting Segment LB cells with llid all ones. endToEnd(6) - Transmitting End to End LB cells with llid all ones. segmentLlid(7) - Transmitting Segment LB cells with llid indicated in the address field. endToEndLlid(8) - Transmitting LB cells with llid indicated in the address field. This parameter value might be in conflict with atmConfVpOamSupport value, since this parameter is for LB, while atmConfVpOamSupport is for any other OAM cells.

atmConfVpLoopbackSinkAddress.name: atmConfVpLoopbackSinkAddress
atmConfVpLoopbackSinkAddress.description: Destination address. For ace101: 2 bytes are used. For ace2002: 16 bytes are used.

atmConfVpCongestionControl.name: atmConfVpCongestionControl
atmConfVpCongestionControl.description: Each bit indicates a selection of one option as the following description. All combinations are possible and legal. The codes are: 1 - EPD 2 - CLP 4 - EFCI

atmConfVpCCDirection.name: atmConfVpCCDirection
atmConfVpCCDirection.description: both(2) - Agent send OAM CC cells and check received OAM CC cells source(4)- Agent send OAM CC cells. sink(5) - Agent checks received OAM CC cells.

atmConfVpCreationTime.name: atmConfVpCreationTime
atmConfVpCreationTime.description: A date-time in which the VP was created.

atmConfVpOamSupport.name: atmConfVpOamSupport
atmConfVpOamSupport.description: OAM support mode, which determines the device location in a segment wise.

atmConfVpCCOperStatus.name: atmConfVpCCOperStatus
atmConfVpCCOperStatus.description: initial(1) - The CC activation process is not started. source(4) - Agent sends OAM CC cells. sink(5) - Agent checks received OAM CC cells. both (8) - OAM CC of local and remote agents activation. timeout (9) - Timeout occured on receiving answer from the remote agent. denied (10) - CC activation process rejected by remote agent. conflict (11) - local and remote sides requested activation simultaneously. manual (12) - OAM CC of local agent activated manually.

atmConfVpLoopbackTraffic.name: atmConfVpLoopbackTraffic
atmConfVpLoopbackTraffic.description: This parameter has both command and status meanings: off(2) - Set to 'Off' will Stop traffic loop. Getting this value means that the loop is not running. on (3) - Set to 'On' will start traffic loop. Getting this value means that the loop is currently running.

atmConfVpLoopbackFailureInd.name: atmConfVpLoopbackFailureInd
atmConfVpLoopbackFailureInd.description: This object allows user to define the Indication that will be created upon a LB cell failure. disabled(2) - no indication will be created. segmentAis(3) - will cause Tx of a segment AIS. segmentRdi(4) - will cause Tx of a segment RDI. segmentAisAndRdi(5) - will cause Tx of a segment AIS & RDI. endToEndAis(6) - will cause Tx of an End to End AIS. endToEndRdi(7) - will cause Tx of an End to End RDI. endToEndAisAndRdi(8) - will cause Tx of an End to End AIS & RDI. Default: disabled(2).

atmConfVpLoopbackFailureThreshold.name: atmConfVpLoopbackFailureThreshold
atmConfVpLoopbackFailureThreshold.description: The number of the LB failures before starting transmission of the Indication defined by atmConfVcLoopbackFailureInd. Range: 1..16. Default: 1.

atmConfVpOamDirection.name: atmConfVpOamDirection
atmConfVpOamDirection.description: The direction of OAM cell insertion. downStream(2) - The OAM cell will be inserted in downStream. upStream(3) - The OAM cell will be inserted in upStream.

atmConfVpOamDescrIndex.name: atmConfVpOamDescrIndex
atmConfVpOamDescrIndex.description: This parameter indicates the VPL's OAM Descriptor index, according to the OAM Descriptor Configuration Table.

atmConfVpConnected.name: atmConfVpConnected
atmConfVpConnected.description: This object indicates whether this VP is connected and if connected, what is it connected to.

atmNteAlarmVpEntry.name: atmNteAlarmVpEntry
atmNteAlarmVpEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VP Alarm table. ifIndex of the ATM layer.

atmNteVpAlarmVpi.name: atmNteVpAlarmVpi
atmNteVpAlarmVpi.description: The VPI on which there is an active alarm.

atmNteVpActiveAlarms.name: atmNteVpActiveAlarms
atmNteVpActiveAlarms.description: A Bit String of the active alarms on this VP. An up bit (1) means there is an active alarm of this type. A down bit (0) means there is no such alarm. The meaning of the bits is as follows: 1 - VP AIS 2 - VP Loss Of Continuity 3 - VP RDI Reception 4 - VP Errored Cells > Threshold 5 - VP Lost Cells > Threshold 6 - VP Misinserted Cells > Threshold 9 - VP Loopback Failure

atmNteAlarmVcEntry.name: atmNteAlarmVcEntry
atmNteAlarmVcEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VC Alarm table. ifIndex of the ATM layer.

atmNteVcAlarmVpi.name: atmNteVcAlarmVpi
atmNteVcAlarmVpi.description: The VPI of the VC on which there is an active alarm.

atmNteVcAlarmVci.name: atmNteVcAlarmVci
atmNteVcAlarmVci.description: The VCI of the VC on which there is an active alarm.

atmNteVcActiveAlarms.name: atmNteVcActiveAlarms
atmNteVcActiveAlarms.description: A Bit String of the active alarms on this VC. An up bit (1) means there is an active alarm of this type. A down bit (0) means there is no such alarm. The meaning of the bits is as follows: 1 - VC AIS 2 - VC Loss Of Continuity 3 - VC RDI 4 - VC Errored Cells > Threshold 5 - VC Lost Cells > Threshold 6 - VC Misinserted Cells > Threshold 7 - Tx VC AIS 8 - Tx VC RDI 9 - VC Loopback Failure

atmIfDataEntry.name: atmIfDataEntry
atmIfDataEntry.description: An entry in the ATM interface Data table.

atmIfTimeElapsed.name: atmIfTimeElapsed
atmIfTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the near end current error- measurement period.

atmIfValidIntervals.name: atmIfValidIntervals
atmIfValidIntervals.description: The number of previous near end intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought online within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute near end intervals since the interface has been online.

atmIfTxCells.name: atmIfTxCells
atmIfTxCells.description: The counter associated with the total number of transmitted cells, encountered by an ATM interface.

atmIfRxCells.name: atmIfRxCells
atmIfRxCells.description: The counter associated with the total number of received cells, encountered by an ATM interface.

atmIfUncorrectedHecs.name: atmIfUncorrectedHecs
atmIfUncorrectedHecs.description: The counter associated with the total number of cells with uncorrected HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface.

atmIfCurrentEntry.name: atmIfCurrentEntry
atmIfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the ATM interface Current table.

atmIfCurrentTxCells.name: atmIfCurrentTxCells
atmIfCurrentTxCells.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted cells, encountered by an ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmIfCurrentRxCells.name: atmIfCurrentRxCells
atmIfCurrentRxCells.description: The counter associated with the number of received cells, encountered by an ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmIfCurrentCorrectedHecs.name: atmIfCurrentCorrectedHecs
atmIfCurrentCorrectedHecs.description: The counter associated with the number of cells with corrected HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.
