atmIfCurrentUncorrectedHecs.name: atmIfCurrentUncorrectedHecs
atmIfCurrentUncorrectedHecs.description: The counter associated with the number of cells with uncorrected HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmIfCurrentHecErrorSeconds.name: atmIfCurrentHecErrorSeconds
atmIfCurrentHecErrorSeconds.description: The counter associated with the number of seconds with HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmIfIntervalEntry.name: atmIfIntervalEntry
atmIfIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the ATM interface Interval table.

atmIfIntervalNumber.name: atmIfIntervalNumber
atmIfIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

atmIfIntervalTxCells.name: atmIfIntervalTxCells
atmIfIntervalTxCells.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted cells , encountered by an ATM interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmIfIntervalRxCells.name: atmIfIntervalRxCells
atmIfIntervalRxCells.description: The counter associated with the number of received cells, encountered by an ATM interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmIfIntervalCorrectedHecs.name: atmIfIntervalCorrectedHecs
atmIfIntervalCorrectedHecs.description: The counter associated with the number of cells with corrected HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmIfIntervalUncorrectedHecs.name: atmIfIntervalUncorrectedHecs
atmIfIntervalUncorrectedHecs.description: The counter associated with the number of cells with uncorrected HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmIfIntervalHecErrorSeconds.name: atmIfIntervalHecErrorSeconds
atmIfIntervalHecErrorSeconds.description: The counter associated with the number of seconds with HEC errors, encountered by an ATM interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVpCurrentEntry.name: atmVpCurrentEntry
atmVpCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VP Current table.

atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp01.name: atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp01
atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp01.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp0.name: atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp0
atmVpCurrentRxCellsClp0.description: The counter associated with the number of received cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentGcra0Violations.name: atmVpCurrentGcra0Violations
atmVpCurrentGcra0Violations.description: The counter associated with the number of cells violating GCRA0, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentGcra1Violations.name: atmVpCurrentGcra1Violations
atmVpCurrentGcra1Violations.description: The counter associated with the number of cells violating GCRA1, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentRxAIS.name: atmVpCurrentRxAIS
atmVpCurrentRxAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of received AIS cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentTxAIS.name: atmVpCurrentTxAIS
atmVpCurrentTxAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted AIS cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval. Not Supported in the first phase.

atmVpCurrentRxRDI.name: atmVpCurrentRxRDI
atmVpCurrentRxRDI.description: The counter associated with the number of received RDI cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentTxRDI.name: atmVpCurrentTxRDI
atmVpCurrentTxRDI.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted RDI cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentContinuityLoss.name: atmVpCurrentContinuityLoss
atmVpCurrentContinuityLoss.description: The counter associated with the number of loss of continuity cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentUAS.name: atmVpCurrentUAS
atmVpCurrentUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentSES.name: atmVpCurrentSES
atmVpCurrentSES.description: The counter associated with the number of Severerly Errored Seconds, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpCurrentCDC.name: atmVpCurrentCDC
atmVpCurrentCDC.description: Amount of cells dropped in the current 15 minute interval of the VP connection.

atmVpCurrentTotalDiscards.name: atmVpCurrentTotalDiscards
atmVpCurrentTotalDiscards.description: The total number of valid ATM cells discarded by the traffic policing entity. This includes cells originally received with CLP=0 and CLP=1.

atmVpCurrentClp0Discards.name: atmVpCurrentClp0Discards
atmVpCurrentClp0Discards.description: The total number of valid ATM cells received with CLP=0 and discarded by the traffic policing entity.

atmVpCurrentTotalCellOuts.name: atmVpCurrentTotalCellOuts
atmVpCurrentTotalCellOuts.description: The total number of valid ATM cells transmitted by this VPL. This includes both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells.

atmVpCurrentClp0CellOuts.name: atmVpCurrentClp0CellOuts
atmVpCurrentClp0CellOuts.description: The total number of valid ATM cells transmitted with CLP=0 by this VPL.

atmVpCurrentTaggedOuts.name: atmVpCurrentTaggedOuts
atmVpCurrentTaggedOuts.description: The total number of valid ATM cells tagged by the traffic policing entity from CLP=0 to CLP=1 and transmitted by this VPL.

atmVpCurrentPCR.name: atmVpCurrentPCR
atmVpCurrentPCR.description: The maximum traffic rate encountered in the last interval of the VP connection (monitored once a second).

atmVpCurrentSCR.name: atmVpCurrentSCR
atmVpCurrentSCR.description: The average traffic rate during the last interval of the VP connection.

atmVpCurrentMCR.name: atmVpCurrentMCR
atmVpCurrentMCR.description: MCR - The minimum traffic rate encountered in the last interval of the VP connection (monitored once a second).

atmVpCurrentShaperTotalDiscards.name: atmVpCurrentShaperTotalDiscards
atmVpCurrentShaperTotalDiscards.description: The total number of cells (CLP0 and CLP1) discarded due to congestion by the traffic shaper.

atmVpCurrentShaperClp0Discards.name: atmVpCurrentShaperClp0Discards
atmVpCurrentShaperClp0Discards.description: The total number of CLP0 cells discarded due to congestion by the traffic shaper.

atmVpCurrentShaperClp1Discards.name: atmVpCurrentShaperClp1Discards
atmVpCurrentShaperClp1Discards.description: The total number of CLP1 cells discarded due to congestion by the traffic shaper.

atmVpPMCurrentTable.name: atmVpPMCurrentTable
atmVpPMCurrentTable.description: The ATM VP Current table for Performance Management.

atmVpPMCurrentEntry.name: atmVpPMCurrentEntry
atmVpPMCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VP Current table for Performance Management.

atmVpPMCurrentTxClp01.name: atmVpPMCurrentTxClp01
atmVpPMCurrentTxClp01.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted CLP 0+1 cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentTxClp0.name: atmVpPMCurrentTxClp0
atmVpPMCurrentTxClp0.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted CLP 0 cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentRxClp01.name: atmVpPMCurrentRxClp01
atmVpPMCurrentRxClp01.description: The counter associated with the number of received CLP 0+1 cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentRxClp0.name: atmVpPMCurrentRxClp0
atmVpPMCurrentRxClp0.description: The counter associated with the number of received CLP 0 cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentErroredCells.name: atmVpPMCurrentErroredCells
atmVpPMCurrentErroredCells.description: The counter associated with the number of errored cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentLostCells.name: atmVpPMCurrentLostCells
atmVpPMCurrentLostCells.description: The counter associated with the number of lost cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentMisinsertedCells.name: atmVpPMCurrentMisinsertedCells
atmVpPMCurrentMisinsertedCells.description: The counter associated with the number of misinserted cells, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentECB.name: atmVpPMCurrentECB
atmVpPMCurrentECB.description: The counter associated with the number of ECB, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentSECB.name: atmVpPMCurrentSECB
atmVpPMCurrentSECB.description: The counter associated with the number of SECB, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentES.name: atmVpPMCurrentES
atmVpPMCurrentES.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentSES.name: atmVpPMCurrentSES
atmVpPMCurrentSES.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentUAS.name: atmVpPMCurrentUAS
atmVpPMCurrentUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds, encountered by the VPL of this ATM interface in the current 15 minute interval.

atmVpPMCurrentIntervalQuality.name: atmVpPMCurrentIntervalQuality

atmVpQoSPeriodRef.name: atmVpQoSPeriodRef
atmVpQoSPeriodRef.description: This object is an index that specifies which period of time, the next 2 objects refer to. currentPeriod - the period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. lastPeriod - the period between last two commands of systemResetAllStatsCmd. - If only one command occurred since Start-up: the period between Start-up and last command. - If no command occurred since Start-up: this period will not actually exist. In this case, he following 5 objects will be 0.

atmVpQoSElapsedTime.name: atmVpQoSElapsedTime
atmVpQoSElapsedTime.description: Elapsed Time in seconds. - for atmVpQoSPeriodRef = currentPeriod: The period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. - for atmVpQoSPeriodRef = lastPeriod: The value of atmVpQoSElapsedTime when last systemResetAllStatsCmd was received.

atmVpQoSUAS.name: atmVpQoSUAS
atmVpQoSUAS.description: Number of Unavailable Seconds for the reference period (atmVpQoSPeriodRef).

atmVpPMQoSPeriodRef.name: atmVpPMQoSPeriodRef
atmVpPMQoSPeriodRef.description: This object is an index that specifies which period of time, the next 5 objects refer to. currentPeriod - the period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. lastPeriod - the period between last two commands of systemResetAllStatsCmd. - If only one command occurred since Start-up: the period between Start-up and last command. - If no command occurred since Start-up: this period will not actually exist. In this case, he following 5 objects will be 0.

atmVcPMIntervalTxClp01.name: atmVcPMIntervalTxClp01
atmVcPMIntervalTxClp01.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted CLP 0+1 cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalTxClp0.name: atmVcPMIntervalTxClp0
atmVcPMIntervalTxClp0.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted CLP 0 cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalRxClp01.name: atmVcPMIntervalRxClp01
atmVcPMIntervalRxClp01.description: The counter associated with the number of received CLP 0+1 cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalRxClp0.name: atmVcPMIntervalRxClp0
atmVcPMIntervalRxClp0.description: The counter associated with the number of received CLP 0 cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalErroredCells.name: atmVcPMIntervalErroredCells
atmVcPMIntervalErroredCells.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalLostCells.name: atmVcPMIntervalLostCells
atmVcPMIntervalLostCells.description: The counter associated with the number of Lost cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalMisinsertedCells.name: atmVcPMIntervalMisinsertedCells
atmVcPMIntervalMisinsertedCells.description: The counter associated with the number of Misinserted cells, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalECB.name: atmVcPMIntervalECB
atmVcPMIntervalECB.description: The counter associated with the number of ECBs encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalSECB.name: atmVcPMIntervalSECB
atmVcPMIntervalSECB.description: The counter associated with the number of SECBs encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalES.name: atmVcPMIntervalES
atmVcPMIntervalES.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalSES.name: atmVcPMIntervalSES
atmVcPMIntervalSES.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalUAS.name: atmVcPMIntervalUAS
atmVcPMIntervalUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds, encountered by an ATM interface/VC in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

atmVcPMIntervalQuality.name: atmVcPMIntervalQuality
atmVcPMIntervalQuality.description: If the number of errors per interval is superior to the atmNteUPLTCR value, the quality of service of the interval is declared as unacceptable.

atmVcPMIntervalLastDayQuality.name: atmVcPMIntervalLastDayQuality
atmVcPMIntervalLastDayQuality.description: If the number of errors per 24 hours is superior to the atmNteDPLTCR value, the quality of service of the day is declared as degraded.

atmVcQoSEntry.name: atmVcQoSEntry
atmVcQoSEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VP table.

atmVcQoSPeriodRef.name: atmVcQoSPeriodRef
atmVcQoSPeriodRef.description: This object is an index that specifies which period of time, the next 2 objects refer to. currentPeriod - the period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. lastPeriod - the period between last two commands of systemResetAllStatsCmd. - If only one command occurred since Start-up: the period between Start-up and last command. - If no command occurred since Start-up: this period will not actually exist. In this case, he following 5 objects will be 0.

atmVcQoSElapsedTime.name: atmVcQoSElapsedTime
atmVcQoSElapsedTime.description: Elapsed Time in seconds. - for atmVcQoSPeriodRef = currentPeriod: The period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. - for atmVcQoSPeriodRef = lastPeriod: The value of atmVcQoSElapsedTime when last systemResetAllStatsCmd was received.

atmVcQoSUAS.name: atmVcQoSUAS
atmVcQoSUAS.description: Number of Unavailable Seconds for the reference period (atmVcQoSPeriodRef).

atmVcPMQoSEntry.name: atmVcPMQoSEntry
atmVcPMQoSEntry.description: An entry in the VC PM QoS table.

atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef.name: atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef
atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef.description: This object is an index that specifies which period of time, the next 5 objects refer to. currentPeriod - the period since last systemResetAllStatsCmd received or since Start-up (if no systemResetAllStatsCmd was received since Start-up) until now. lastPeriod - the period between last two commands of systemResetAllStatsCmd. - If only one command occurred since Start-up: the period between Start-up and last command. - If no command occurred since Start-up: this period will not actually exist. In this case, he following 5 objects will be 0.

atmVcPMQoSCLR.name: atmVcPMQoSCLR
atmVcPMQoSCLR.description: Cell Loss Ratio counter for the reference period (atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef)- defined in accordance with I.356 , in %. The value will be multipuled by 100.

atmVcPMQoSCER.name: atmVcPMQoSCER
atmVcPMQoSCER.description: Cell Error Ratio counter for the reference period (atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef) defined in accordance with I.356 , in %. The value will be multipuled by 100.

atmVcPMQoSCMR.name: atmVcPMQoSCMR
atmVcPMQoSCMR.description: Cell Miss-insertion Ratio counter for the reference period (atmVcPMQoSPeriodRef) defined in accordance with I.356 , cells/sec .

atmVcShaperStatTable.name: atmVcShaperStatTable
atmVcShaperStatTable.description: The ATM VC shaper statistics table.

atmVcShaperStatEntry.name: atmVcShaperStatEntry
atmVcShaperStatEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VC shaper statistics table.

atmVcShaperDiscarded.name: atmVcShaperDiscarded
atmVcShaperDiscarded.description: The number of Cells that were discarded in the shaper on that VCC due to buffer overflow. This counter counts till it reaches its MAX value (20 bits) and then rolls over.

atmVcShaperOccupation.name: atmVcShaperOccupation
atmVcShaperOccupation.description: The number of Cells that are currently stored in the buffer. This parameter is limited to 20 bits.

atmVcShaperMaxOccupation.name: atmVcShaperMaxOccupation
atmVcShaperMaxOccupation.description: The Maximum number of Cells that were stored in the buffer, since this VC was activated. This parameter is limited to 20 bits.

atmVcShaperLevel.name: atmVcShaperLevel
atmVcShaperLevel.description: The occupation of the buffer according to a predefined threshold. empty - buffer is Empty full - buffer is Full below - buffer is Below the threshold above - buffer is Above the threshold. This is also the trigger to start EPD\PPD mechanism, if set for the VCC.

atmVcShaperEpdDropped.name: atmVcShaperEpdDropped
atmVcShaperEpdDropped.description: The number of Cells that were dropped in the shaper on that VCC due to EPD\PPD mechanism in the last second. This parameter is limited to 24 bits. Applicable for a EPD/PPD VC only.

atmVcShaperTotalEpdDropped.name: atmVcShaperTotalEpdDropped
atmVcShaperTotalEpdDropped.description: The Total number of Cells that were dropped in the shaper on that VPC due to EPD\PPD mechanism in the last 15 minutes. This counter automatically reset itself every 15 minutes. Applicable for a EPD/PPD VC only.

atmIntervalDateTable.name: atmIntervalDateTable
atmIntervalDateTable.description: The agent will keep in this group the date & time corresponding to each interval.

atmIntervalDateEntry.name: atmIntervalDateEntry
atmIntervalDateEntry.description: The date & time for the given interval.

atmIntervalDateInterval.name: atmIntervalDateInterval
atmIntervalDateInterval.description: The interval number defining this entry.

atmIntervalDateDate.name: atmIntervalDateDate
atmIntervalDateDate.description: The date corresponding to this interval.

atmIntervalDateTime.name: atmIntervalDateTime
atmIntervalDateTime.description: The time corresponding to this interval.

atmNteManagerTable.name: atmNteManagerTable
atmNteManagerTable.description: The Manager Table includes all the NMSs that receive traps from this agent. A single manager can receive traps on more than one PVC. The agent will set implicitly the correct ifIndex, VPI, VCI values to all relevant entries in the table when the user changes them for one of the PVCs.

atmNteManagerEntry.name: atmNteManagerEntry
atmNteManagerEntry.description: A single manager and the PVC for receiving traps.

atmNteManagerIP.name: atmNteManagerIP
atmNteManagerIP.description: The IP address of the NMS.

atmNteManagerPvc.name: atmNteManagerPvc
atmNteManagerPvc.description: A PVC index. The range is 1..8. There are four PVCs on the User Port and four PVCs on the Network Port. The default VPI, VCI values are specified below.

atmNteManagerIfIndex.name: atmNteManagerIfIndex
atmNteManagerIfIndex.description: The ATM interface index of the management port.

atmNteManagerVpi.name: atmNteManagerVpi
atmNteManagerVpi.description: The VPI of the management VCL. Default: 0.

atmNteManagerVci.name: atmNteManagerVci
atmNteManagerVci.description: The VCI of the management VCL. Defaults: 32,33,34,35.

atmNteManagerTrapMask.name: atmNteManagerTrapMask
atmNteManagerTrapMask.description: The value of this attribute determines the type of traps the agent should mask and not send to this NMS. The value is differently determined for different products. There are mainly two methods: - an integer number, specifying the traps' severity. - a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain masked trap group. User should consult the product specification, to find out the method employed.

atmNteManagerRowStatus.name: atmNteManagerRowStatus
atmNteManagerRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

atmNteManagerNextHop.name: atmNteManagerNextHop
atmNteManagerNextHop.description: This parameter is relevant to Ethernet out of band host only (PVC=10). The Next Hop IP address of the entry route.

atmNteManagerVlanSupport.name: atmNteManagerVlanSupport
atmNteManagerVlanSupport.description: VLAN support (Tagging). no - No support to VLAN. yes - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to the frame.

atmNteManagerAlarmTrapMask.name: atmNteManagerAlarmTrapMask
atmNteManagerAlarmTrapMask.description: The value of this object determines the alarm traps that the agent should mask and not send to this NMS. The value is an Octet String, where each bit is assigned to a certain trap. If the bit = 1, the trap will be masked. If the bit = 0, the trap will not be masked. More details on the masked traps exist in the product specification. For products that do not mask specific traps, the value of the bits will be 0.

atmNteManagerConfigPorts.name: atmNteManagerConfigPorts
atmNteManagerConfigPorts.description: This variable defines from which port/s this manager can configure the device. For IPmux 11 the value of this variable will be according to the ports combination: Network =1 User1=2 User2=4 (For Example: All ports = 7).

atmNteUPLTCR.name: atmNteUPLTCR
atmNteUPLTCR.description: The Unacceptable ES Limit threshold for Performance Management.

atmNteDPLTCR.name: atmNteDPLTCR
atmNteDPLTCR.description: The Degraded ES Limit threshold for Performance Management.

atmNteSysLogClearAll.name: atmNteSysLogClearAll
atmNteSysLogClearAll.description: Setting the variable to clear(3) removes all entries in the Log Buffer of the agent. The agent will immediately reset the variable to off(2).

atmNteUSESLTCR.name: atmNteUSESLTCR
atmNteUSESLTCR.description: The Unacceptable SES Limit threshold for Performance Management.

atmNteDSESLTCR.name: atmNteDSESLTCR
atmNteDSESLTCR.description: The Degraded ES Limit threshold for Performance Management.

atmNteProtectionMode.name: atmNteProtectionMode
atmNteProtectionMode.description: Protection Mode. MspOn - Multiplex section protection. pathOn - High order path protection. mspUniOn - Multiplex section Uni-directional protection. mspOneToN - Multiplex section protection.

atmNteProtectionWorkingLink.name: atmNteProtectionWorkingLink
atmNteProtectionWorkingLink.description: Selects the working link when atmNteProtectionMode is off.

atmNteProtectionSwitchLink.name: atmNteProtectionSwitchLink
atmNteProtectionSwitchLink.description: ForceSwitch - will force Switching from the working link to the backup link. Afterwards the agent will set atmNteProtectionSwitchLink back to off(1). atmNteProtectionMode must be either mspOn or pathOn.

atmNteConfOamSupport.name: atmNteConfOamSupport
atmNteConfOamSupport.description: OAM support mode, which determines the device location in a segment wise.

atmNteConfOamAIS.name: atmNteConfOamAIS
atmNteConfOamAIS.description: Defines if a F4 segment OAM cell is transmitted due to problems in the other port, i.e. physical layer alarm or F4 defect. This is valid only when the ACE101 has ATM UNI interfaces in both sides and is configured for 'Non-Intrusive' mode. none - AIS is not sent to any of the ports. user - F4 AIS will be sent toward the user when defect is detected in the network port. network - F4 AIS will be sent toward the network when defect is detected in the user port. both - F4 AIS will be sent toward the network when defect is detected in the user port and toward the user when defect is detected in the network port.

atmNteConfOamRDI.name: atmNteConfOamRDI
atmNteConfOamRDI.description: Defines if an F4 OAM RDI cell is transmitted due to physical layer problems in the port (in addition to F4 RDI cells transmitted due to ATM layer problems). The type of F4 RDI (Segment or End-to-End) is according to the ACE-101 OAM mode. For example, If it is enabled for Network port, then physical layer defect will initiate the transmission of F4 RDI cell back to the trunk.

atmNteConfLoopbackAddMode.name: atmNteConfLoopbackAddMode
atmNteConfLoopbackAddMode.description: Loopback addressing mode. on - will enable loopback addressing. off - will disable loopback addressing.

atmNteConfLoopbackSourceAdd.name: atmNteConfLoopbackSourceAdd
atmNteConfLoopbackSourceAdd.description: Loopback source address. This field is relevant when atmNteConfOamAddMode is on.

atmNteConfOamIfAisRdi.name: atmNteConfOamIfAisRdi
atmNteConfOamIfAisRdi.description: This parameter controls the generation of F4/F5 AIS and RDI due to lower order problems such as physical layer problems. For AIS: Defines if F4/F5 AIS cell is transmitted due to problems such as physical layer alarm or F4/F5 defect. This is applicable for all ports . off - Problems in this port will not trigger F4/F5 AIS transmition to the ajacent port (e.g. from USER to NETWORK) of a VPC/VCC. on - Problems in this port will trigger F4/F5 AIS transmition to the ajacent port (e.g. from USER to NETWORK) of a VPC/VCC. For RDI: Defines if F4/F5 RDI cell will be transmitted due to physical layer problems in that port (in addition to F4/F5 RDI cells transmitted due to ATM layer problems). For example, If it is enabled for Network port, then physical layer defect will initiate the transmission of F4/F5 RDI cell back to the trunk. The type of F4/F5 (Segment or End-to-End) is according to the configuration of the VPC/VCC.

atmNteConfCACMode.name: atmNteConfCACMode
atmNteConfCACMode.description: CAC support mode. For ACE2002, the following are the applicable values: disable(1), enable(2), 10 - 1000.

atmNteHostPvcIndex.name: atmNteHostPvcIndex
atmNteHostPvcIndex.description: A PVC index. The range is 1..10.

atmNteHostAtmIfIndex.name: atmNteHostAtmIfIndex
atmNteHostAtmIfIndex.description: ATM interface index. Will be 1 for user port, and 2 for network port.

atmNteHostVpi.name: atmNteHostVpi
atmNteHostVpi.description: VPI of the PVC connected to that host interface.

atmNteHostVci.name: atmNteHostVci
atmNteHostVci.description: VCI of the PVC connected to that host interface.

atmNteHostRowStatus.name: atmNteHostRowStatus
atmNteHostRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

atmNteHostRdnVpi.name: atmNteHostRdnVpi
atmNteHostRdnVpi.description: The VPI of the redundant management VCL. This parameter is applicable only if atmNteRdnManagement=enable(3).

atmNteHostRdnVci.name: atmNteHostRdnVci
atmNteHostRdnVci.description: The VCI of the redundant management VCL. This parameter is applicable only if atmNteRdnManagement=enable(3).

atmNteHostDefaultNextHop.name: atmNteHostDefaultNextHop
atmNteHostDefaultNextHop.description: The host interface Default Next Hop address. This address will be used as default next hop for every Bundle mapped to this Host.

atmNteHostVlanTagging.name: atmNteHostVlanTagging
atmNteHostVlanTagging.description: VLAN Tag support. no - No support to VLAN. yes - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to each frame connected to this Host.

atmNteHostDefaultVlanID.name: atmNteHostDefaultVlanID
atmNteHostDefaultVlanID.description: Default VLAN ID of this Host.

atmNteHostDefaultVlanPriority.name: atmNteHostDefaultVlanPriority
atmNteHostDefaultVlanPriority.description: Default VLAN priority for this Host.

atmNteShaperMode.name: atmNteShaperMode
atmNteShaperMode.description: Shaper Mode. vpInbandMng - Vcc within a Vp for management.

atmNteOutputRate.name: atmNteOutputRate
atmNteOutputRate.description: Aggregate shaping output rate in Cells per Seconds units. Default value is the Network port rate.

atmNteTosMask.name: atmNteTosMask
atmNteTosMask.description: This parameter determines the seqence of bits that will be used for TOS. For ACE101 this parameter is applicable only if atmNteTosMode = enable. Valid only for IP-TOS process.

atmNteTosHighPriority.name: atmNteTosHighPriority
atmNteTosHighPriority.description: Priorities options are High or Low. High priority will be represented by bit = 1. Low priority will be represented by bit = 0. Each TOS value will be represented by the bit location. For example, the string for TOS 2, 9, 15 with High priority, will be: |0000 0000|... ...|0000 0000|1000 0010|0000 0100| ...98 7654 3210 (Bit #) 8 ... 3 2 1 (Byte #).

atmNtePlugAndPlayActivity.name: atmNtePlugAndPlayActivity
atmNtePlugAndPlayActivity.description: Activity control for Manager Plug And Play. disable - disable the feature. offline - Automatic learn IP address into offline memory. online - Automatic learn IP address into online memory.

atmNteSlotUsage.name: atmNteSlotUsage
atmNteSlotUsage.description: Applicable to ace2002. Slot 2 might be configured as user slot or as network slot.

atmNteConnectionsMaxNumber.name: atmNteConnectionsMaxNumber
atmNteConnectionsMaxNumber.description: The MAX number of connections supported by system. Setting this parameter will affect the number of MAX intervals supported. This parameter will affect the system only after reset. Changing this parameter from high value to a low value, will be accepted by agent only if the actual used connection <= the desired connection Max number. Applicable to ace2002.

atmNtePlugAndPlayIfIndex.name: atmNtePlugAndPlayIfIndex
atmNtePlugAndPlayIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the Plug and Play VCC.

atmNteLoopbackTimeout.name: atmNteLoopbackTimeout
atmNteLoopbackTimeout.description: The Loopback state timeout in minutes. A value of zero means no timeout (for ever). Default is 5 min.

atmNteOamTable.name: atmNteOamTable
atmNteOamTable.description: This table is a static table, which is created by agent once upon initialization. The created entries are actually, only the supported OAM features. This table enables addition of new features by adding new entries rather than adding scalar parameters. An OAM feature is defined by the indexes values combination.

atmNteOamEntry.name: atmNteOamEntry
atmNteOamEntry.description: An entry in the OAM table. Each entry in this table will indicate a special OAM.

atmNteOamMode.name: atmNteOamMode
atmNteOamMode.description: The OAM cell path. endToEnd(1) - the entire path.

atmNteOamCellType.name: atmNteOamCellType
atmNteOamCellType.description: This object indicates a unique Indication Signal. aisAndRdi(1) - Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) and Remote Defect Indication (RDI) cell. loopback(2) - Loopback cell.

atmNteOamLevel.name: atmNteOamLevel
atmNteOamLevel.description: The level of the OAM cell. -- f4 (2) - VP level, f5 (3) - VC level.

atmNteOamEnable.name: atmNteOamEnable
atmNteOamEnable.description: This parameter determines if the specified OAM cells will be enabled.

atmNteDefaultLoopbackThreshold.name: atmNteDefaultLoopbackThreshold
atmNteDefaultLoopbackThreshold.description: The Default OAM Loopback Failure Threshold value that will be used for configuration.

atmNteMaxBurstSize.name: atmNteMaxBurstSize
atmNteMaxBurstSize.description: The Maximum allowed burst size (cell units). This object is applicable for each Physical port.

atmNteGranularityFactor.name: atmNteGranularityFactor
atmNteGranularityFactor.description: This parameter affects the granularity of the guaranteed Rate (SCR+MCR) in spaced connection (cell/sec units). It is also defines the minimum guaranteed rate in spaced connection.

atmNteTotalInputRate.name: atmNteTotalInputRate
atmNteTotalInputRate.description: This parameter indicates the total input rate of the device in cells/sec.

atmNteTotalOutputRate.name: atmNteTotalOutputRate
atmNteTotalOutputRate.description: This parameter indicates the total output rate of the device in cells/sec.

atmAlarmForwardingTable.name: atmAlarmForwardingTable
atmAlarmForwardingTable.description: The Alarm Forwarding Mechanism will be operated for this table entries.

atmAlarmForwardingEntry.name: atmAlarmForwardingEntry
atmAlarmForwardingEntry.description: Each entry in this table is a pair of ports that the Alarm Forwarding Mechanism is determined for.

atmAlarmForwardingFailPort.name: atmAlarmForwardingFailPort
atmAlarmForwardingFailPort.description: An Index of the port on which a fail occurs.

atmAlarmForwardingToPort.name: atmAlarmForwardingToPort
atmAlarmForwardingToPort.description: An Index of the port that will be affected upon the failure of the atmAlarmForwardingFailPort.

atmAlarmForwardingRowStatus.name: atmAlarmForwardingRowStatus
atmAlarmForwardingRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

atmAlarmForwardingFailureLevel.name: atmAlarmForwardingFailureLevel
atmAlarmForwardingFailureLevel.description: This parameter determines the level of failure that will operate the Alarm Forwarding Mechanism.

atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryMode.name: atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryMode
atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryMode.description: This parameter determines the Recovery Mode. manual - The user should stop the RDI transmission by using the atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryCommand. automatic - The RDI transmission will be automatically stopped upon atmAlarmForwardingFailPort recovery.

atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryCommand.name: atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryCommand
atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryCommand.description: This parameter is a command. It is applicable when atmAlarmForwardingRecoveryMode = manual. on - Will stop the RDI transmission. After setting to 'On' the agent will set this parameter back to 'Off'.

atmAlarmForwardingTimeFilterWindow.name: atmAlarmForwardingTimeFilterWindow
atmAlarmForwardingTimeFilterWindow.description: This parameter determines the Time Filter Window, meaning: how much time (in seconds) should the alarm exist in order to start the Alarm Forwarding operation.

atmSysConfigCellTestPort.name: atmSysConfigCellTestPort
atmSysConfigCellTestPort.description: An Index of the port on which the cell test will be sent.

atmSysConfigCellTestVpi.name: atmSysConfigCellTestVpi
atmSysConfigCellTestVpi.description: The VPI on which the cell test will be sent.

atmSysConfigCellTestVci.name: atmSysConfigCellTestVci
atmSysConfigCellTestVci.description: The VCI on which the cell test will be sent.

atmSysConfigCellTestOamType.name: atmSysConfigCellTestOamType
atmSysConfigCellTestOamType.description: The OAM type of the Cell. This object is applicable if atmSysConfigCellTestPti = oamSegment/oamEndToEnd .

atmSysConfigCellTestPayload.name: atmSysConfigCellTestPayload
atmSysConfigCellTestPayload.description: The payload of the cell. For OAM cell the payload is set automatically to 6A.

atmSysConfigCellTestSendCmd.name: atmSysConfigCellTestSendCmd
atmSysConfigCellTestSendCmd.description: Setting the variable to send(3) perfroms cell test. The agent will immediately reset the variable to off(2).

atmVpCrossConnectExtenTable.name: atmVpCrossConnectExtenTable
atmVpCrossConnectExtenTable.description: An extension to the ATM VP Cross Connect table (RFC2515 - atmVpCrossConnectTable).

atmVcCrossConnectExtenTable.name: atmVcCrossConnectExtenTable
atmVcCrossConnectExtenTable.description: An extension to the ATM VC Cross Connect table (RFC2515 - atmVcCrossConnectTable).

atmNteQosMode.name: atmNteQosMode
atmNteQosMode.description: This variable defines the QoS Mode. disable(1) - QoS is disabled. multipleVc(2) - QoS is enabled and multiple VCs can be bound per bridge port. singleVc(3) - QoS is enabled and only single VC can be bound per bridge port.

atmTrafficDescrParamXTable.name: atmTrafficDescrParamXTable
atmTrafficDescrParamXTable.description: An Augment to ATM Traffic Descriptor Parameter Table (atmTrafficDescrParamTable in ATM-MIB; RFC-2515).

atmTrafficDescrParamMode.name: atmTrafficDescrParamMode
atmTrafficDescrParamMode.description: The Mode of the Traffic Descriptor.

atmNteIdTable.name: atmNteIdTable
atmNteIdTable.description: The IDs of the cards and of the system.

atmNteIdIndex.name: atmNteIdIndex
atmNteIdIndex.description: An Index of the Unit ID table. The following units have IDs in this table: 1 - System 2 - ATM Board 3 - User Card 4 - Trunk 1 card 5 - Trunk 2 card 6 - Shaper 7 - Clock Unit 8 - Slot 1 card 9 - Slot 2 card 10 - Slot 3 card 11 - Slot 4 card 12 - Fan1 13 - Fan2 14 - Control Unit.

atmNteUnitId.name: atmNteUnitId
atmNteUnitId.description: The ID of the Unit. For index = 6, the id will describe the validity of a shaper in the system: 0 - Shaper Not exist 1 - Shaper exist. For index = 7, the id will describe the validity of a clock in the system: 0 - Clock Not exist 1 - Clock exist. 2- Clock exist but failed. For index = 12,13 the id will describe the functionality of a FAN1 : 0 - OK 1 - Failed.

atmNteUnitVersion.name: atmNteUnitVersion
atmNteUnitVersion.description: Hardware and Software version of the module.

atmNteCardStatus.name: atmNteCardStatus
atmNteCardStatus.description: Status of the card in the selected slot. notActive - Connections are in NotReady state. No configuration is available for the card. The access to the card HW is blocked. This state is relevant for an extracted card, and for a case in which the card was deactivated. active - The module installed and functions. A card that in this state can be configured. inProgress - The status during proccessing of a command from atmNteCardCmd. empty - No information is valid for the selected slot. This status is relevant to a case in which the card configaration was deleted, or in case in which a slot was empty since the device startup.

atmNteCardCmd.name: atmNteCardCmd
atmNteCardCmd.description: Command on the card that is installed in the selected slot. The commands are applicable according to the value of atmNteCardStatus. See the specification document for details. deleteConfig - Deletes the card configuration. deactivate - All the connections state will be changed to NotReady. The card configuration will be blocked. activate - Does the same as done upon card insertion: Initiates the relevant parameters, activates the physical layer, ATM layer and logical layer.

atmSysPSunits.name: atmSysPSunits
atmSysPSunits.description: The number of power supply units.

atmSysPSunitsInUse.name: atmSysPSunitsInUse
atmSysPSunitsInUse.description: The main power supply in this unit.

atmNteBridgingMode.name: atmNteBridgingMode
atmNteBridgingMode.description: Bridging mode can be one of the following: ATM <> Ethernet - Bridging is between the Ethernet port and the ATM port (there is no bridging between VCs). ATM <> Ethernet + ATM - Bridging is done both between the Ethernet port and the ATM port and also between VCs.

atmSysCurrentCdc.name: atmSysCurrentCdc
atmSysCurrentCdc.description: Seconds in which cells dropped was occured in the current 15 minutes interval.

atmSysIntervalNumber.name: atmSysIntervalNumber
atmSysIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

atmSysIntervalCdc.name: atmSysIntervalCdc
atmSysIntervalCdc.description: Seconds in which cells dropped was occured in 15 minutes interval.

atmNteEventType.name: atmNteEventType
atmNteEventType.description: This parameter identifies the event. On - the problem exist. Off - the problem not exist. InvalidLogin - Invalid login on local console. CorrectLogin - Successful login operation.

atmNteIntervalMaxNumber.name: atmNteIntervalMaxNumber
atmNteIntervalMaxNumber.description: The MAX number of connections intervals supported by system. This parameter value is a function of atmNteConnectionsMaxNumber parameter. This parameter should affect the threshold values selected by user. Applicable to ace2002.

atmNteAlarmType.name: atmNteAlarmType
atmNteAlarmType.description: This object specifies the type of the alarm.

atmNteLevel.name: atmNteLevel
atmNteLevel.description: This object specifies the ATM level.

atmNteConnectionsNumber.name: atmNteConnectionsNumber
atmNteConnectionsNumber.description: This object specifies a quantity of connections.

atmNteTotalLb.name: atmNteTotalLb
atmNteTotalLb.description: This parameter counts the total number of end-points that were configured with Loopback (LB).

atmNteTotalCc.name: atmNteTotalCc
atmNteTotalCc.description: This parameter counts the total number of end-points that were configured with Continuity Check (CC).

atmNteTotalPm.name: atmNteTotalPm
atmNteTotalPm.description: This parameter counts the total number of end-points that were configured with PM.

atmLoopbackVpTable.name: atmLoopbackVpTable
atmLoopbackVpTable.description: This table contains parameters for an OAM VP loopback test.

atmLoopbackVpIfIndex.name: atmLoopbackVpIfIndex
atmLoopbackVpIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmLoopbackVpVpi.name: atmLoopbackVpVpi
atmLoopbackVpVpi.description: The VPI of the OAM VPL.

atmLoopbackVpOperStatus.name: atmLoopbackVpOperStatus
atmLoopbackVpOperStatus.description: -noActive(1) means that the loopback test has not been activated for this VP. -inProgress(2) means that the test has been activated and there is currently no problem. -failed(3) means there was problem during the test or after having stopped it -endSuccessfully(4) means that the test was stopped and all was OK.

atmLoopbackVpCDV.name: atmLoopbackVpCDV
atmLoopbackVpCDV.description: Cell Delay Variation for this sampling.

atmLoopbackVpAverageDelay.name: atmLoopbackVpAverageDelay
atmLoopbackVpAverageDelay.description: Average delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVpMaxDelay.name: atmLoopbackVpMaxDelay
atmLoopbackVpMaxDelay.description: Maximum delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVpErrSessions.name: atmLoopbackVpErrSessions
atmLoopbackVpErrSessions.description: Errored Sessions. Will be updated once in 5 seconds.

atmLoopbackVcTable.name: atmLoopbackVcTable
atmLoopbackVcTable.description: This table contains parameters for an OAM VC loopback test.

atmLoopbackVcIfIndex.name: atmLoopbackVcIfIndex
atmLoopbackVcIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmLoopbackVcVpi.name: atmLoopbackVcVpi
atmLoopbackVcVpi.description: The VPI of the OAM VCL.

atmLoopbackVcVci.name: atmLoopbackVcVci
atmLoopbackVcVci.description: The VCI of the OAM VCL.

atmLoopbackVcOperStatus.name: atmLoopbackVcOperStatus
atmLoopbackVcOperStatus.description: -noActive(1) means that the loopback test has not been activated for this VP. -inProgress(2) means that the test has been activated and there is currently no problem. -failed(3) means there was problem during the test or after having stopped it -endSuccessfully(4) means that the test was stopped and all was OK.

atmLoopbackVcCDV.name: atmLoopbackVcCDV
atmLoopbackVcCDV.description: Cell Delay Variation for this sampling.

atmLoopbackVcAverageDelay.name: atmLoopbackVcAverageDelay
atmLoopbackVcAverageDelay.description: Average delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVcMaxDelay.name: atmLoopbackVcMaxDelay
atmLoopbackVcMaxDelay.description: The maximum delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVcErrSessions.name: atmLoopbackVcErrSessions
atmLoopbackVcErrSessions.description: Errored Sessions. Will be updated once in 5 seconds.

atmLoopbackVpIvlTable.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlTable
atmLoopbackVpIvlTable.description: This table contains parameters for an OAM VP loopback test, according interval number.

atmLoopbackVpIvlIfIndex.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlIfIndex
atmLoopbackVpIvlIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmLoopbackVpIvlVpi.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlVpi
atmLoopbackVpIvlVpi.description: The VPI of the OAM VPL.

atmLoopbackVpIvlOperStatus.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlOperStatus
atmLoopbackVpIvlOperStatus.description: -noActive(1) means that the loopback test has not been activated for this VP during this interval. -inProgress(2) has no meaning for an ended interval. -failed(3) means there was problem during the test or after having stopped it -endSuccessfully(4) means that the test was OK.

atmLoopbackVpIvlCDV.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlCDV
atmLoopbackVpIvlCDV.description: Cell Delay Variation for this interval.

atmLoopbackVpIvlAverageDelay.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlAverageDelay
atmLoopbackVpIvlAverageDelay.description: Average delay without including lost cells for this interval.

atmLoopbackVpIvlMaxDelay.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlMaxDelay
atmLoopbackVpIvlMaxDelay.description: The maximum delay without including lost cells for this interval.

atmLoopbackVpIvlMinDelay.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlMinDelay
atmLoopbackVpIvlMinDelay.description: The minimum delay for this interval.

atmLoopbackVpIvlErrSessions.name: atmLoopbackVpIvlErrSessions
atmLoopbackVpIvlErrSessions.description: Errored Sessions. Will be updated once in 5 seconds.

atmLoopbackVcIvlTable.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlTable
atmLoopbackVcIvlTable.description: This table contains parameters for an OAM VC loopback test.

atmLoopbackVcIvlIfIndex.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlIfIndex
atmLoopbackVcIvlIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmLoopbackVcIvlVpi.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlVpi
atmLoopbackVcIvlVpi.description: The VPI of the OAM VCL.

atmLoopbackVcIvlVci.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlVci
atmLoopbackVcIvlVci.description: The VCI of the OAM VCL.

atmLoopbackVcIvlOperStatus.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlOperStatus
atmLoopbackVcIvlOperStatus.description: -noActive(1) means that the loopback test has not been activated for this VC during this interval. -inProgress(2) has no meaning per interval. -failed(3) means there was problem for this test during this interval. -endSuccessfully(4) means that the test was OK.

atmLoopbackVcIvlCDV.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlCDV
atmLoopbackVcIvlCDV.description: Cell Delay Variation for this interval.

atmLoopbackVcIvlAverageDelay.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlAverageDelay
atmLoopbackVcIvlAverageDelay.description: Average delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVcIvlMaxDelay.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlMaxDelay
atmLoopbackVcIvlMaxDelay.description: The maximum delay without including lost cells.

atmLoopbackVcIvlErrSessions.name: atmLoopbackVcIvlErrSessions
atmLoopbackVcIvlErrSessions.description: Errored Sessions. Will be updated once in 5 seconds.

atmVpPmTable.name: atmVpPmTable
atmVpPmTable.description: This table contains parameters for VP performance monitoring.

atmVpPmIfIndex.name: atmVpPmIfIndex
atmVpPmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmVpPmVpi.name: atmVpPmVpi
atmVpPmVpi.description: The VPI of the Performance Monitoring VPL.

atmVpPmAdminStatus.name: atmVpPmAdminStatus
atmVpPmAdminStatus.description: up(2) - Activate PM. down(3) - Deactivate PM. listenToActivationCells(4) - . originateActivationCells(5) - .

atmVpPmRowStatus.name: atmVpPmRowStatus
atmVpPmRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

atmVpPmSink.name: atmVpPmSink
atmVpPmSink.description: off (1) - Deactivate PM. fwd (2) - Activate Forward PM only. fwdAndBwdReport(3) - Activate Forward PM and Backward reporting.

atmVpPmSource.name: atmVpPmSource
atmVpPmSource.description: off (1) - Deactivate PM. fwd (2) - Activate Forward PM only. fwdAndBwdReport(3) - Activate Forward PM and Backward reporting.

atmVcPmTable.name: atmVcPmTable
atmVcPmTable.description: This table contains parameters for VC performance monitoring.

atmVcPmIfIndex.name: atmVcPmIfIndex
atmVcPmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the ATM layer.

atmVcPmVpi.name: atmVcPmVpi
atmVcPmVpi.description: The VPI of the Performance Monitoring VCL.

atmVcPmVci.name: atmVcPmVci
atmVcPmVci.description: The VCI of the PM VCL.

atmVcPmAdminStatus.name: atmVcPmAdminStatus
atmVcPmAdminStatus.description: up(2) - Activate PM. down(3) - Deactivate PM. listenToActivationCells(4) - . originateActivationCells(5) - .

atmVcPmRowStatus.name: atmVcPmRowStatus
atmVcPmRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

atmVcPmSink.name: atmVcPmSink
atmVcPmSink.description: off (1) - Deactivate PM. fwd (2) - Activate Forward PM only. fwdAndBwdReport(3) - Activate Forward PM and Backward reporting.

atmVcPmSource.name: atmVcPmSource
atmVcPmSource.description: off (1) - Deactivate PM. fwd (2) - Activate Forward PM only. fwdAndBwdReport(3) - Activate Forward PM and Backward reporting.

atmNteMdlConfigEntry.name: atmNteMdlConfigEntry
atmNteMdlConfigEntry.description: There is an entry in this table just for those modules that have parameters that are relevant to module level only.

atmNteMdlPrtCpuSharing.name: atmNteMdlPrtCpuSharing
atmNteMdlPrtCpuSharing.description: This object lets the user decide what will be the CPU sharing between the ports of the module. This object is applicable for modules in which the same CPU handles the traffic of all ports. equal - All ports will have the same CPU resource. port1 - Port 1 will have higher priority than the other ports.

atmNteMdlInputPriorityMechanism.name: atmNteMdlInputPriorityMechanism
atmNteMdlInputPriorityMechanism.description: This object allows the user to Enable/Disable the Input priority mechanism. This object is applicable for modules with more than one port, in which the total ports input may be greater than the port output. disabled - all LAN VCCs will be transmitted through the same queue (queue 1). Upon congestion frames will be dropped randomly. enabled - the user should configure each port/connection priority. Upon congestion frames will be dropped according to priority.

atmGenSysSelfTestTable.name: atmGenSysSelfTestTable
atmGenSysSelfTestTable.description: A table containing the results of the initial testing of the device.

atmGenSysSelfTestIndex.name: atmGenSysSelfTestIndex
atmGenSysSelfTestIndex.description: A running index for the table.

atmGenSysSelfTestResult.name: atmGenSysSelfTestResult
atmGenSysSelfTestResult.description: The results of the initial testing of the device.

atmGenSysSelfTestModule.name: atmGenSysSelfTestModule
atmGenSysSelfTestModule.description: The name of module on which the test was performed.

atmGenSysLogClearAll.name: atmGenSysLogClearAll
atmGenSysLogClearAll.description: Setting the variable to clear(3) removes all entries in the Log Buffer of the agent. The agent will immediately reset the variable to off(2).

atmGenSysLogTable.name: atmGenSysLogTable
atmGenSysLogTable.description: A copy of the log buffer.

atmGenSysLogIndex.name: atmGenSysLogIndex
atmGenSysLogIndex.description: The index of the log buffer.

atmGenSysLogMessage.name: atmGenSysLogMessage
atmGenSysLogMessage.description: The log buffer entry message text.

atmGenSysSetDefaultConfg.name: atmGenSysSetDefaultConfg
atmGenSysSetDefaultConfg.description: When set to on(3), the agent will set all the configuration parameters to their default values. The variable is then reset to off(2) by the agent. The agent must be reset for the default configuration to apply.

atmGenSysCxRefTable.name: atmGenSysCxRefTable
atmGenSysCxRefTable.description: A Cross Reference table. The table maintains an index of an object which is also the table index, and a counter that indicates how many times this object was referenced. When using this table for more than one referenced table, which uses the same range of indexes, then the index should be shifted by a unique offset per table. In ACE2002 this table is used for TD and for FR Desc. Thus, the index for FR Descriptor is: FR Descriptor index + offset. The offset is described in the ACE2002 NMS SRS.

atmGenSysCxRefEntry.name: atmGenSysCxRefEntry
atmGenSysCxRefEntry.description: The entries will be added by the agent upon an entry addition in the referenced tables (TD table, FR Descriptor etc.)

atmGenSysCxRefIndex.name: atmGenSysCxRefIndex
atmGenSysCxRefIndex.description: The index specifies an entry in the table of the object.

atmGenSysCxRefCounter.name: atmGenSysCxRefCounter
atmGenSysCxRefCounter.description: The counter counts the number of references that have been made to the object .

atmAceStatusChange.name: atmAceStatusChange
atmAceStatusChange.description: The trap is sent every time there is a change in the state of one of the LEDs.

atmAceAlarmTrap.name: atmAceAlarmTrap
atmAceAlarmTrap.description: The trap is sent whenever there is a transition from a no alarm state to a state with at least one active alarm. An active alarm state exists if: 1) The atmInterfaceActiveAlarms vector is different than 0. 2) The atmNteAlarmVpTable contains entries. 3) The atmNteAlarmVcTable contains entries. The trap is also sent when a transition into the no alarm state occurs. The second variable will be atmInterfaceActiveAlarms to indicate the kind of the alarm. The trap is not sent more than once in a 10 second interval.

atmAceModuleChangeTrap.name: atmAceModuleChangeTrap
atmAceModuleChangeTrap.description: The trap is sent every time a module is changed (Hot swapping). The second variable will be atmNteCardType to indicate the type of card that was inserted. The value empty(255) indicates that a card was taken out.

atmAceRedundancyTrap.name: atmAceRedundancyTrap
atmAceRedundancyTrap.description: The trap is sent upon change in link as a result of redundancy. The ifIndex parameter indicates the current active link.

atmAceModuleMismatchTrap.name: atmAceModuleMismatchTrap
atmAceModuleMismatchTrap.description: The trap is sent upon starting or stopping of a module mismatch state. A possible mismatch is when the inserted module is other than the programmed one.

atmAceSystemTrap.name: atmAceSystemTrap
atmAceSystemTrap.description: This trap alerts of major problems in the device.

atmAceAlarmForwardingTrap.name: atmAceAlarmForwardingTrap
atmAceAlarmForwardingTrap.description: This trap is sent upon starting or stopping Alarm Forwarding Mechanism.

atmAceDateAndTimeRequest.name: atmAceDateAndTimeRequest
atmAceDateAndTimeRequest.description: This trap is sent upon restart. Upon recieving this trap the NMS will set the device's date and time. This trap's purpose is to fix a problem in ACE2002, ACE-2002E, ACE-202. The problem is that the Date and Time is stored in the NVRAM, and when the NVRAM's battery is empty, the device loses this information.

atmAceAlarmLOS.name: atmAceAlarmLOS
atmAceAlarmLOS.description: This trap indicates Loss Of Signal.

atmAceAlarmLOF.name: atmAceAlarmLOF
atmAceAlarmLOF.description: This trap indicates Loss Of Frame.

atmAceAlarmLCD.name: atmAceAlarmLCD
atmAceAlarmLCD.description: This trap indicates Loss of Cell Delineation.

atmAceAlarmSLM.name: atmAceAlarmSLM
atmAceAlarmSLM.description: This trap indicates Signal Line Mismatch.

atmAceAlarmLOP.name: atmAceAlarmLOP
atmAceAlarmLOP.description: This trap indicates Loss of Pointer.

atmAceAlarmPathRDI.name: atmAceAlarmPathRDI
atmAceAlarmPathRDI.description: This trap indicates Path RDIand Path RAI(Yellow) for DS1 interfaces.

atmAceAlarmSectionBIP.name: atmAceAlarmSectionBIP
atmAceAlarmSectionBIP.description: This trap indicates Section Bit Interleave Parity.

atmAceAlarmLineBIP.name: atmAceAlarmLineBIP
atmAceAlarmLineBIP.description: This trap indicates Line Bit Interleave Parity.

atmAceAlarmPathBIP.name: atmAceAlarmPathBIP
atmAceAlarmPathBIP.description: This trap indicates Path Bit Interleave Parity.

atmAceAlarmLineFEBE.name: atmAceAlarmLineFEBE
atmAceAlarmLineFEBE.description: This trap indicates Line Far End Block Error.

atmAceAlarmPathFEBE.name: atmAceAlarmPathFEBE
atmAceAlarmPathFEBE.description: This trap indicates Path Far End Block Error.

atmAceAlarmPlcpLOF.name: atmAceAlarmPlcpLOF
atmAceAlarmPlcpLOF.description: This trap indicates T3 PLCP Loss Of Frame.

atmAceAlarmPlcpYELLOW.name: atmAceAlarmPlcpYELLOW
atmAceAlarmPlcpYELLOW.description: This trap indicates T3 Plcp Yellow.

atmAceAlarmPlcpBIP.name: atmAceAlarmPlcpBIP
atmAceAlarmPlcpBIP.description: This trap indicates T3 Plcp Bit Interleave Parity.

atmAceAlarmPlcpFEBE.name: atmAceAlarmPlcpFEBE
atmAceAlarmPlcpFEBE.description: This trap indicates T3 Plcp Far End Block Error.

atmAceAlarmPlcpP1P2.name: atmAceAlarmPlcpP1P2
atmAceAlarmPlcpP1P2.description: This trap indicates T3 Plcp Parity errors in P1/P2 bytes.

atmAceAlarmUAS.name: atmAceAlarmUAS
atmAceAlarmUAS.description: This trap is sent upon UAS start or end per port.

atmAceAlarmCluster.name: atmAceAlarmCluster
atmAceAlarmCluster.description: This trap is sent upon atmNteAlarmType start or end, for a cluster of VPs/VCs (according to atmNteLevel) with the same alarm on the same physical port. This trap replaces sending the same alarm for a big quantity (the quantity described in the product specification document) of VPs/VCs in order to prevent flooding the NMS and the network with traps.

atmAceHwFailure.name: atmAceHwFailure
atmAceHwFailure.description: This trap is sent upon HW failure per port.

atmAceUnavailableBwTrap.name: atmAceUnavailableBwTrap
atmAceUnavailableBwTrap.description: This trap is sent when Bandwidth allocation is > max possible value for the installed card. For ACE2002 this trap will be sent for the following cases: Card insertion - if the total Input and/or Output Bandwidth is over allocated, then the specific card rate will be set to 0 and this trap will be sent with the Input/Output rates values. Upgrade from former version - when an over allocated Bandwidth is detected, this trap will be sent with atmConfIfInputRate=atmConfIfOutputRate=0xFFFFFFFF.

atmAceAlarmVpContinuityLoss.name: atmAceAlarmVpContinuityLoss
atmAceAlarmVpContinuityLoss.description: This trap indicates Loss of Continuity Check on a VP Connection.

atmAceAlarmVpAISReception.name: atmAceAlarmVpAISReception
atmAceAlarmVpAISReception.description: This trap indicates AIS Reception on a VP Connection.

atmAceAlarmVpRDIReception.name: atmAceAlarmVpRDIReception
atmAceAlarmVpRDIReception.description: This trap indicates RDI Reception on a VP Connection.

atmAceAlarmVpErroredCells.name: atmAceAlarmVpErroredCells
atmAceAlarmVpErroredCells.description: This trap indicates Errored Cells on a VP Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVpLostCells.name: atmAceAlarmVpLostCells
atmAceAlarmVpLostCells.description: This trap indicates Lost Cells on a VP Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVpMisinsertedCells.name: atmAceAlarmVpMisinsertedCells
atmAceAlarmVpMisinsertedCells.description: This trap indicates Misinserted Cells on a VP Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVpUAS.name: atmAceAlarmVpUAS
atmAceAlarmVpUAS.description: This trap is sent upon UAS start or end per VP.

atmAceAlarmVpLoopback.name: atmAceAlarmVpLoopback
atmAceAlarmVpLoopback.description: This trap is sent upon OAM LoopBack fail status per VP.

atmAceAlarmVpGCRAViolation.name: atmAceAlarmVpGCRAViolation
atmAceAlarmVpGCRAViolation.description: This trap indicates GCRA violation on a VP Connection reported by UPC device.

atmAceAlarmVcContinuityLoss.name: atmAceAlarmVcContinuityLoss
atmAceAlarmVcContinuityLoss.description: This trap indicates Loss of Continuity Check on a VC Connection.

atmAceAlarmVcAISReception.name: atmAceAlarmVcAISReception
atmAceAlarmVcAISReception.description: This trap indicates AIS Reception on a VC.

atmAceAlarmVcRDIReception.name: atmAceAlarmVcRDIReception
atmAceAlarmVcRDIReception.description: This trap indicates RDI Reception on a VC Connection.

atmAceAlarmVcErroredCells.name: atmAceAlarmVcErroredCells
atmAceAlarmVcErroredCells.description: This trap indicates Errored Cells on a VC Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVcLostCells.name: atmAceAlarmVcLostCells
atmAceAlarmVcLostCells.description: This trap indicates Lost Cells on a VC Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVcMisinsertedCells.name: atmAceAlarmVcMisinsertedCells
atmAceAlarmVcMisinsertedCells.description: This trap indicates Misinserted Cells on a VC Connection reported by PM.

atmAceAlarmVcUnexpectedCell.name: atmAceAlarmVcUnexpectedCell
atmAceAlarmVcUnexpectedCell.description: This trap indicates an unexpected cell from user or network port.

atmAceAlarmVcUAS.name: atmAceAlarmVcUAS
atmAceAlarmVcUAS.description: This trap is sent upon UAS start or end per VC.

atmAceAlarmVcLoopback.name: atmAceAlarmVcLoopback
atmAceAlarmVcLoopback.description: This trap is sent upon OAM LoopBack fail status per VC.

atmAceAlarmVcGCRAViolation.name: atmAceAlarmVcGCRAViolation
atmAceAlarmVcGCRAViolation.description: This trap indicates GCRA violation on a VC Connection reported by UPC device.

ip2IfChannelIndex.name: ip2IfChannelIndex
ip2IfChannelIndex.description: The channel index, which is actualy the bundle ID.

ip2IfRowStatus.name: ip2IfRowStatus
ip2IfRowStatus.description: This parameter allows NMS to create/delete entries of this table.

ip2IfOperStatus.name: ip2IfOperStatus
ip2IfOperStatus.description: The actual link status. remoteFail - No Rx. localFail - No Tx. unavailable - No echo replay or replay with invalid code or when connection is in Test state. valiodationFail - Connection is in not valid state. standby - offline (can be in pre-sync mode). tdmFail - oper status is down cause of failure in the tdm. hwMismatch - the bundle exists on a card that is not installed or has a different type than the programmed card.

ip2IfAdminStatus.name: ip2IfAdminStatus
ip2IfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the link.

ip2IfNextHop.name: ip2IfNextHop
ip2IfNextHop.description: The next hop to which the frame should be sent. Default value - 0.0.0.0. Upon setting the default value the frame is sent to the default Gateway.

ip2IfDestPort.name: ip2IfDestPort
ip2IfDestPort.description: The destination Bundle at the far-end device.

ip2IfMacAddr.name: ip2IfMacAddr
ip2IfMacAddr.description: The Destination MAC address of the next hop or destination station.

ip2IfJitterBuffer.name: ip2IfJitterBuffer
ip2IfJitterBuffer.description: The maximum cell arrival jitter in 10 usec that the reassembly process will tolerate in the cell stream, without producing errors on the CBR service interface. For KM2100: KML.11 - The range that will be used is 3...300 msec in steps of 1 msec. For Vmux: The range that will be used is 20...100 msec in steps of 10 msec.

ip2IfTos.name: ip2IfTos
ip2IfTos.description: The TOS (Type of Service) value: 0..255. In Vmux-2100/110 devices versions 3.1 and up, in Vmux-210 and in Vmux-4x0: LSB 8 bits - 00 00 00 XX will be used for Signaling packets TOS. Next 8 bits - 00 00 XX 00 will be used for Media packets TOS. Next 16 bits - will be 0. XX = Hex values: 0..FF For mixed packets, TOS of Media Packets will be used. Signaling packets are for example: Keep alive packets and ABCD signaling bits. Media packets are for example: voice, fax, HDLC, payload packets.

ip2IfTDMBytesInFrame.name: ip2IfTDMBytesInFrame
ip2IfTDMBytesInFrame.description: The number of TDM bytes to be placed in a single IP frame payload. For ip2IfTDMoIpMode = cesOverPsn this parameter indicates the number of IP frames, calculated as: 1440/<Number of Timeslots>.

ip2IfVlanSupport.name: ip2IfVlanSupport
ip2IfVlanSupport.description: VLAN support (Tagging). no - No support to VLAN. yes - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to the frame.

ip2IfExitPort.name: ip2IfExitPort
ip2IfExitPort.description: This object determines to which external port the traffic will be sent. auto - the device will decide automatically the exit port. If there is an option for Tx via more than one ETH card then use ext1 (1) and ext2(2) for ETH card #1 (ex. LAN1 or Ggabit-ETH1) and use card2Ext1(5) and card2Ext2(6) for card #2 (ex. LAN1 or Ggabit-ETH1). In Vmux-110/210 ext5 is used for ETH-NET, ext 6 is used for E1/T1 link and ext7 is used for Serial Link. In Vmux-2100 Main Board: ext 5 is used for ETH-NET, ext 6 is used for E1/T1 link A, prtE1T1B is used for E1/T1 link B and prtEthUser is used for ETH-User. prt17(10) - prt20(13) values were added in order to support Gmux2000 VMX Card.

ip2IfVoiceOos.name: ip2IfVoiceOos
ip2IfVoiceOos.description: Voice Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

ip2IfDataOos.name: ip2IfDataOos
ip2IfDataOos.description: Data Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

ip2IfBundleUsage.name: ip2IfBundleUsage
ip2IfBundleUsage.description: The Bundle Resource usage in Kbps.

ip2IfOAM.name: ip2IfOAM
ip2IfOAM.description: This parameter determine the OAM configuration. The LSB (Bit 0 the most right one) is used for OAM connectivity. Values: 0 = disable, 1= enable.

ip2IfTDMoIpMode.name: ip2IfTDMoIpMode
ip2IfTDMoIpMode.description: The TDMoIP Mode configuration. Static- means TS can Tx any time. dynamicLES - means TS can Tx only when line is enabled according to LES protocol. dynamicCAS - means TS can Tx only when line is enabled according to CAS protocol. cesOverIp - use for information that this bundle is used for CES Over IP. voiceOverMpls - Voice over Multi Protocol Label Switching. hdlc - High Level Data Link. voIpComprHeader - indicates proprietary compressed IP header packets. voMplsComprHeader - indicates proprietary compressed MPLS header packets.

ip2IfTimeElapsed.name: ip2IfTimeElapsed
ip2IfTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement period. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value.

ip2IfValidIntervals.name: ip2IfValidIntervals
ip2IfValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought online within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals since the interface has been online.

ip2IfFarEndType.name: ip2IfFarEndType
ip2IfFarEndType.description: This object defines the type of the Far-End device. This data is important for signaling and DS0 format. For Vmux: e1 (2) value is used for a PBX in the Far End. fxs (5) is used for Phone. Other values are not used.

ip2IfRdnState.name: ip2IfRdnState
ip2IfRdnState.description: This object defines the role this bundle plays in the redundancy scheme: none(2) - means this bundle is not part of redundancy pair. primary/ secondary - means this bundle is not part of redundancy pair, and that is the primary bundle or the secondary bunle.

ip2IfSourceAddr.name: ip2IfSourceAddr
ip2IfSourceAddr.description: Source IP Address of the bundle.

ip2IfBandWidth.name: ip2IfBandWidth
ip2IfBandWidth.description: Defines the Bandwidth of the bundle. For TDM bundles - it is the Number of Time Slots in The Bundle. - For T1 the value will be: 1..24 - For E1 the value will be: 1..31 - For T3 the value will be: 1..84 - For E3 the value will be: 1..63 This parameter is required for devices like Emux where the bandwidth of the bundles is unknown. The bundles that are received should be transmitted without any change in the bandwidth. It is the user's responsibility to enter the correct bandwidth. For Ethernet bundles - it is the bandwidth, measured in Kbps.

ip2IfMeasuredSilence.name: ip2IfMeasuredSilence
ip2IfMeasuredSilence.description: This object shows the percentage of Silence that was measured by the device for the current bundle in the transmitted payload. Relevant values: 0..100, 255. Default value is 50. 0 means that there is no silence on the line. 100 means that there is only silence. In this case, there might be no traffic. 255 - value for not applicable or unknown.

ip2IfPayloadType.name: ip2IfPayloadType
ip2IfPayloadType.description: This object defines the TDMoIP payload type.

ip2IfProtocolVersion.name: ip2IfProtocolVersion
ip2IfProtocolVersion.description: This object defines the TDMoIP protocol Version.

ip2IfTdmBackUpNextHop.name: ip2IfTdmBackUpNextHop
ip2IfTdmBackUpNextHop.description: Defines the TDM bundle default router in case there was a switch from the Primary Link (for example an ETH port) to a TDM backup Link like E1, T1 or Serial Link. This parameter is relevant only when a Backup Link is configured. When a Backup Link is not configured the value will be: 0.0.0.0

ip2IfOosTxEnable.name: ip2IfOosTxEnable
ip2IfOosTxEnable.description: This object defines whether OOS will be Transmitted. Note that for IPmux1000 the Lbit is always sent, but the OOS will be sent according to user selection in this parameter.

ip2IfConnCheckPktFrequency.name: ip2IfConnCheckPktFrequency
ip2IfConnCheckPktFrequency.description: Time in sec. between 2 Bundle Connectivity Check packets. Valid values: 0..60. 0 = Not Applicable.

ip2IfConnPktTimeOutCycles.name: ip2IfConnPktTimeOutCycles
ip2IfConnPktTimeOutCycles.description: No. of cycles the agent will send Bundle Connectivity packets without receiving a response from the remote device before declaring that the bundle connection to the remote side is down - Time Out. Valid values: 0..5. 0 = Not Applicable.

ip2IfSuperTandem.name: ip2IfSuperTandem
ip2IfSuperTandem.description: The Super Tandem feature provides end to end compression over multiple hops, solving the double compression problem detected in Voice compressing systems. The Super Tandem allows transmission of compressed voice between a few Vmux 2100 hubs, and eliminates the need to decompress an recompress it over each voice card and PBX, thus improving voice quality and reducing delay.

ip2IfSrcPort.name: ip2IfSrcPort
ip2IfSrcPort.description: The source Bundle at the local device, this parameter used for cases where there is no match between ip2IfChannelIndex and the Source Bundle ID.

ip2IfModemCalls.name: ip2IfModemCalls
ip2IfModemCalls.description: This MIB object shows whether Modem Calls are enabled via the bundle. relay option (3) means that the bundle will send to the network only modulated data.

ip2IfMinPulseWidth.name: ip2IfMinPulseWidth
ip2IfMinPulseWidth.description: Indicates the minimum width in milliseconds of the MF (Multi Frequency) tone transmitted by the switch. Valid values: 45-300 msec. notApplicable=0.

ip2IfMinPowerLevel.name: ip2IfMinPowerLevel
ip2IfMinPowerLevel.description: Indicates the minimum power level in dBm of the MF (Multi Frequency) tone transmitted by the switch. Valid values: -1...-35 dBm.

ip2IfCodingLaw.name: ip2IfCodingLaw
ip2IfCodingLaw.description: This attribute indicates the Method/Law for decoding/encoding the voice information. aLaw(1) is the standard Law for E1 links. uLaw(2) is the standard Law for T1 links.

ip2IfCustomToneDetect.name: ip2IfCustomToneDetect
ip2IfCustomToneDetect.description: Custom Tone Detection (COT) is a Control operation of a 2Khz tone detector. This tone is sent between PBX devices in order to check that the line status is OK. When the COT is enabled the device will not compress/decompress the tone. In this case, if the tone is initiated by the local PBX, the Device runs a 2Khz detector tone and once detected by the Remote Device, if the COT is enabled in the Remote Device, the Remote Device will generate a 2khz tone to the remote PBX.

ip2IfCallerIdDelay.name: ip2IfCallerIdDelay
ip2IfCallerIdDelay.description: Time in msec between CLID (Caller ID) signal detection on the line and CLID signal transmission. The CLID must be sent between ringing signals and the value of the delay is used for synchronizing the CLID transmission with the ringing signals transmission. Valid values: 0 - 3000 msec.

ip2IfConnectivityMode.name: ip2IfConnectivityMode
ip2IfConnectivityMode.description: This MIB object shows whether to send Pings or OAM frames over the bundle.

ip2IfClockSourceEnable.name: ip2IfClockSourceEnable
ip2IfClockSourceEnable.description: This MIB object defines whether this bundle can be a clock source.

ip2IfNetworkType.name: ip2IfNetworkType
ip2IfNetworkType.description: This MIB object defines the network over which the Bundle PSN (Packet Switching Network)is transported. In Gmux2000: ipComprHeader indicates proprietary compressed IP header packets. mplsComprHeader indicates proprietary compressed MPLS header packets.

ip2IfMplsRxLabelEnable.name: ip2IfMplsRxLabelEnable
ip2IfMplsRxLabelEnable.description: This MIB object defines whether there is user defined inner (Rx.) label for this Bundle.

ip2IfMplsRxLabel.name: ip2IfMplsRxLabel
ip2IfMplsRxLabel.description: This MIB object defines the MPLS Rx. Label for this Bundle.

ip2IfMplsTxLabelEnable.name: ip2IfMplsTxLabelEnable
ip2IfMplsTxLabelEnable.description: This MIB object defines whether there is user defined outer (Tx.) label for this Bundle.

ip2IfMplsTxLabel.name: ip2IfMplsTxLabel
ip2IfMplsTxLabel.description: This MIB object defines the MPLS Tx. Label for this Bundle.

ip2IfMplsTxExpBits.name: ip2IfMplsTxExpBits
ip2IfMplsTxExpBits.description: The MPLS Network priority (EXP bits) used for this bundle.

ip2IfMfcSpoofing.name: ip2IfMfcSpoofing
ip2IfMfcSpoofing.description: This MIB object defines whether the MFC (Multi Frequency Compelled) protocol spoofing will exist in the bundle. When the MFC Spoofing is used, the Local and Remote PBXs will send MFC Signaling to each other. The Vmuxes between the PBXs will send proprietary signaling to each other. They will however create and send MFC tones to their local PBX. The PBXs will not know that the actual signaling was not sent from a PBX but from a Vmux.

ip2IfToneAckInterval.name: ip2IfToneAckInterval
ip2IfToneAckInterval.description: Time Interval in milli seconds from the time a Vmux sends tone/s to a local PBX until it receives an acknowledgement from this PBX. Valid values: 60...400 in steps of 20.

ip2IfNextHopType.name: ip2IfNextHopType
ip2IfNextHopType.description: This MIB object defines the Bundle next Hop Address Type.

ip2IfNoiseLevelForVAD.name: ip2IfNoiseLevelForVAD
ip2IfNoiseLevelForVAD.description: This object defines the Level of Noise on the line, the Voice Activation Detector (VAD) will have to handle.

ip2IfClockPreferences.name: ip2IfClockPreferences
ip2IfClockPreferences.description: The Clock preferences: accurateness (2) = Accurate clock is more important than Constant Delay. constantDelay (3)= Constant Delay is more important than Accurate clock .

ip2IfConnectionMode.name: ip2IfConnectionMode
ip2IfConnectionMode.description: The Connection Mode: tdmOIpCe (2) = TDMOiP (CE) = Circuit Emulation. tdmOIpCv (3)= TDMOiP (CV) = Compressed Voice.

ip2IfReversePolarity.name: ip2IfReversePolarity
ip2IfReversePolarity.description: Enables or disable Reverse polarity synthesis.

ip2IfPulseMeter.name: ip2IfPulseMeter
ip2IfPulseMeter.description: Enables or disable Pulse metering synthesis.

ip2IfPulseMeterFreq.name: ip2IfPulseMeterFreq
ip2IfPulseMeterFreq.description: Frequency of synthesized pulse metering for this bundle.

ip2IfPulseMeterPeriod.name: ip2IfPulseMeterPeriod
ip2IfPulseMeterPeriod.description: Duration of synthesized pulse metering. current values are: 100-250.

ip2IfOnHookDetect.name: ip2IfOnHookDetect
ip2IfOnHookDetect.description: Enables or disable immediate reaction to On-Hook bits from network in Ringing.

ip2IfComfortNoiseGen.name: ip2IfComfortNoiseGen
ip2IfComfortNoiseGen.description: Enable or disable Comfort Noise Generation (CNG). When this parameter is enabled and no voice payload exists on the line for some time period during the call (moments of silence), the device will generate a soft background noise which assures the user that the connection is still alive (CNG). When this parameter is disabled and no voice payload exists on the line, absolute silence will be heard (Comfort Noise will not be generated).

ip2IfExitChannel.name: ip2IfExitChannel
ip2IfExitChannel.description: The channelized bundle that the voice bundle exits through. In Gmux2000 it is the ifIndex of the Channelized Bundle (sub-channel) that the Voice Bundle exits through. The ifIndex contains the Slot+Prt+Channelized Bundle No.

ip2IfMaxVBDModemCalls.name: ip2IfMaxVBDModemCalls
ip2IfMaxVBDModemCalls.description: Maximum VBD modem calls for this bundle.

ip2IfMaxRelayModemCalls.name: ip2IfMaxRelayModemCalls
ip2IfMaxRelayModemCalls.description: Maximum Relay modem calls for this bundle.

ip2IfCustomToneFrequency.name: ip2IfCustomToneFrequency
ip2IfCustomToneFrequency.description: This is the frequency of the Custom Tone that is sent between PBXs in order to check that the line status is OK. When the Custom Tone Detection is enabled the device will not compress/decompress this tone. The custom tone that is received from the local PBX will be sent to the remote PBX with the same frequency it was received. When the Custom Tone Frequency is f1780Plus2000Hz (4), the device will not compress/decompress any tone with frequencies of 1780Hz or 2000 Hz.

ip2IfVadMethod.name: ip2IfVadMethod
ip2IfVadMethod.description: Voice Activity Detection (VAD) method. proprietary (2) - non standard VAD based only on power measurement. It is very sensitive to background noise. internalITUT (3) - standard ITU-T VAD. It is a robust method.

ip2IfCallerIDType.name: ip2IfCallerIDType
ip2IfCallerIDType.description: Caller ID Type used by the DSP for this bundle. Bellcore type is used by the American method. V.23 type is used by the European method.

ip2IfPeerAddrType.name: ip2IfPeerAddrType
ip2IfPeerAddrType.description: This MIB object defines the peer Address Type.

ip2IfVbdRate.name: ip2IfVbdRate
ip2IfVbdRate.description: Voice Band Data (VBD) rate for this bundle.

ip2IfDtmfDetection.name: ip2IfDtmfDetection
ip2IfDtmfDetection.description: Enable/Disable DTMF (Dual Tone Multi Frequency) detectors for this bundle.

ip2IfNlpCutoffLevel.name: ip2IfNlpCutoffLevel
ip2IfNlpCutoffLevel.description: Non Linear Processor (NLP) Cutoff Level for this bundle. This parameter is used by the echo canceller. It is the maximum absolute linear PCM amplitude of the near-end signal that will cause the NLP module to be active and to mute low level residual echo & noisy surroundings.

ip2IfDtdErlRatioCutoffQ3.name: ip2IfDtdErlRatioCutoffQ3
ip2IfDtdErlRatioCutoffQ3.description: The DTD ERL cutoff level is used in order to determine whether the near-end is talking or not. This parameter is used by the echo canceller when echo exists and there is voice with low volume on the line. DTD means Double Talk Detection. ERL means Echo Return Loss.
