alrGenSeverity.description: This object enables the user to select a severity for each alarm. The severity is set per alarm code (same for all slots/ports using this code).

alrGenDebounce.name: alrGenDebounce
alrGenDebounce.description: Debounce time for each alarm code, in seconds. The meaning is, that an alarm will be 'declared' as ON (or OFF), only after it was actually ON/OFF the Debouncing time selected by user. 0 = default debounce selection (each alarm has a default value). 250 = maximum value of seconds for debounce. 253 = mask = the alarm will Never be reported. 254 = default debounce selection (each alarm has a default value). 255 = not applicable

alrGenDefSeverity.name: alrGenDefSeverity
alrGenDefSeverity.description: This object reports the default severity of each alarm. User can change the severity of the alarms defined by this default via the alrGenSeverity object.

sanityCheckTrap.name: sanityCheckTrap
sanityCheckTrap.description: This trap is sent after a data base download attempt. It returns the sanity result status and the configuration no.checked.

dacsMuxAlarmsTrap.name: dacsMuxAlarmsTrap
dacsMuxAlarmsTrap.description: This trap is sent when an alarm occurs.

mdlConnectTrap.name: mdlConnectTrap
mdlConnectTrap.description: This trap is sent when a card is removed.

sysAlrStatusTrap.name: sysAlrStatusTrap
sysAlrStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change in the value of any of the variables.

sysStatusChangedTrap.name: sysStatusChangedTrap
sysStatusChangedTrap.description: This trap is sent when Leds status is changed.

cnfgUpdateTrap.name: cnfgUpdateTrap
cnfgUpdateTrap.description: This trap is sent upon change of the active Configuration DB.

sysRedundancyStatusTrap.name: sysRedundancyStatusTrap
sysRedundancyStatusTrap.description: The trap is sent upon change in Redundancy Status.

sysRedundancyActiveCardTrap.name: sysRedundancyActiveCardTrap
sysRedundancyActiveCardTrap.description: The trap is sent upon change of Active Main/CL Card.

sysRedundancyActivePortTrap.name: sysRedundancyActivePortTrap
sysRedundancyActivePortTrap.description: The trap is sent upon change of Active Port of Redundancy Group.

wfqTable.name: wfqTable
wfqTable.description: This table allows user to define several WFQ tables per output port. WFQ supports flows with different bandwidth requirements by giving each queue a weight that assigns it a different percentage of output port bandwidth. When Weighted Fair Queuing is used, it is possible to precisely attribute bandwidth partitioning among the queues. When there is congestion, each class (queue) is not allowed to use more bandwidth than the amount allocated to it.

wfqEntry.name: wfqEntry
wfqEntry.description: An entry in the Weighted Fair Queueing table.

wfqCnfgIdx.name: wfqCnfgIdx
wfqCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Agent Cnfg the following objects refer. 255=Temporary Cnfg (when relevant, Set is done only to this configuration). For Agents that support only one configuration, this object will be constant=1.

wfqPrtIdx.name: wfqPrtIdx
wfqPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique port or interface number, for which Weighted Fair Queueing table is applicable . For numbering, see product's spec. For some products, the numbering can equal ifIndex. Value of 255 (not applicable) refer to system level queue

wfqTblIdx.name: wfqTblIdx
wfqTblIdx.description: This object indicates which Weighted Fair Queueing (WFQ) Table is being used. There can be several tables. For FCD-155 User will select which one will be used for a virtual concatenation group.Valid values are 1,2

wfqQueueIdx.name: wfqQueueIdx
wfqQueueIdx.description: This object indicates a queue index. For FCD-155, valid queues are 1..3. The 4th queue is not in MIB. Its weight will be RO, Calculated according to the sum of the 3 first queues.

wfqRowStatus.name: wfqRowStatus
wfqRowStatus.description: This object enables Creation/Deletion of rows in the WFQ table. For FCD-155, rows are not created nor destroyed by user.

wfqWeightValue.name: wfqWeightValue
wfqWeightValue.description: This object indicates a relative weight value. User should make sure that the sum of values for all queues will not exceed 100% (sum should be BELOW 100% in order to leave some BW percentage for last queue) Note that when this attribute is being used, the wfqMinRateAbsolute attribute is NA.

wfqSchedulingMode.name: wfqSchedulingMode
wfqSchedulingMode.description: This object controls which scheduling mode is used: Weighted Fair Queuing (WFQ) scheme or priority Queue (Strict Priority).

wfqMinRateAbsolute.name: wfqMinRateAbsolute
wfqMinRateAbsolute.description: The minimum absolute rate, in kbps, that should be allocated to this queue. If the value is zero, then there is effectively no minimum rate guarantee. If the value is non-zero, then the servicing of this queue in at least this rate is assured. Note that when this attribute is being used, the wfqWeightValue attribute is NA.

wfqMaxPacketSize.name: wfqMaxPacketSize
wfqMaxPacketSize.description: The size of the largest packet which can be received on this queue, specified in octets. Packets larger than this size will be discarded.

Dscp.name: Dscp
Dscp.description: A Differentiated Services Code-Point that may be used for marking a traffic stream.

dscpMappingTable.name: dscpMappingTable
dscpMappingTable.description: Mapping of DSCP value to a regenerated priority level.

dscpMappingCnfgIdx.name: dscpMappingCnfgIdx
dscpMappingCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Agent Cnfg the following objects refer to. 255=Temporary Cnfg (when relevant, Set is done only to this configuration). For Agents that support only one configuration, this object will be constant=1. This object can be used to carry additional indexing (e.g port index) when needed.

dscpMappingDscpIdx.name: dscpMappingDscpIdx
dscpMappingDscpIdx.description: DSCP value of the incoming IP packet

dscpMappingRegenPriority.name: dscpMappingRegenPriority
dscpMappingRegenPriority.description: The Regenerated Priority level the incoming DSCP value is mapped to. For FCD-155, valid values are 0,1,2,3

ifTeQosEntry.name: ifTeQosEntry
ifTeQosEntry.description: An entry in the TE QOS Interface table.

ifTeQosIdx1.name: ifTeQosIdx1
ifTeQosIdx1.description: This object indicates the 1st Index of the table.

ifTeQosIdx2.name: ifTeQosIdx2
ifTeQosIdx2.description: This object indicates the 2nd Index of the table.

ifTeQosIdx3.name: ifTeQosIdx3
ifTeQosIdx3.description: This object indicates the 3rd Index of the table.

ifTeQosParam.name: ifTeQosParam
ifTeQosParam.description: This object is used for QOS attributes of the entry's entities.

ifTeQosParam2.name: ifTeQosParam2
ifTeQosParam2.description: This object is used for 2nd group QOS attributes of the entry's entities.

ifTeQosStatus.name: ifTeQosStatus
ifTeQosStatus.description: This object is used to create, activate and destroy entries of this table.

prtPriorityTable.name: prtPriorityTable
prtPriorityTable.description: A table - Parameters per port per Priority .

prtPriorityIdx1.name: prtPriorityIdx1
prtPriorityIdx1.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. or any other Index.

prtPriorityPrtIdx.name: prtPriorityPrtIdx
prtPriorityPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Port Index. Refer to device specification for port Index.

prtPriorityIdx.name: prtPriorityIdx
prtPriorityIdx.description: This object indicates the Traffic Priority Index.

prtPriorityIngressRateLimit.name: prtPriorityIngressRateLimit
prtPriorityIngressRateLimit.description: The maximum rate permitted at Ingress of this port with this Traffic Priority, in Kbps.

prtQosIdx.name: prtQosIdx
prtQosIdx.description: The first index of the table. This attribute might indicate the Idx of the Cnfg (1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg or any other Index.

prtQosPrtIdx.name: prtQosPrtIdx
prtQosPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Port Index. Refer to device specification for port Index.

prtQosDirection.name: prtQosDirection
prtQosDirection.description: This object indicates the port's QoS Direction.

prtQosRateLimitPacketType.name: prtQosRateLimitPacketType
prtQosRateLimitPacketType.description: This object indicates the Type of Packets on which Rate Limitation is applied.

prtQosRateLimitCIR.name: prtQosRateLimitCIR
prtQosRateLimitCIR.description: This object indicates the port's CIR (Committed Information Rate) in Kbps. Value=0 represents best effort.

prtQosRateLimitCBS.name: prtQosRateLimitCBS
prtQosRateLimitCBS.description: This object indicates the port's CBS (Committed Burst Size) in KB. Value=0 represents best effort.

prtQosRateLimitEIR.name: prtQosRateLimitEIR
prtQosRateLimitEIR.description: This object indicates the port's EIR (Excess Information Rate) in Kbps.

prtQosRateLimitEBS.name: prtQosRateLimitEBS
prtQosRateLimitEBS.description: This object indicates the port's EBS (Excess Burst Size) in KB.

portTrafficClassTable.name: portTrafficClassTable
portTrafficClassTable.description: Mapping of port to Traffic Class level.

portTrafficClassIdx1.name: portTrafficClassIdx1
portTrafficClassIdx1.description: This attribute indicates the 1st index of the table. This may be the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg, or any other Index.

portTrafficClassPortIdx.name: portTrafficClassPortIdx
portTrafficClassPortIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Port Index. Refer to device specification for port Index.

portTrafficClass.name: portTrafficClass
portTrafficClass.description: This object indicates the Traffic Class level of this port.

serviceEntry.name: serviceEntry
serviceEntry.description: An entry in the Service Table.

flowIndex.name: flowIndex
flowIndex.description: Defines the Flow ID the service is associated to.

serviceIndex.name: serviceIndex
serviceIndex.description: Defines the Service ID - according to the CoS.

serviceRowStatus.name: serviceRowStatus
serviceRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

serviceName.name: serviceName
serviceName.description: This attribute defines the service name.

serviceBwProfileId.name: serviceBwProfileId
serviceBwProfileId.description: This variable holds the index of the Ingress BW profile assigned to that service.

evcCosTable.name: evcCosTable
evcCosTable.description: This table defines mapping of Ethernet Virtual Connection (EVC) ID to Class of Service (CoS) ID

evcCosCnfgIdx.name: evcCosCnfgIdx
evcCosCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

evcCosRowStatus.name: evcCosRowStatus
evcCosRowStatus.description: This attribute allows to create/delete a row in this table.

evcCosEvcName.name: evcCosEvcName
evcCosEvcName.description: A string that identifies the EVC. It should be unique in the Maintenance Domain (i.e., in the managed network) Used as MEG ID field in OAM messages.

evcCosSpVlanId.name: evcCosSpVlanId
evcCosSpVlanId.description: This object indicates the SP (Service Provider) VLAN used when sending an OAM message for the specified EVC.

serviceStatEntry.name: serviceStatEntry
serviceStatEntry.description: An entry in the Service Statistics Table.

serviceStatDirection.name: serviceStatDirection
serviceStatDirection.description: The direction in wich the measurement is taken.

srvForwardGreenPackets.name: srvForwardGreenPackets
srvForwardGreenPackets.description: This attribute displays the counted number of forwarded packets that where marked Green.

srvForwardGreenPacktesOverflow.name: srvForwardGreenPacktesOverflow
srvForwardGreenPacktesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the forwardGreenPackets counter has overflowed.

srvForwardYellowPackets.name: srvForwardYellowPackets
srvForwardYellowPackets.description: This attribute displays the counted number of forwarded packets that where marked Yellow.

srvForwardYellowPacketsOverflow.name: srvForwardYellowPacketsOverflow
srvForwardYellowPacketsOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the forwardYellowPackets counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardGreenPacket.name: srvDiscardGreenPacket
srvDiscardGreenPacket.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded packets that where marked Green.

srvDiscardGreenPacketOverflow.name: srvDiscardGreenPacketOverflow
srvDiscardGreenPacketOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardGreenPacket counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardYellowRedPackets.name: srvDiscardYellowRedPackets
srvDiscardYellowRedPackets.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded packets that where marked Yellow or Red.

srvDiscardYellowRedPacketsOverflow.name: srvDiscardYellowRedPacketsOverflow
srvDiscardYellowRedPacketsOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardYellowRedPackets counter has overflowed.

srvForwardGreenBytes.name: srvForwardGreenBytes
srvForwardGreenBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of forwarded bytes that where marked Green.

srvForwardGreenBytesOverflow.name: srvForwardGreenBytesOverflow
srvForwardGreenBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the forwardGreenBytes counter has overflowed.

srvForwardYellowBytes.name: srvForwardYellowBytes
srvForwardYellowBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of forwarded bytes that where marked Yellow.

srvForwardYellowBytesOverflow.name: srvForwardYellowBytesOverflow
srvForwardYellowBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the forwardYellowBytes counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardGreenBytes.name: srvDiscardGreenBytes
srvDiscardGreenBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded bytes that where marked Green.

srvDiscardGreenBytesOverflow.name: srvDiscardGreenBytesOverflow
srvDiscardGreenBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardGreenBytes counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardYellowRedBytes.name: srvDiscardYellowRedBytes
srvDiscardYellowRedBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded bytes that where marked Yellow or Red.

srvDiscardYellowRedBytesOverflow.name: srvDiscardYellowRedBytesOverflow
srvDiscardYellowRedBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardYellowRedBytes counter has overflowed.

srvResetStatsCmd.name: srvResetStatsCmd
srvResetStatsCmd.description: Reset statistic counters of the service.

srvDiscardYellowPackets.name: srvDiscardYellowPackets
srvDiscardYellowPackets.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded packets that where marked Yellow.

srvDiscardYellowPacketsOverflow.name: srvDiscardYellowPacketsOverflow
srvDiscardYellowPacketsOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardYellowPackets counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardYellowBytes.name: srvDiscardYellowBytes
srvDiscardYellowBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded bytes that where marked Yellow.

srvDiscardYellowBytesOverflow.name: srvDiscardYellowBytesOverflow
srvDiscardYellowBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardYellowBytes counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardRedPackets.name: srvDiscardRedPackets
srvDiscardRedPackets.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded packets that where marked Red.

srvDiscardRedPacketsOverflow.name: srvDiscardRedPacketsOverflow
srvDiscardRedPacketsOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardRedPackets counter has overflowed.

srvDiscardRedBytes.name: srvDiscardRedBytes
srvDiscardRedBytes.description: This attribute displays the counted number of discarded bytes that where marked Red.

srvDiscardRedBytesOverflow.name: srvDiscardRedBytesOverflow
srvDiscardRedBytesOverflow.description: This attribute displays the number of times that the discardRedBytes counter has overflowed.

flowMappingProfileTable.name: flowMappingProfileTable
flowMappingProfileTable.description: This table holds flow mapping profiles.

flowMappingProfileEntry.name: flowMappingProfileEntry
flowMappingProfileEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one Flow mapping profile with one of its Flow Mapping supported, according to the Priority order. The information includes a reference to a Flow Mapping index.

flowMappingProfileIndex.name: flowMappingProfileIndex
flowMappingProfileIndex.description: A running index for the Flow Mapping Profile table.

flowMappingProfilePriority.name: flowMappingProfilePriority
flowMappingProfilePriority.description: The priority of the Mapping selected by flowMappingProfileMapIndex within the Flow Mapping Profile.

flowMappingProfileRowStatus.name: flowMappingProfileRowStatus
flowMappingProfileRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

flowMappingProfileNumOfMaps.name: flowMappingProfileNumOfMaps
flowMappingProfileNumOfMaps.description: This attribute determines the number of the mappings associated to the Flow Mapping Profile.

flowMappingProfileMapIndex.name: flowMappingProfileMapIndex
flowMappingProfileMapIndex.description: This attribute holds a reference to the mapping index. It specifies the mapping selected for the Mapping Profile for the selected Priority. When flowMappingProfileNumOfMaps=0, this attribute is not relevant.

flowMappingProfileName.name: flowMappingProfileName
flowMappingProfileName.description: This attribute defines the name assigned to flowMappingIndex profile.

qosFlowMappingEntry.name: qosFlowMappingEntry
qosFlowMappingEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one Flow Mapping. The information includes combination (AND function) of all the classifications, as defined in the qosFlowMappingCriteria field. Classifiers are: TOS, DSCP, VLAN ID, MAC and IP source and destination addresses, IP protocol, IP Precedence, TCP and UDP source and destination ports.

qosFlowMappingIdx1.name: qosFlowMappingIdx1
qosFlowMappingIdx1.description: - In case the table is accessed via flowMappingProfileTable this is a running index for the QoS Flow Mapping table. - In case the table is not accessed via flowMappingProfileTable, this will be the ifIndex of the XNI (bridge port) to which the QoS mapping applies.

qosFlowMappingIdx2.name: qosFlowMappingIdx2
qosFlowMappingIdx2.description: An index for the QoS Flow Mapping table. - In case the table is accessed via flowMappingProfileTable the index will be fixed = 1. - In case the table is not accessed via flowMappingProfileTable, this will be the index of the Flow (EVC) to which the QoS mapping applies.

qosFlowMappingIdx3.name: qosFlowMappingIdx3
qosFlowMappingIdx3.description: An index for the QoS Flow Mapping table. - In case the table is accessed via flowMappingProfileTable the index will be fixed = 1. - In case the table is not accessed via flowMappingProfileTable, this will be the Priority to which the QoS mapping applies.

qosFlowMappingRowStatus.name: qosFlowMappingRowStatus
qosFlowMappingRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

qosFlowMappingCriteria.name: qosFlowMappingCriteria
qosFlowMappingCriteria.description: This attribute determines upon which criterion the flow will be mapped.

qosFlowMappingIeee802dot1p.name: qosFlowMappingIeee802dot1p
qosFlowMappingIeee802dot1p.description: This attribute determines which TOS values are applicable for that flow. Each bit (0..7) represents a different 802.1 P-bit value. Setting '1' to the bit means that the corresponding 802.1 P-bit value is applicable. It is relevant only in case the ieee802dot1p bit(0) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingTos.name: qosFlowMappingTos
qosFlowMappingTos.description: This attribute determines which TOS values are applicable for that flow. Each bit (0..7) represents a different TOS value. Setting '1' to the bit means that the corresponding TOS value is applicable. It is relevant only in case the tos bit (1) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromDscp.name: qosFlowMappingFromDscp
qosFlowMappingFromDscp.description: This attribute determines the first DSCP value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the dscp bit (2) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToDscp.name: qosFlowMappingToDscp
qosFlowMappingToDscp.description: This attribute determines the first DSCP value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the dscp bit (2) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromVlanId.name: qosFlowMappingFromVlanId
qosFlowMappingFromVlanId.description: This attribute determines the first VLAN ID value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the vlanId bit (3) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToVlanId.name: qosFlowMappingToVlanId
qosFlowMappingToVlanId.description: This attribute determines the last VLAN ID value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the vlanId bit (3) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromSrcMacAddr.name: qosFlowMappingFromSrcMacAddr
qosFlowMappingFromSrcMacAddr.description: This attribute determines the first source MAC address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the macSrcAddr bit (4) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToSrcMacAddr.name: qosFlowMappingToSrcMacAddr
qosFlowMappingToSrcMacAddr.description: This attribute determines the last source MAC address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the macSrcAddr bit (4) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromDestMacAddr.name: qosFlowMappingFromDestMacAddr
qosFlowMappingFromDestMacAddr.description: This attribute determines the first destination MAC address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the macDestAddr (5) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToDestMacAddr.name: qosFlowMappingToDestMacAddr
qosFlowMappingToDestMacAddr.description: This attribute determines the last destination MAC address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the macDestAddr (5) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromSrcIpAddr.name: qosFlowMappingFromSrcIpAddr
qosFlowMappingFromSrcIpAddr.description: This attribute determines the first source IP address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the ipSrcAddr (6) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToSrcIpAddr.name: qosFlowMappingToSrcIpAddr
qosFlowMappingToSrcIpAddr.description: This attribute determines the last source IP address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the ipSrcAddr (6) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromDestIpAddr.name: qosFlowMappingFromDestIpAddr
qosFlowMappingFromDestIpAddr.description: This attribute determines the first destination IP address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the ipDestAddr (7) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToDestIpAddr.name: qosFlowMappingToDestIpAddr
qosFlowMappingToDestIpAddr.description: This attribute determines the last destination IP address to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the ipDestAddr (7) bit in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromTcpSrcPort.name: qosFlowMappingFromTcpSrcPort
qosFlowMappingFromTcpSrcPort.description: This attribute determines the first TCP source port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the tcpSrcPort bit (8) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToTcpSrcPort.name: qosFlowMappingToTcpSrcPort
qosFlowMappingToTcpSrcPort.description: This attribute determines the last TCP source port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the tcpSrcPort bit (8) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromTcpDestPort.name: qosFlowMappingFromTcpDestPort
qosFlowMappingFromTcpDestPort.description: This attribute determines the first TCP destination port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the tcpDestPort bit (9) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToTcpDestPort.name: qosFlowMappingToTcpDestPort
qosFlowMappingToTcpDestPort.description: This attribute determines the last TCP destination port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the tcpDestPort bit (9) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromUdpSrcPort.name: qosFlowMappingFromUdpSrcPort
qosFlowMappingFromUdpSrcPort.description: This attribute determines the first UDP source port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the udpSrcPort bit (10) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToUdpSrcPort.name: qosFlowMappingToUdpSrcPort
qosFlowMappingToUdpSrcPort.description: This attribute determines the last UDP source port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the udpSrcPort bit (10) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromUdpDestPort.name: qosFlowMappingFromUdpDestPort
qosFlowMappingFromUdpDestPort.description: This attribute determines the first UDP destination port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the udpDestPort bit (11) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToUdpDestPort.name: qosFlowMappingToUdpDestPort
qosFlowMappingToUdpDestPort.description: This attribute determines the last UDP destination port to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the udpDestPort bit (11) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromIpPrecedence.name: qosFlowMappingFromIpPrecedence
qosFlowMappingFromIpPrecedence.description: This attribute determines the first IpPrecedence value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the IpPrecedence bit (12) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToIpPrecedence.name: qosFlowMappingToIpPrecedence
qosFlowMappingToIpPrecedence.description: This attribute determines the last IpPrecedence value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the IpPrecedence bit (12) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingInnerIeee802dot1p.name: qosFlowMappingInnerIeee802dot1p
qosFlowMappingInnerIeee802dot1p.description: This attribute determines which TOS values are applicable for that flow. Each bit (0..7) represents a different inner 802.1 P-bit value. Setting '1' to the bit means that the corresponding inner 802.1 P-bit value is applicable. It is relevant only in case the innerIeee802dot1p bit (13) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingFromInnerVlanId.name: qosFlowMappingFromInnerVlanId
qosFlowMappingFromInnerVlanId.description: This attribute determines the first inner VLAN ID value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the innerVlanId bit(14) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

qosFlowMappingToInnerVlanId.name: qosFlowMappingToInnerVlanId
qosFlowMappingToInnerVlanId.description: This attribute determines the last inner VLAN ID value to compare with in a range. It is relevant only in case the innerVlanId bit(14) in qosFlowMappingCriteria equals 1.

cosProfileTable.name: cosProfileTable
cosProfileTable.description: Class of Service Profile table. Each profile holds a priority method, and a mappring function that maps the priority values (range according to the method) into CoS values.

cosProfileEntry.name: cosProfileEntry
cosProfileEntry.description: A conceptual row where each row contains one CoS attributes.

cosProfileRowStatus.name: cosProfileRowStatus
cosProfileRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

cosProfileCosMethod.name: cosProfileCosMethod
cosProfileCosMethod.description: Defines the priority method upon CoS mapping is done.

cosProfileName.name: cosProfileName
cosProfileName.description: This attribute defines the name assigned to CoS profile.

cosProfileCosMapping.name: cosProfileCosMapping
cosProfileCosMapping.description: This attribute defines the value of the CoS that is assigned for each priority. The number of the valid octets depends upon the priority method selected: Octet 0 corresponds to priority = 0 Octet 1 corresponds to priority = 1 ... Octet 63 corresponds to priority = 63.

qProfileTable.name: qProfileTable
qProfileTable.description: This table defines the profiles for a cluster of queues.

qProfileEntry.name: qProfileEntry
qProfileEntry.description: A conceptual row where each row contains one Queue Cluster attribute.

qProfileIndex.name: qProfileIndex
qProfileIndex.description: Defines the Queue Cluster Profile ID.

qProfileRowStatus.name: qProfileRowStatus
qProfileRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

qProfileName.name: qProfileName
qProfileName.description: This attribute holds the name of the Queue cluster profile.

qProfileNumberOfInternalQ.name: qProfileNumberOfInternalQ
qProfileNumberOfInternalQ.description: This attribute holds the number of the internal queue profiles that are pointed by qInternalQProfile.

qProfileInternalQProfile.name: qProfileInternalQProfile
qProfileInternalQProfile.description: This attribute holds the indexes to the queue profiles in the qInternalProfileTable. Each couple of octets holds an index to the qInternalProfileTable.

qInternalProfileEntry.name: qInternalProfileEntry
qInternalProfileEntry.description: A conceptual row where each row contains one Queue attribute.

qInternalProfileRowStatus.name: qInternalProfileRowStatus
qInternalProfileRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

qInternalProfileScheduling.name: qInternalProfileScheduling
qInternalProfileScheduling.description: This attribute determines the queue scheduling method.

qInternalProfileWFQWeight.name: qInternalProfileWFQWeight
qInternalProfileWFQWeight.description: This attribute determines the weight that each WFQ (Weighted Fair Queue) participant gets. It is applicable only when scheduling is configured to WFQ.

qInternalProfileQueueLength.name: qInternalProfileQueueLength
qInternalProfileQueueLength.description: This attribute determines the length of the queue.

qInternalProfileWredStartDropThresh.name: qInternalProfileWredStartDropThresh
qInternalProfileWredStartDropThresh.description: This attribute determines the length that the queue (Start Value) must reach before the packets colored yellow will start being dropped by the WRED (Weighted Random Early Detection/Discard) mechanism. WRED is one the most commonly used method for congestion avoidance.

qInternalProfileWredDropAllThresh.name: qInternalProfileWredDropAllThresh
qInternalProfileWredDropAllThresh.description: This attribute determines the length that the queue (Stop Value) must reach before the WRED (Weighted Random Early Detection) shaper mechanism stops dropping randomly, and just drops all further packets marked as yellow.

qInternalProfileWredDropProbability.name: qInternalProfileWredDropProbability
qInternalProfileWredDropProbability.description: This attribute determines the percentage of packets that are being dropped at the point when the length of the queue reaches the Stop value. So, effectively, this defines how quickly the rate of dropping packet must increase as the queue length grows from the Start Value to the Stop Value.

qInternalProfileRateLimit.name: qInternalProfileRateLimit
qInternalProfileRateLimit.description: This attribute determines the Rate Limit of the queue in Kbps. Value=0 represents best effort.

qInternalProfileShaperProfile.name: qInternalProfileShaperProfile
qInternalProfileShaperProfile.description: This attribute defines the Shaper Profile (bwProfileIndex from bwProfileTable) assigned to this qInternalProfile. Valid range of bwProfileIndex for Shaper Profiles is 0x8000001-0x8000041. If set to '0', no profile is assigned to this qInternalProfile.

queueGroupTable.name: queueGroupTable
queueGroupTable.description: This table defines the queue groups/blocks,their level and connections between them.

queueGroupEntry.name: queueGroupEntry
queueGroupEntry.description: A conceptual row where each row contains one Queue group.

queueGroupName.name: queueGroupName
queueGroupName.description: Defines the Queue Group unique name.

queueGroupQBlockLevel.name: queueGroupQBlockLevel
queueGroupQBlockLevel.description: This attribute holds the Level of the Queue Block .First level is 1. NA=2^32-1.

queueGroupQBlockIdx.name: queueGroupQBlockIdx
queueGroupQBlockIdx.description: This attribute holds the ID of the Queue Block. NA=2^32-1.

queueGroupRowStatus.name: queueGroupRowStatus
queueGroupRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

queueGroupQBlockProfile.name: queueGroupQBlockProfile
queueGroupQBlockProfile.description: This attribute defines the Queue profile assigned to this Queue Block. This object points to qProfileIndex in qProfileTable.

queueGroupQBlockShaperProfile.name: queueGroupQBlockShaperProfile
queueGroupQBlockShaperProfile.description: This attribute defines the Shaper profile assigned to this Queue Block.

queueGroupPointToQBlock.name: queueGroupPointToQBlock
queueGroupPointToQBlock.description: This attribute defines the Queue Block name of the next Queue Block level that is pointed by this Queue Block.

queueGroupPointToInternalQueue.name: queueGroupPointToInternalQueue
queueGroupPointToInternalQueue.description: This attribute defines the internal queue whithin queueGroupPointToQBlock that is pointed by this Queue Block.

queueGroupQBlockName.name: queueGroupQBlockName
queueGroupQBlockName.description: This attribute holds the name of the Queue Block.

markingProfileTable.name: markingProfileTable
markingProfileTable.description: Marking profile table. Each profile holds a marking function which converts CoS values to Service Provider priority values.

markingProfileEntry.name: markingProfileEntry
markingProfileEntry.description: A conceptual row where each row contains one Marking attribute.

markingProfileRowStatus.name: markingProfileRowStatus
markingProfileRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

markingProfileName.name: markingProfileName
markingProfileName.description: This attribute defines the unique name assigned to the Marking profile.

markingSpVlanPBit.name: markingSpVlanPBit
markingSpVlanPBit.description: For ETX-202A : This attribute defines the value of the SP VLAN P-Bit that is assigned for each CoS: Octet 0 corresponds to CoS = 0 Octet 1 corresponds to CoS = 1 ... Octet 7 corresponds to CoS = 7. For LA-210 from V1.5 : This attribute defines the value of the SP VLAN P-Bit that is assigned for each frame according to the value of markingProfileMethod parameter : Octet 0 corresponds to value 0 of 802.1 P-bit/DSCP/TOS. Octet 1 corresponds to value 1 of 802.1 P-bit/DSCP/TOS. ... Octet 7 corresponds to value 7 of 802.1 P-bit/DSCP/TOS. Octets 8-63 correspond to DSCP values 8-63.

markingProfileMethod.name: markingProfileMethod
markingProfileMethod.description: This attribute defines the method upon which marking is done.

ethIfIdx.name: ethIfIdx
ethIfIdx.description: A unique index of the ethernet interface/port.

ethMode.name: ethMode
ethMode.description: This object indicates the Ethernet mode of operation.

ethBridgingMode.name: ethBridgingMode
ethBridgingMode.description: This object indicates the bridging mode of the Ethernet interface.

ethEncapsulationCRCMode.name: ethEncapsulationCRCMode
ethEncapsulationCRCMode.description: This object define the encapsulation type requested for the Ethernet interface. It indicates if we transfer the Ethernet frame to the other side with or without the CRC.

ethBackPressure.name: ethBackPressure
ethBackPressure.description: This parameter defines whether to enable or disable Back pressure. Back Pressure is a flow control parameter.

ethLimit4.name: ethLimit4
ethLimit4.description: This parameter determine the Back off algorithm mode. Every 4 following collisions the Framer will be thrown out (4 times more than usuall).

ethSkipInitReset.name: ethSkipInitReset
ethSkipInitReset.description: This parameter defines whether read status on reset.

ethMulticastBlock.name: ethMulticastBlock
ethMulticastBlock.description: This parameter defines whether to send multicast message to WAN from LAN or not.

ethBroadcastBlock.name: ethBroadcastBlock
ethBroadcastBlock.description: This parameter defines whether to send broadcast message to WAN from LAN or not.

ethSpeed.name: ethSpeed
ethSpeed.description: This parameter defines the line speed.

ethRip2.name: ethRip2
ethRip2.description: This parameter defines whether to send RIP II message to WAN from LAN or not

ethPortPriority.name: ethPortPriority
ethPortPriority.description: This parameter defines if priority is to be considered for this Port.

ethPortMngEnable.name: ethPortMngEnable
ethPortMngEnable.description: This parameter defines whether management data can pass through this Port. localOnly (4) - Only local device can be managed via this port.

ethFlowCtrlMacAddress.name: ethFlowCtrlMacAddress
ethFlowCtrlMacAddress.description: In case of flow control - transmit frame with this specific MAC address to inform the other end to stop sending frames. Default: 01.80.C2.00.00.01.

ethRateLimit.name: ethRateLimit
ethRateLimit.description: This parameter defines the Rate Limit of the line, in Mbps.

ethJumboFrameEnable.name: ethJumboFrameEnable
ethJumboFrameEnable.description: This parameter defines whether to support Jumbo Frame or not.

ethAutoMdiXEnable.name: ethAutoMdiXEnable
ethAutoMdiXEnable.description: This parameter defines whether to support automatic change between MDI and MDI[X].

ethPortDataEnable.name: ethPortDataEnable
ethPortDataEnable.description: This parameter defines whether this port is enabled for data (that is not management). no(2) - management can run on this port yes(3) - both management and payload data can run on this port.

ethIfUse.name: ethIfUse
ethIfUse.description: This parameter defines the use of the port. 1=NET 2=USER .

ethLineOam.name: ethLineOam
ethLineOam.description: This parameter defines the working mode of 802.AH OAM mechanism.

ethRoutingProtocol.name: ethRoutingProtocol
ethRoutingProtocol.description: This parameter defines the routing protocol used above ETH port.

ethMdiXManualSwitch.name: ethMdiXManualSwitch
ethMdiXManualSwitch.description: This parameter sets the port to be MDI-X (cross-over) or MDI (straight-through). It is applicable only when ethAutoMdiXEnable = no, namely, only when the automatic MDI/MDIX crossover function is disabled.

ethDot1xEnable.name: ethDot1xEnable
ethDot1xEnable.description: Determines if the Port-Based Network Access Protocol (IEEE-802.1x) is enabled for the Ethernet Port.

ethPartnerRateMode.name: ethPartnerRateMode
ethPartnerRateMode.description: For converters having couples of ports, where each couple contains a port with an SFP connector and a port with a RJ connector, this parameter is relevant for the SFP port. It affects Rate configuration of its partner (RJ port). manual - user can configure manually ETH parameters of RJ port (e.g Autonegotiation, Max Capability Advertised, etc...) automatic - SFP Rate will be enforced on the RJ port. In this mode, user cannot configure the Rate related parameters of the RJ port (e.g Autonegotiation, Max Capability Advertised, etc...)

ethDot1xPortRole.name: ethDot1xPortRole
ethDot1xPortRole.description: Determine the functionality of the port in the Port-Based Network Access Protocol (IEEE-802.1x) - either Authenticator or Supplicant.

ethIfCurrentTable.name: ethIfCurrentTable
ethIfCurrentTable.description: The Ethernet Current table. When the index specifies the Ethernet interface (only), the counters are for an interval of 15 minutes.

ethIfCurrentEntry.name: ethIfCurrentEntry
ethIfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Current table.

ethIfCurrentIndex.name: ethIfCurrentIndex
ethIfCurrentIndex.description: The index of the Ethernet interface. It may be ifIndex. For some devices (e.g RICi-622GE), supporting several types of intervals, this index will be a concatenation of the port index and interval type. Interval type can indicate: 1 minute, 15 minutes, 1 hour, 24 hours. For the exact formula, see device specification.

ethIfCurrentStatus.name: ethIfCurrentStatus
ethIfCurrentStatus.description: The status of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

ethIfCurrentInFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInFrames
ethIfCurrentInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInOctets.name: ethIfCurrentInOctets
ethIfCurrentInOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of received octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors.name: ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors
ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, which are not complete (The result of dividing the number of bits by 8 is not an Integer), encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentFCSErrors.name: ethIfCurrentFCSErrors
ethIfCurrentFCSErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames that didn't pass the FCS test, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentLengthError.name: ethIfCurrentLengthError
ethIfCurrentLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutFrames
ethIfCurrentOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutOctets.name: ethIfCurrentOutOctets
ethIfCurrentOutOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames
ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by exactly one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by more than one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions.name: ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions
ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames for which the first transmission attempt was delayed due to a busy media, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentLateCollisions.name: ethIfCurrentLateCollisions
ethIfCurrentLateCollisions.description: The counter associated with the number of times that a collision was detected later than the first 64 bytes of the frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors.name: ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors
ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped
ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of frames dropped due to lack of buffers in ingress pool, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped
ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Transmit direction to the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInOctets.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInOctets
ethIfCurrentOverflowInOctets.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInOctets counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowFCSErrors.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowFCSErrors
ethIfCurrentOverflowFCSErrors.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentFCSErrors counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutOctets.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutOctets
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutOctets.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutOctets counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowMultipleCollisionFra.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowMultipleCollisionFra.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInUnicastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInUnicastFrames
ethIfCurrentInUnicastFrames.description: The number of received Unicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutUnicastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutUnicastFrames
ethIfCurrentOutUnicastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Unicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInMulticastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInMulticastFrames
ethIfCurrentInMulticastFrames.description: The number of received Multicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutMulticastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutMulticastFrames
ethIfCurrentOutMulticastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Multicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInBroadcastFrames
ethIfCurrentInBroadcastFrames.description: The number of received Broadcast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutBroadcastFrames
ethIfCurrentOutBroadcastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Broadcast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInDiscardFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInDiscardFrames
ethIfCurrentInDiscardFrames.description: The number of received Discarded frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutDiscardFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutDiscardFrames
ethIfCurrentOutDiscardFrames.description: The number of transmitted Discarded frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentInPauseFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInPauseFrames
ethIfCurrentInPauseFrames.description: The number of received Pause frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOutPauseFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutPauseFrames
ethIfCurrentOutPauseFrames.description: The number of transmitted Pause frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInUnicastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInUnicastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInUnicastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInUnicastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutUnicastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutUnicastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutUnicastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutUnicastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInMulticastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInMulticastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInMulticastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInMulticastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutMulticastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutMulticastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutMulticastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutMulticastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInBroadcastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInBroadcastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInBroadcastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutBroadcastFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutBroadcastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutBroadcastFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInDiscardFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInDiscardFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInDiscardFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInDiscardFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutDiscardFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutDiscardFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutDiscardFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutDiscardFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowInPauseFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowInPauseFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowInPauseFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentInPauseFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfCurrentOverflowOutPauseFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOverflowOutPauseFrames
ethIfCurrentOverflowOutPauseFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfCurrentOutPauseFrames counter has overflowed in the current interval.

ethIfIntervalTable.name: ethIfIntervalTable
ethIfIntervalTable.description: The Ethernet Interval table. When ethIfIntervalIndex specifies the Ethernet interface (only), the counters are for an interval of 15 minutes.

ethIfIntervalEntry.name: ethIfIntervalEntry
ethIfIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Interval table.

ethIfIntervalIndex.name: ethIfIntervalIndex
ethIfIntervalIndex.description: The index of the Ethernet interface. It may be ifIndex. For some devices (e.g RICi-622GE), supporting several types of intervals, this index will be a concatenation of the port index and interval type. Interval type can indicate: 1 minute, 15 minutes, 1 hour, 24 hours. For the exact formula, see device specification.

ethIfIntervalNumber.name: ethIfIntervalNumber
ethIfIntervalNumber.description: The Interval Number. This number is between 1 and x, where 1 is the most recently completed interval and x is the least recently completed interval. For 15 minute intervals, usually x=96, but it can be different, depending on device capabilities.

ethIfIntervalStatus.name: ethIfIntervalStatus
ethIfIntervalStatus.description: The status of the interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

ethIfIntervalInFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInFrames
ethIfIntervalInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInOctets.name: ethIfIntervalInOctets
ethIfIntervalInOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of received octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors.name: ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors
ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, which are not complete (The result of dividing the number of bits by 8 is not an Integer), encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalFCSErrors.name: ethIfIntervalFCSErrors
ethIfIntervalFCSErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames that didn't pass the FCS test, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalLengthError.name: ethIfIntervalLengthError
ethIfIntervalLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutFrames
ethIfIntervalOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutOctets.name: ethIfIntervalOutOctets
ethIfIntervalOutOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames
ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by exactly one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by more than one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions.name: ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions
ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames for which the first transmission attempt was delayed due to a busy media, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalLateCollisions.name: ethIfIntervalLateCollisions
ethIfIntervalLateCollisions.description: The counter associated with the number of times that a collision was detected later than the first 64 bytes of the frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors.name: ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors
ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped
ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Receive direction to the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped
ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Transmit direction to the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInOctets.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInOctets
ethIfIntervalOverflowInOctets.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInOctets counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowFCSErrors.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowFCSErrors
ethIfIntervalOverflowFCSErrors.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalFCSErrors counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutOctets.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutOctets
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutOctets.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutOctets counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowMultipleCollisionFr.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowMultipleCollisionFr.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInUnicastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInUnicastFrames
ethIfIntervalInUnicastFrames.description: The number of received Unicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutUnicastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutUnicastFrames
ethIfIntervalOutUnicastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Unicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInMulticastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInMulticastFrames
ethIfIntervalInMulticastFrames.description: The number of received Multicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutMulticastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutMulticastFrames
ethIfIntervalOutMulticastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Multicast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInBroadcastFrames
ethIfIntervalInBroadcastFrames.description: The number of received Broadcast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutBroadcastFrames
ethIfIntervalOutBroadcastFrames.description: The number of transmitted Broadcast frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInDiscardFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInDiscardFrames
ethIfIntervalInDiscardFrames.description: The number of received Discarded frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutDiscardFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutDiscardFrames
ethIfIntervalOutDiscardFrames.description: The number of transmitted Discarded frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalInPauseFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInPauseFrames
ethIfIntervalInPauseFrames.description: The number of received Pause frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOutPauseFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutPauseFrames
ethIfIntervalOutPauseFrames.description: The number of transmitted Pause frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInUnicastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInUnicastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInUnicastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInUnicastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutUnicastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutUnicastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutUnicastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutUnicastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInMulticastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInMulticastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInMulticastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInMulticastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutMulticastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutMulticastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutMulticastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutMulticastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInBroadcastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInBroadcastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInBroadcastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutBroadcastFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutBroadcastFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutBroadcastFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutBroadcastFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInDiscardFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInDiscardFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInDiscardFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInDiscardFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutDiscardFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutDiscardFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutDiscardFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutDiscardFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowInPauseFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowInPauseFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowInPauseFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalInPauseFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethIfIntervalOverflowOutPauseFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOverflowOutPauseFrames
ethIfIntervalOverflowOutPauseFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethIfIntervalOutPauseFrames counter has overflowed in the interval.

ethPerformanceMode.name: ethPerformanceMode
ethPerformanceMode.description: This object indicates whether OK or Fail statistics will be counted.

ethIfPerfEntry.name: ethIfPerfEntry
ethIfPerfEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Performance table.

ethIfPerfInOkFrames.name: ethIfPerfInOkFrames
ethIfPerfInOkFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received OK frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done.

ethIfPerfOutOkFrames.name: ethIfPerfOutOkFrames
ethIfPerfOutOkFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted OK frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done.

ethIfPerfTotalCollisions.name: ethIfPerfTotalCollisions
ethIfPerfTotalCollisions.description: The counter associated with the total number of collisions of any type encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done

ethIfPerfInOkOctets.name: ethIfPerfInOkOctets
ethIfPerfInOkOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of received OK Octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done.

ethOamCfmDefectCondition.name: ethOamCfmDefectCondition
ethOamCfmDefectCondition.description: This trap indicates that a MEP has a persistent defect condition.

radMepTable.name: radMepTable
radMepTable.description: MEG End Point (MEP) configuration table associated with Maitenance Entity Group (MEG) End Point. MEP is a short name for an expanded ETH flow point that includes a compound ETH Segment flow termination function, which marks the end point of an ETH ME, and a compound ETH Diagnostic flow function.

radOamIdx1.name: radOamIdx1
radOamIdx1.description: This object may indicate the Bridge Index or Configuration index.

radOamEvcIdx.name: radOamEvcIdx
radOamEvcIdx.description: This object indicates the Index of the EVC (Ethernet Virtual Circuit) that the MEP is associated to.

radMepIdx.name: radMepIdx
radMepIdx.description: This object indicates the ID of the MEP being accessed.

radMepRowStatus.name: radMepRowStatus
radMepRowStatus.description: This attribute allows to create/delete a row in this table.

radMepLocalMepId.name: radMepLocalMepId
radMepLocalMepId.description: This object indicates the local MEP ID.

radMepRemoteMepId.name: radMepRemoteMepId
radMepRemoteMepId.description: This atribute is currently implemneted at radMepCcTable, that supports multicast.

radMepOamMode.name: radMepOamMode
radMepOamMode.description: This object determines the OAM mode of the MEP: disabled - no CC is initiated nor responded initiate - the device initiates and responds to CC react - the device does not initiate a CC, but responds to CC.

radMepContinuityVerMode.name: radMepContinuityVerMode
radMepContinuityVerMode.description: This object determines the OAM behavior of the MEP: disabled - no CC is done cc_based - CC is done based on incoming messages lb_based - CC is done based on loopback messages.

radMepMeLevel.name: radMepMeLevel
radMepMeLevel.description: At any point in a network, ME Level is used to distinguish between OAM signals belonging to different nested MEs. Maintenance Entity Levels are defined as follows: 0,1,2 are assigned to customers 3,4 are assigned to providers 5,6,7 are assigned to operators.

radMepOamDestAddrType.name: radMepOamDestAddrType
radMepOamDestAddrType.description: This object determines if the OAM messages are sent to user defined unicast address, or to RAD proprietary multicast address.

radMepOamDestMacAddr.name: radMepOamDestMacAddr
radMepOamDestMacAddr.description: This object determines the MAC address that OAM packets are sent to.

radMepDefaultPriority.name: radMepDefaultPriority
radMepDefaultPriority.description: This object defines the priority of the OAM messages sent when no service is defined on EVC. If a service is defined, the OAM messages will get the highest service priority existing on the EVC.

radMepCcStatus.name: radMepCcStatus
radMepCcStatus.description: This object indicates the Continuity Check (CC) status.

radMepOamProtocol.name: radMepOamProtocol
radMepOamProtocol.description: Determines whether to use proprietary OAM mechanism, or to use the standard (IEEE 802.1ag, ITU-T Y.1731).

radMepMdId.name: radMepMdId
radMepMdId.description: The index of the Maintenance Domain in the radMdTable (radMdIndex).

radMepMaFormat.name: radMepMaFormat
radMepMaFormat.description: The type (and thereby format) of the Maintenance Association Name.

radMepSpVlanId.name: radMepSpVlanId
radMepSpVlanId.description: The SP (Service Provider) VLAN used when sending an OAM message.

radMepCcInterval.name: radMepCcInterval
radMepCcInterval.description: Indicates the interval at which CCMs are sent by a MEP Valid only if radMepOamMode = initiate(4).

radMepTransmitLbmDestMacAddress.name: radMepTransmitLbmDestMacAddress
radMepTransmitLbmDestMacAddress.description: The Target MAC Address Field to be transmitted in the Loopback Message: For unicast MAC Address this is the unicast destination MAC address. For multicast MAC Address, this variable is read-only. This address will be used if the value of radMepTransmitLbmDestIsMepId is no (2). 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.3.2:b.

radMepTransmitLbmDestMepId.name: radMepTransmitLbmDestMepId
radMepTransmitLbmDestMepId.description: The MEPID of another MEP in the same MA to which the LBM is to be sent. This address will be used if the value of radMepTransmitLbmDestIsMepId is yes (3). 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.3.2:b.

radMepTransmitLbmDestIsMepId.name: radMepTransmitLbmDestIsMepId
radMepTransmitLbmDestIsMepId.description: yes (3) indicates that MEPID of the target MEP is used for loopback transmission. no (2) indicates that unicast destination MAC address of the target MEP is used. 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.3.2:b.

radMepTransmitLbmMassages.name: radMepTransmitLbmMassages
radMepTransmitLbmMassages.description: The number of Loopback messages to be transmitted.

radMepTransmitLbmVlanPriority.name: radMepTransmitLbmVlanPriority
radMepTransmitLbmVlanPriority.description: The priority to be used in the VLAN tag, if present, in the transmitted frame. The default value is CCM priority. 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.3.2:e

radMepTransmitLbmVlanDropEnable.name: radMepTransmitLbmVlanDropEnable
radMepTransmitLbmVlanDropEnable.description: Drop Enable bit to be used in the VLAN tag, if present, in the transmitted frame. 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.3.2:e

radMepLbrIn.name: radMepLbrIn
radMepLbrIn.description: Total number of valid, in-order Loopback Replies received.

radMepLbrInOutOfOrder.name: radMepLbrInOutOfOrder
radMepLbrInOutOfOrder.description: The total number of valid, out-of-order Loopback Replies received.

radMepLbmOut.name: radMepLbmOut
radMepLbmOut.description: Total number of Loopback Messages transmitted.

radMepTransmitLtmTargetMacAddress.name: radMepTransmitLtmTargetMacAddress
radMepTransmitLtmTargetMacAddress.description: The Target MAC Address Field to be transmitted in the Link Trace Message: A unicast destination MAC address. This address will be used if the value of radMepTransmitLtmTargetIsMepId is no (2). 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.4.2:c.

radMepTransmitLtmTargetMepId.name: radMepTransmitLtmTargetMepId
radMepTransmitLtmTargetMepId.description: The MEPID of another MEP in the same MA to which LTM is to be transmitted. This address will be used if the value of radMepTransmitLtmTargetIsMepId is yes (3). 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.4.2:c.

radMepTransmitLtmTargetIsMepId.name: radMepTransmitLtmTargetIsMepId
radMepTransmitLtmTargetIsMepId.description: yes (3) indicates that MEPID of the target MEP is used for Linktrace transmission. no (2) indicates that unicast destination MAC address of the target MEP is used. 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.4.2:c.

radMepTransmitLtmTtl.name: radMepTransmitLtmTtl
radMepTransmitLtmTtl.description: The LTM TTL field. Default value, if not specified, is 64. The TTL field indicates the number of hops remaining to the LTM. Decremented by 1 each Linktrace Responder that handles the LTM. The value received in the LTM is returned in the LTR. If 0 on input, the LTM is not transmitted to the next hop. 802.1ag clause 12.14.7.4.2:b and 21.8.4.

radMepTransmitLtmActivationCmd.name: radMepTransmitLtmActivationCmd
radMepTransmitLtmActivationCmd.description: Activation command for starting Loop Trace. Set will be always to 'on' value. After operation was finished, Agent will turn the value to 'off'.

ethOamServiceTable.name: ethOamServiceTable
ethOamServiceTable.description: Service configuration table associated with Services running on a MEP.

ethOamServiceIdx.name: ethOamServiceIdx
ethOamServiceIdx.description: This object indicates the Index of the service being accessed.

ethOamServiceRowStatus.name: ethOamServiceRowStatus
ethOamServiceRowStatus.description: This attribute allows to create/delete a row in this table.

ethOamServicePriority.name: ethOamServicePriority
ethOamServicePriority.description: This object determines the priority of the service. It is sent as P bits in an OAM message originated by this service.

ethOamServicePmEnable.name: ethOamServicePmEnable
ethOamServicePmEnable.description: This object determines PM (Performance Monitoring) shall be enabled or not for the service.

ethOamServiceFrameLossRatioThresh.name: ethOamServiceFrameLossRatioThresh
ethOamServiceFrameLossRatioThresh.description: This object determines the Frame Loss ratio threshold in exponent of 1/10. That is, a value of 4 means that the threshold is 1E-4.

ethOamServiceDelayThresh.name: ethOamServiceDelayThresh
ethOamServiceDelayThresh.description: This object determines the delay threshold defined for this service, in measurement unit of 0.1 msec.

ethOamServiceDelayVarThresh.name: ethOamServiceDelayVarThresh
ethOamServiceDelayVarThresh.description: This object determines the delay variation threshold defined for this service, in measurement unit of 0.1 msec.

ethOamServiceUnavailRatioThresh.name: ethOamServiceUnavailRatioThresh
ethOamServiceUnavailRatioThresh.description: This object determines the Unavailability ratio threshold in exponent of 1/10. That is, a value of 4 means that the threshold is 1E-4.

ethOamServiceTxFrames.name: ethOamServiceTxFrames
ethOamServiceTxFrames.description: Counts the number of frames trnasmitted by since the time the service is up.

ethOamServiceOverflowTxFrames.name: ethOamServiceOverflowTxFrames
ethOamServiceOverflowTxFrames.description: The number of times the associated ethOamServiceTxFrames counter has overflowed.

ethOamServiceFrameLoss.name: ethOamServiceFrameLoss
ethOamServiceFrameLoss.description: Counts the number of frames lost since the time the service is up.

ethOamServiceOverflowFrameLoss.name: ethOamServiceOverflowFrameLoss
ethOamServiceOverflowFrameLoss.description: The number of times the associated ethOamServiceFrameLoss counter has overflowed.

ethOamServiceFrameLossRatio.name: ethOamServiceFrameLossRatio
ethOamServiceFrameLossRatio.description: Indicates the ratio of the lost frames since the time the service is up. The value is the ratio multiplied by 1E10. 0xFFFFFFFF will be returned for ratio greater than 4/10 (40%).

ethOamServiceElapsedTime.name: ethOamServiceElapsedTime
ethOamServiceElapsedTime.description: Indicates the time elapsed in seconds since the time the service is up.

ethOamServiceUnavailSec.name: ethOamServiceUnavailSec
ethOamServiceUnavailSec.description: Indicates the number of unavailable seconds since the time the service is up.

ethOamServiceUnavailRatio.name: ethOamServiceUnavailRatio
ethOamServiceUnavailRatio.description: Indicates the ratio of the unavailable seconds since the time the service is up. The value is the ratio multiplied by 1E10. 0xFFFFFFFF will be returned for ratio greater than 4/10 (40%).

ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelay.name: ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelay
ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelay.description: Indicates the number of frames arrived with delay greater than the delay threshold.

ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelay.name: ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelay
ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelay.description: Indicates the number of times the associated ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelay counter has overflowed.

ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelayVar.name: ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelayVar
ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelayVar.description: Indicates the number of frames arrived with delay variation greater than the delay variation threshold.

ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelayVar.name: ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelayVar
ethOamServiceOverflowFramesAboveDelayVar.description: Indicates the number of times the associated ethOamServiceFramesAboveDelayVar counter has overflowed.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDelayThresh.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDelayThresh
ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDelayThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in the current interval at a delay greater than the threshold value defined for the service.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDelayThresh.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDelayThresh
ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDelayThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in the current interval at a delay lower than or equal to the threshold value defined for the service.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDVarThresh.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDVarThresh
ethOamSvcCurrFramesAboveDVarThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in the current interval at a delay variation greater than the threshold value defined for the service.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDVarThresh.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDVarThresh
ethOamSvcCurrFramesBelowDVarThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in the current interval at a delay variation lower than or equal to the threshold value defined for the service.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesTxCounter.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesTxCounter
ethOamSvcCurrFramesTxCounter.description: Number of trnasmitted frames in the current interval.

ethOamSvcCurrFramesLossCounter.name: ethOamSvcCurrFramesLossCounter
ethOamSvcCurrFramesLossCounter.description: Number of lost frames in the current interval.

ethOamSvcCurrMinRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcCurrMinRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcCurrMinRoundTripDelay.description: The mininal value of round trip delay in the current interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDelay.description: The maximum value of round trip delay in the current interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDelay.description: The average round trip delay in the current interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDVar.name: ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDVar
ethOamSvcCurrMaxRoundTripDVar.description: The maximum value of round trip delay variation in the current interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDVar.name: ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDVar
ethOamSvcCurrAvgRoundTripDVar.description: The average round trip delay variation in the current interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcCurrElapsedTime.name: ethOamSvcCurrElapsedTime
ethOamSvcCurrElapsedTime.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current interval.

ethOamSvcCurrUnavailSec.name: ethOamSvcCurrUnavailSec
ethOamSvcCurrUnavailSec.description: The number of seconds that the service was unavailable in the current interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalNum.name: ethOamSvcIntervalNum
ethOamSvcIntervalNum.description: The Interval index, which is actualy the Interval number, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals exist).

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDelayThresh.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDelayThresh
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDelayThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in a delay greater than the threshold value defined for the service in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDelayThresh.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDelayThresh
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDelayThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in a delay lower than the threshold value defined for the service in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDVarThresh.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDVarThresh
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesAboveDVarThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in a delay variation greater than the threshold value defined for the service in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDVarThresh.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDVarThresh
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesBelowDVarThresh.description: Number of frames that arrived in a delay variation lower than the threshold value defined for the service in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesTxCounter.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesTxCounter
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesTxCounter.description: Number of trnasmitted frames in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalFramesLossCounter.name: ethOamSvcIntervalFramesLossCounter
ethOamSvcIntervalFramesLossCounter.description: Number of lost frames in the selected interval.

ethOamSvcIntervalMinRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcIntervalMinRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcIntervalMinRoundTripDelay.description: The mininal value of round trip delay in the selected interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDelay.description: The maximum value of round trip delay in the selected interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDelay.name: ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDelay
ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDelay.description: The average round trip delay in the selected interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDVar.name: ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDVar
ethOamSvcIntervalMaxRoundTripDVar.description: The maximum value of round trip delay variation in the selected interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDVar.name: ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDVar
ethOamSvcIntervalAvgRoundTripDVar.description: The average round trip delay variation in the selected interval. Values units are of 0.1 msec.

ethOamSvcIntervalUnavailSec.name: ethOamSvcIntervalUnavailSec
ethOamSvcIntervalUnavailSec.description: The number of seconds that the service was unavailable in the selected interval.
